72/*
73 * Flag to control whether to check the TCP checksum.
74 *
75 * In at least some Solaris network traces, there are packets with bad
76 * TCP checksums, but the traffic appears to indicate that the packets
77 * *were* received; the packets were probably sent by the host on which
78 * the capture was being done, on a network interface to which
79 * checksumming was offloaded, so that DLPI supplied an un-checksummed
80 * packet to the capture program but a checksummed packet got put onto
81 * the wire.
82 */
83static gboolean tcp_check_checksum = FALSE(0);

389/* static expert_field ei_mptcp_stream_incomplete = EI_INIT; */
390/* static expert_field ei_mptcp_analysis_dsn_out_of_order = EI_INIT; */
391
392/* Some protocols such as encrypted DCE/RPCoverHTTP have dependencies
393 * from one PDU to the next PDU and require that they are called in sequence.
394 * These protocols would not be able to handle PDUs coming out of order
395 * or for example when a PDU is seen twice, like for retransmissions.
396 * This preference can be set for such protocols to make sure that we don't
397 * invoke the subdissectors for retransmitted or out-of-order segments.
398 */
399static gboolean tcp_no_subdissector_on_error = TRUE(!(0));
400
401/*
402 * FF: (draft-ietf-tcpm-experimental-options-03)
403 * With this flag set we assume the option structure for experimental
404 * codepoints (253, 254) has a magic number field (first field after the
405 * Kind and Length). The magic number is used to differentiate different
406 * experiments and thus will be used in data dissection.
407 */
408static gboolean tcp_exp_options_with_magic = TRUE(!(0));
409
410/* Process info, currently discovered via IPFIX */
411static gboolean tcp_display_process_info = FALSE(0);
412

626
627static const char* tcp_conv_get_filter_type(conv_item_t* conv, conv_filter_type_e filter)
628{
629
630 if (filter == CONV_FT_SRC_PORT)
631 return "tcp.srcport";
632
633 if (filter == CONV_FT_DST_PORT)
634 return "tcp.dstport";
635
636 if (filter == CONV_FT_ANY_PORT)
637 return "tcp.port";
638
639 if(!conv) {
640 return CONV_FILTER_INVALID"INVALID";
641 }
642
643 if (filter == CONV_FT_SRC_ADDRESS) {
644 if (conv->src_address.type == AT_IPv4)
645 return "ip.src";
646 if (conv->src_address.type == AT_IPv6)
647 return "ipv6.src";
648 }
649
650 if (filter == CONV_FT_DST_ADDRESS) {
651 if (conv->dst_address.type == AT_IPv4)
652 return "ip.dst";
653 if (conv->dst_address.type == AT_IPv6)
654 return "ipv6.dst";
655 }
656
657 if (filter == CONV_FT_ANY_ADDRESS) {
658 if (conv->src_address.type == AT_IPv4)
659 return "ip.addr";
660 if (conv->src_address.type == AT_IPv6)
661 return "ipv6.addr";
662 }
663
664 return CONV_FILTER_INVALID"INVALID";
665}
666
667static ct_dissector_info_t tcp_ct_dissector_info = {&tcp_conv_get_filter_type};
668
669static int
670tcpip_conversation_packet(void *pct, packet_info *pinfo, epan_dissect_t *edt _U___attribute__((unused)), const void *vip)
671{
672 conv_hash_t *hash = (conv_hash_t*) pct;
673 const struct tcpheader *tcphdr=(const struct tcpheader *)vip;
674
675 add_conversation_table_data_with_conv_id(hash, &tcphdr->ip_src, &tcphdr->ip_dst, tcphdr->th_sport, tcphdr->th_dport, (conv_id_t) tcphdr->th_stream, 1, pinfo->fd->pkt_len,
676 &pinfo->rel_ts, &pinfo->abs_ts, &tcp_ct_dissector_info, PT_TCP);
677
678 return 1;
679}
680
681static int
682mptcpip_conversation_packet(void *pct, packet_info *pinfo, epan_dissect_t *edt _U___attribute__((unused)), const void *vip)
683{
684 conv_hash_t *hash = (conv_hash_t*) pct;
685 const struct tcp_analysis *tcpd=(const struct tcp_analysis *)vip;
686 const mptcp_meta_flow_t *meta=(const mptcp_meta_flow_t *)tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta;
687
688 add_conversation_table_data_with_conv_id(hash, &meta->ip_src, &meta->ip_dst,
689 meta->sport, meta->dport, (conv_id_t) tcpd->mptcp_analysis->stream, 1, pinfo->fd->pkt_len,
690 &pinfo->rel_ts, &pinfo->abs_ts, &tcp_ct_dissector_info, PT_TCP);
691
692 return 1;
693}

695static const char* tcp_host_get_filter_type(hostlist_talker_t* host, conv_filter_type_e filter)
696{
697 if (filter == CONV_FT_SRC_PORT)
698 return "tcp.srcport";
699
700 if (filter == CONV_FT_DST_PORT)
701 return "tcp.dstport";
702
703 if (filter == CONV_FT_ANY_PORT)
704 return "tcp.port";
705
706 if(!host) {
707 return CONV_FILTER_INVALID"INVALID";
708 }
709
710 if (filter == CONV_FT_SRC_ADDRESS) {
711 if (host->myaddress.type == AT_IPv4)
712 return "ip.src";
713 if (host->myaddress.type == AT_IPv6)
714 return "ipv6.src";
715 }
716
717 if (filter == CONV_FT_DST_ADDRESS) {
718 if (host->myaddress.type == AT_IPv4)
719 return "ip.dst";
720 if (host->myaddress.type == AT_IPv6)
721 return "ipv6.dst";
722 }
723
724 if (filter == CONV_FT_ANY_ADDRESS) {
725 if (host->myaddress.type == AT_IPv4)
726 return "ip.addr";
727 if (host->myaddress.type == AT_IPv6)
728 return "ipv6.addr";
729 }
730
731 return CONV_FILTER_INVALID"INVALID";
732}
733
734static hostlist_dissector_info_t tcp_host_dissector_info = {&tcp_host_get_filter_type};
735
736static int
737tcpip_hostlist_packet(void *pit, packet_info *pinfo, epan_dissect_t *edt _U___attribute__((unused)), const void *vip)
738{
739 conv_hash_t *hash = (conv_hash_t*) pit;
740 const struct tcpheader *tcphdr=(const struct tcpheader *)vip;
741
742 /* Take two "add" passes per packet, adding for each direction, ensures that all
743 packets are counted properly (even if address is sending to itself)
744 XXX - this could probably be done more efficiently inside hostlist_table */
745 add_hostlist_table_data(hash, &tcphdr->ip_src, tcphdr->th_sport, TRUE(!(0)), 1, pinfo->fd->pkt_len, &tcp_host_dissector_info, PT_TCP);
746 add_hostlist_table_data(hash, &tcphdr->ip_dst, tcphdr->th_dport, FALSE(0), 1, pinfo->fd->pkt_len, &tcp_host_dissector_info, PT_TCP);
747
748 return 1;
749}

751static gboolean
752tcp_filter_valid(packet_info *pinfo)
753{
754 return proto_is_frame_protocol(pinfo->layers, "tcp");
755}
756
757static gchar*
758tcp_build_filter(packet_info *pinfo)
759{
760 if( pinfo->net_src.type == AT_IPv4 && pinfo->net_dst.type == AT_IPv4 ) {
761 /* TCP over IPv4 */
762 return g_strdup_printf("(ip.addr eq %s and ip.addr eq %s) and (tcp.port eq %d and tcp.port eq %d)",
763 address_to_str(pinfo->pool, &pinfo->net_src),
764 address_to_str(pinfo->pool, &pinfo->net_dst),
765 pinfo->srcport, pinfo->destport );
766 }
767
768 if( pinfo->net_src.type == AT_IPv6 && pinfo->net_dst.type == AT_IPv6 ) {
769 /* TCP over IPv6 */
770 return g_strdup_printf("(ipv6.addr eq %s and ipv6.addr eq %s) and (tcp.port eq %d and tcp.port eq %d)",
771 address_to_str(pinfo->pool, &pinfo->net_src),
772 address_to_str(pinfo->pool, &pinfo->net_dst),
773 pinfo->srcport, pinfo->destport );
774 }
775
776 return NULL((void*)0);
777}
778
779gchar* tcp_follow_conv_filter(packet_info* pinfo, int* stream)
780{
781 conversation_t *conv;
782 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd;
783
784 if (((pinfo->net_src.type == AT_IPv4 && pinfo->net_dst.type == AT_IPv4) ||
785 (pinfo->net_src.type == AT_IPv6 && pinfo->net_dst.type == AT_IPv6))
786 && (conv=find_conversation(pinfo->num, &pinfo->src, &pinfo->dst, pinfo->ptype,
787 pinfo->srcport, pinfo->destport, 0)) != NULL((void*)0) )
788 {
789 /* TCP over IPv4/6 */
790 tcpd=get_tcp_conversation_data(conv, pinfo);
791 if (tcpd == NULL((void*)0))
792 return NULL((void*)0);
793
794 *stream = tcpd->stream;
795 return g_strdup_printf("tcp.stream eq %d", tcpd->stream);
796 }
797
798 return NULL((void*)0);
799}
800
801gchar* tcp_follow_index_filter(int stream)
802{
803 return g_strdup_printf("tcp.stream eq %d", stream);
804}
805
806gchar* tcp_follow_address_filter(address* src_addr, address* dst_addr, int src_port, int dst_port)
807{
808 const gchar *ip_version = src_addr->type == AT_IPv6 ? "v6" : "";
809 gchar src_addr_str[MAX_IP6_STR_LEN46];
810 gchar dst_addr_str[MAX_IP6_STR_LEN46];
811
812 address_to_str_buf(src_addr, src_addr_str, sizeof(src_addr_str));
813 address_to_str_buf(dst_addr, dst_addr_str, sizeof(dst_addr_str));
814
815 return g_strdup_printf("((ip%s.src eq %s and tcp.srcport eq %d) and "
816 "(ip%s.dst eq %s and tcp.dstport eq %d))"
817 " or "
818 "((ip%s.src eq %s and tcp.srcport eq %d) and "
819 "(ip%s.dst eq %s and tcp.dstport eq %d))",
820 ip_version, src_addr_str, src_port,
821 ip_version, dst_addr_str, dst_port,
822 ip_version, dst_addr_str, dst_port,
823 ip_version, src_addr_str, src_port);
824
825}
826
827typedef struct tcp_follow_tap_data
828{
829 tvbuff_t *tvb;
830 struct tcpheader* tcph;
831 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd;
832
833} tcp_follow_tap_data_t;
834
835static gboolean
836check_follow_fragments(follow_info_t *follow_info, gboolean is_server, guint32 acknowledged, guint32 packet_num)
837{
838 GList *fragment_entry;
839 follow_record_t *fragment, *follow_record;
840 guint32 lowest_seq;
841 gchar *dummy_str;
842
843 fragment_entry = g_list_first(follow_info->fragments[is_server]);
844 if (fragment_entry == NULL((void*)0))
845 return FALSE(0);
846
847 for (; fragment_entry != NULL((void*)0); fragment_entry = g_list_next(fragment_entry)((fragment_entry) ? (((GList *)(fragment_entry))->next) : (
(void*)0)))
848 {
849 fragment = (follow_record_t*)fragment_entry->data;
850 lowest_seq = fragment->seq;
851
852 if( GT_SEQ(lowest_seq, fragment->seq)((gint32)((fragment->seq) - (lowest_seq)) < 0) ) {
853 lowest_seq = fragment->seq;
854 }
855
856 if( LT_SEQ(fragment->seq, follow_info->seq[is_server])((gint32)((fragment->seq) - (follow_info->seq[is_server
])) < 0) ) {
857 guint32 newseq;
858 /* this sequence number seems dated, but
859 check the end to make sure it has no more
860 info than we have already seen */
861 newseq = fragment->seq + fragment->data->len;
862 if( GT_SEQ(newseq, follow_info->seq[is_server])((gint32)((follow_info->seq[is_server]) - (newseq)) < 0
) ) {
863 guint32 new_pos;
864
865 /* this one has more than we have seen. let's get the
866 payload that we have not seen. This happens when
867 part of this frame has been retransmitted */
868
869 new_pos = follow_info->seq[is_server] - fragment->seq;
870
871 if ( fragment->data->len > new_pos ) {
872 guint32 new_frag_size = fragment->data->len - new_pos;
873
874 follow_record = g_new0(follow_record_t,1)(follow_record_t *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (1)
; gsize __s = sizeof (follow_record_t); gpointer __p; if (__s
== 1) __p = g_malloc0 (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p (
__n) && (__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L *
2UL+1UL) / __s)) __p = g_malloc0 (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc0_n
(__n, __s); __p; }));
875
876 follow_record->is_server = is_server;
877 follow_record->packet_num = fragment->packet_num;
878 follow_record->seq = follow_info->seq[is_server] + new_frag_size;
879
880 follow_record->data = g_byte_array_append(g_byte_array_new(),
881 fragment->data->data + new_pos,
882 new_frag_size);
883
884 follow_info->payload = g_list_append(follow_info->payload, follow_record);
885 }
886
887 follow_info->seq[is_server] += (fragment->data->len - new_pos);
888 }
889
890 /* Remove the fragment from the list as the "new" part of it
891 * has been processed or its data has been seen already in
892 * another packet. */
893 g_byte_array_free(fragment->data, TRUE(!(0)));
894 g_free(fragment);
895 follow_info->fragments[is_server] = g_list_delete_link(follow_info->fragments[is_server], fragment_entry);
896 return TRUE(!(0));
897 }
898
899 if( EQ_SEQ(fragment->seq, follow_info->seq[is_server])(fragment->seq) == (follow_info->seq[is_server]) ) {
900 /* this fragment fits the stream */
901 if( fragment->data->len > 0 ) {
902 follow_info->payload = g_list_append(follow_info->payload, fragment);
903 }
904
905 follow_info->seq[is_server] += fragment->data->len;
906 follow_info->fragments[is_server] = g_list_delete_link(follow_info->fragments[is_server], fragment_entry);
907 return TRUE(!(0));
908 }
909 }
910
911 if( GT_SEQ(acknowledged, lowest_seq)((gint32)((lowest_seq) - (acknowledged)) < 0) ) {
912 /* There are frames missing in the capture file that were seen
913 * by the receiving host. Add dummy stream chunk with the data
914 * "[xxx bytes missing in capture file]".
915 */
916 dummy_str = g_strdup_printf("[%d bytes missing in capture file]",
917 (int)(lowest_seq - follow_info->seq[is_server]) );
918
919 follow_record = g_new0(follow_record_t,1)(follow_record_t *) (__extension__ ({ gsize __n = (gsize) (1)
; gsize __s = sizeof (follow_record_t); gpointer __p; if (__s
== 1) __p = g_malloc0 (__n); else if (__builtin_constant_p (
__n) && (__s == 0 || __n <= (9223372036854775807L *
2UL+1UL) / __s)) __p = g_malloc0 (__n * __s); else __p = g_malloc0_n
(__n, __s); __p; }));
920
921 follow_record->data = g_byte_array_append(g_byte_array_new(),
922 dummy_str,
923 (guint)strlen(dummy_str)+1);
924 g_free(dummy_str);
925 follow_record->is_server = is_server;
926 follow_record->packet_num = packet_num;
927 follow_record->seq = lowest_seq;
928
929 follow_info->seq[is_server] = lowest_seq;
930 follow_info->payload = g_list_append(follow_info->payload, follow_record);
931 return TRUE(!(0));
932 }
933
934 return FALSE(0);
935}

1097/* if we have no key for this connection, some conversion become impossible,
1098 * thus return false
1099 */
1100static
1101gboolean
1102mptcp_convert_dsn(guint64 dsn, mptcp_meta_flow_t *meta, enum mptcp_dsn_conversion conv, gboolean relative, guint64 *result ) {
1103
1104 *result = dsn;
1105
1106 /* if relative is set then we need the 64 bits version anyway
1107 * we assume no wrapping was done on the 32 lsb so this may be wrong for elphant flows
1108 */
1109 if(conv == DSN_CONV_32_TO_64 || relative) {
1110
1111 if(!(meta->static_flags & MPTCP_META_HAS_BASE_DSN_MSB0x01)) {
1112 /* can't do those without the expected_idsn based on the key */
1113 return FALSE(0);
1114 }
1115 }
1116
1117 if(conv == DSN_CONV_32_TO_64) {
1118 *result = KEEP_32MSB_OF_GUINT64(meta->base_dsn) | dsn;
1119 }
1120
1121 if(relative) {
1122 *result -= meta->base_dsn;
1123 }
1124
1125 if(conv == DSN_CONV_64_TO_32) {
1126 *result = (guint32) *result;
1127 }
1128
1129 return TRUE(!(0));
1130}

1200/* add a new subflow to an mptcp connection */
1201static void
1202mptcp_attach_subflow(struct mptcp_analysis* mptcpd, struct tcp_analysis* tcpd) {
1203

1205 wmem_list_prepend(mptcpd->subflows, tcpd);

1211
1212
1213struct tcp_analysis *
1214get_tcp_conversation_data(conversation_t *conv, packet_info *pinfo)
1215{
1216 int direction;
1217 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd;
1218 gboolean clear_ta = TRUE(!(0));
1219
1220 /* Did the caller supply the conversation pointer? */
1221 if( conv==NULL((void*)0) ) {
1222 /* If the caller didn't supply a conversation, don't
1223 * clear the analysis, it may be needed */
1224 clear_ta = FALSE(0);
1225 conv = find_or_create_conversation(pinfo);
1226 }
1227
1228 /* Get the data for this conversation */
1229 tcpd=(struct tcp_analysis *)conversation_get_proto_data(conv, proto_tcp);
1230
1231 /* If the conversation was just created or it matched a
1232 * conversation with template options, tcpd will not
1233 * have been initialized. So, initialize
1234 * a new tcpd structure for the conversation.
1235 */
1236 if (!tcpd) {
1237 tcpd = init_tcp_conversation_data(pinfo);
1238 conversation_add_proto_data(conv, proto_tcp, tcpd);
1239 }
1240
1241 if (!tcpd) {
1242 return NULL((void*)0);
1243 }
1244
1245 /* check direction and get ua lists */
1246 direction=cmp_address(&pinfo->src, &pinfo->dst);
1247 /* if the addresses are equal, match the ports instead */
1248 if(direction==0) {
1249 direction= (pinfo->srcport > pinfo->destport) ? 1 : -1;
1250 }
1251 if(direction>=0) {
1252 tcpd->fwd=&(tcpd->flow1);
1253 tcpd->rev=&(tcpd->flow2);
1254 } else {
1255 tcpd->fwd=&(tcpd->flow2);
1256 tcpd->rev=&(tcpd->flow1);
1257 }
1258
1259 if (clear_ta) {
1260 tcpd->ta=NULL((void*)0);
1261 }
1262 return tcpd;
1263}

1265/* Attach process info to a flow */
1266/* XXX - We depend on the TCP dissector finding the conversation first */
1267void
1268add_tcp_process_info(guint32 frame_num, address *local_addr, address *remote_addr, guint16 local_port, guint16 remote_port, guint32 uid, guint32 pid, gchar *username, gchar *command) {
1269 conversation_t *conv;
1270 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd;
1271 tcp_flow_t *flow = NULL((void*)0);
1272
1273 if (!tcp_display_process_info)
1274 return;
1275
1276 conv = find_conversation(frame_num, local_addr, remote_addr, PT_TCP, local_port, remote_port, 0);
1277 if (!conv) {
1278 return;
1279 }
1280
1281 tcpd = (struct tcp_analysis *)conversation_get_proto_data(conv, proto_tcp);
1282 if (!tcpd) {
1283 return;
1284 }
1285
1286 if (cmp_address(local_addr, &conv->key_ptr->addr1) == 0 && local_port == conv->key_ptr->port1) {
1287 flow = &tcpd->flow1;
1288 } else if (cmp_address(remote_addr, &conv->key_ptr->addr1) == 0 && remote_port == conv->key_ptr->port1) {
1289 flow = &tcpd->flow2;
1290 }
1291 if (!flow || (flow->process_info && flow->process_info->command)) {
1292 return;
1293 }
1294
1295 if (flow->process_info == NULL((void*)0))
1296 flow->process_info = wmem_new0(wmem_file_scope(), struct tcp_process_info_t)((struct tcp_process_info_t*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_file_scope()),
sizeof(struct tcp_process_info_t)));
1297
1298 flow->process_info->process_uid = uid;
1299 flow->process_info->process_pid = pid;
1300 flow->process_info->username = wmem_strdup(wmem_file_scope(), username);
1301 flow->process_info->command = wmem_strdup(wmem_file_scope(), command);
1302}

1374/* if we know that a PDU starts inside this segment, return the adjusted
1375 offset to where that PDU starts or just return offset back
1376 and let TCP try to find out what it can about this segment
1377*/
1378static int
1379scan_for_next_pdu(tvbuff_t *tvb, proto_tree *tcp_tree, packet_info *pinfo, int offset, guint32 seq, guint32 nxtseq, wmem_tree_t *multisegment_pdus)
1380{
1381 struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *msp=NULL((void*)0);
1382
1383 if(!pinfo->fd->flags.visited) {
1384 msp=(struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *)wmem_tree_lookup32_le(multisegment_pdus, seq-1);
1385 if(msp) {
1386 /* If this is a continuation of a PDU started in a
1387 * previous segment we need to update the last_frame
1388 * variables.
1389 */
1390 if(seq>msp->seq && seq<msp->nxtpdu) {
1391 msp->last_frame=pinfo->num;
1392 msp->last_frame_time=pinfo->abs_ts;
1393 print_pdu_tracking_data(pinfo, tvb, tcp_tree, msp);
1394 }
1395
1396 /* If this segment is completely within a previous PDU
1397 * then we just skip this packet
1398 */
1399 if(seq>msp->seq && nxtseq<=msp->nxtpdu) {
1400 return -1;
1401 }
1402 if(seq<msp->nxtpdu && nxtseq>msp->nxtpdu) {
1403 offset+=msp->nxtpdu-seq;
1404 return offset;
1405 }
1406
1407 }
1408 } else {
1409 /* First we try to find the start and transfer time for a PDU.
1410 * We only print this for the very first segment of a PDU
1411 * and only for PDUs spanning multiple segments.
1412 * Se we look for if there was any multisegment PDU started
1413 * just BEFORE the end of this segment. I.e. either inside this
1414 * segment or in a previous segment.
1415 * Since this might also match PDUs that are completely within
1416 * this segment we also verify that the found PDU does span
1417 * beyond the end of this segment.
1418 */
1419 msp=(struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *)wmem_tree_lookup32_le(multisegment_pdus, nxtseq-1);
1420 if(msp) {
1421 if(pinfo->num==msp->first_frame) {
1422 proto_item *item;
1423 nstime_t ns;
1424
1425 item=proto_tree_add_uint(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_pdu_last_frame, tvb, 0, 0, msp->last_frame);
1426 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
1427
1428 nstime_delta(&ns, &msp->last_frame_time, &pinfo->abs_ts);
1429 item = proto_tree_add_time(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_pdu_time,
1430 tvb, 0, 0, &ns);
1431 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
1432 }
1433 }
1434
1435 /* Second we check if this segment is part of a PDU started
1436 * prior to the segment (seq-1)
1437 */
1438 msp=(struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *)wmem_tree_lookup32_le(multisegment_pdus, seq-1);
1439 if(msp) {
1440 /* If this segment is completely within a previous PDU
1441 * then we just skip this packet
1442 */
1443 if(seq>msp->seq && nxtseq<=msp->nxtpdu) {
1444 print_pdu_tracking_data(pinfo, tvb, tcp_tree, msp);
1445 return -1;
1446 }
1447
1448 if(seq<msp->nxtpdu && nxtseq>msp->nxtpdu) {
1449 offset+=msp->nxtpdu-seq;
1450 return offset;
1451 }
1452 }
1453
1454 }
1455 return offset;
1456}
1457
1458/* if we saw a PDU that extended beyond the end of the segment,
1459 use this function to remember where the next pdu starts
1460*/
1461struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *
1462pdu_store_sequencenumber_of_next_pdu(packet_info *pinfo, guint32 seq, guint32 nxtpdu, wmem_tree_t *multisegment_pdus)
1463{
1464 struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *msp;
1465
1466 msp=wmem_new(wmem_file_scope(), struct tcp_multisegment_pdu)((struct tcp_multisegment_pdu*)wmem_alloc((wmem_file_scope())
, sizeof(struct tcp_multisegment_pdu)));
1467 msp->nxtpdu=nxtpdu;
1468 msp->seq=seq;
1469 msp->first_frame=pinfo->num;
1470 msp->last_frame=pinfo->num;
1471 msp->last_frame_time=pinfo->abs_ts;
1472 msp->flags=0;
1473 wmem_tree_insert32(multisegment_pdus, seq, (void *)msp);
1474 /*g_warning("pdu_store_sequencenumber_of_next_pdu: seq %u", seq);*/
1475 return msp;
1476}
1477
1478/* This is called for SYN and SYN+ACK packets and the purpose is to verify
1479 * that we have seen window scaling in both directions.
1480 * If we can't find window scaling being set in both directions
1481 * that means it was present in the SYN but not in the SYN+ACK
1482 * (or the SYN was missing) and then we disable the window scaling
1483 * for this tcp session.
1484 */
1485static void
1486verify_tcp_window_scaling(gboolean is_synack, struct tcp_analysis *tcpd)
1487{
1488 if( tcpd->fwd->win_scale==-1 ) {
1489 /* We know window scaling will not be used as:
1490 * a) this is the SYN and it does not have the WS option
1491 * (we set the reverse win_scale also in case we miss
1492 * the SYN/ACK)
1493 * b) this is the SYN/ACK and either the SYN packet has not
1494 * been seen or it did have the WS option. As the SYN/ACK
1495 * does not have the WS option, window scaling will not be used.
1496 *
1497 * Setting win_scale to -2 to indicate that we can
1498 * trust the window_size value in the TCP header.
1499 */
1500 tcpd->fwd->win_scale = -2;
1501 tcpd->rev->win_scale = -2;
1502
1503 } else if( is_synack && tcpd->rev->win_scale==-2 ) {
1504 /* The SYN/ACK has the WS option, while the SYN did not,
1505 * this should not happen, but the endpoints will not
1506 * have used window scaling, so we will neither
1507 */
1508 tcpd->fwd->win_scale = -2;
1509 }
1510}
1511
1512/* given a tcpd, returns the mptcp_subflow that sides with meta */
1513static struct mptcp_subflow *
1514mptcp_select_subflow_from_meta(const struct tcp_analysis *tcpd, const mptcp_meta_flow_t *meta)
1515{
1516 /* select the tcp_flow with appropriate direction */
1517 if( tcpd->flow1.mptcp_subflow->meta == meta) {
1518 return tcpd->flow1.mptcp_subflow;
1519 }
1520 else {
1521 return tcpd->flow2.mptcp_subflow;
1522 }
1523}
1524
1525/* if we saw a window scaling option, store it for future reference
1526*/
1527static void
1528pdu_store_window_scale_option(guint8 ws, struct tcp_analysis *tcpd)
1529{
1530 if (tcpd)
1531 tcpd->fwd->win_scale=ws;
1532}
1533
1534/* when this function returns, it will (if createflag) populate the ta pointer.
1535 */
1536static void
1537tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(guint32 frame, guint32 seq, guint32 ack, gboolean createflag, struct tcp_analysis *tcpd)
1538{
1539
1540 wmem_tree_key_t key[4];
1541
1542 key[0].length = 1;
1543 key[0].key = &frame;
1544
1545 key[1].length = 1;
1546 key[1].key = &seq;
1547
1548 key[2].length = 1;
1549 key[2].key = &ack;
1550
1551 key[3].length = 0;
1552 key[3].key = NULL((void*)0);
1553
1554 if (!tcpd) {
1555 return;
1556 }
1557
1558 tcpd->ta = (struct tcp_acked *)wmem_tree_lookup32_array(tcpd->acked_table, key);
1559 if((!tcpd->ta) && createflag) {
1560 tcpd->ta = wmem_new0(wmem_file_scope(), struct tcp_acked)((struct tcp_acked*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_file_scope()), sizeof(struct
tcp_acked)));
1561 wmem_tree_insert32_array(tcpd->acked_table, key, (void *)tcpd->ta);
1562 }
1563}
1564
1565
1566/* fwd contains a list of all segments processed but not yet ACKed in the
1567 * same direction as the current segment.
1568 * rev contains a list of all segments received but not yet ACKed in the
1569 * opposite direction to the current segment.
1570 *
1571 * New segments are always added to the head of the fwd/rev lists.
1572 *
1573 */
1574static void
1575tcp_analyze_sequence_number(packet_info *pinfo, guint32 seq, guint32 ack, guint32 seglen, guint16 flags, guint32 window, struct tcp_analysis *tcpd)
1576{
1577 tcp_unacked_t *ual=NULL((void*)0);
1578 tcp_unacked_t *prevual=NULL((void*)0);
1579 guint32 nextseq;
1580 int ackcount;
1581
1582#if 0
1583 printf("\nanalyze_sequence numbers frame:%u\n",pinfo->num);
1584 printf("FWD list lastflags:0x%04x base_seq:%u:\n",tcpd->fwd->lastsegmentflags,tcpd->fwd->base_seq);
1585 for(ual=tcpd->fwd->segments; ual; ual=ual->next)
1586 printf("Frame:%d Seq:%u Nextseq:%u\n",ual->frame,ual->seq,ual->nextseq);
1587 printf("REV list lastflags:0x%04x base_seq:%u:\n",tcpd->rev->lastsegmentflags,tcpd->rev->base_seq);
1588 for(ual=tcpd->rev->segments; ual; ual=ual->next)
1589 printf("Frame:%d Seq:%u Nextseq:%u\n",ual->frame,ual->seq,ual->nextseq);
1590#endif
1591
1592 if (!tcpd) {
1593 return;
1594 }
1595
1596 /* if this is the first segment for this list we need to store the
1597 * base_seq
1598 * We use TCP_S_SAW_SYN/SYNACK to distinguish between client and server
1599 *
1600 * Start relative seq and ack numbers at 1 if this
1601 * is not a SYN packet. This makes the relative
1602 * seq/ack numbers to be displayed correctly in the
1603 * event that the SYN or SYN/ACK packet is not seen
1604 * (this solves bug 1542)
1605 */
1606 if( !(tcpd->fwd->static_flags & TCP_S_BASE_SEQ_SET0x01)) {
1607 if(flags & TH_SYN0x0002) {
1608 tcpd->fwd->base_seq = seq;
1609 tcpd->fwd->static_flags |= (flags & TH_ACK0x0010) ? TCP_S_SAW_SYNACK0x05 : TCP_S_SAW_SYN0x03;
1610 }
1611 else {
1612 tcpd->fwd->base_seq = seq-1;
1613 }
1614 tcpd->fwd->static_flags |= TCP_S_BASE_SEQ_SET0x01;
1615 }
1616
1617 /* Only store reverse sequence if this isn't the SYN
1618 * There's no guarantee that the ACK field of a SYN
1619 * contains zeros; get the ISN from the first segment
1620 * with the ACK bit set instead (usually the SYN/ACK).
1621 *
1622 * If the SYN and SYN/ACK were received out-of-order,
1623 * the ISN is ack-1. If we missed the SYN/ACK, but got
1624 * the last ACK of the 3WHS, the ISN is ack-1. For all
1625 * other packets the ISN is unknown, so ack-1 is
1626 * as good a guess as ack.
1627 */
1628 if( !(tcpd->rev->static_flags & TCP_S_BASE_SEQ_SET0x01) && (flags & TH_ACK0x0010) ) {
1629 tcpd->rev->base_seq = ack-1;
1630 tcpd->rev->static_flags |= TCP_S_BASE_SEQ_SET0x01;
1631 }
1632
1633 if( flags & TH_ACK0x0010 ) {
1634 tcpd->rev->valid_bif = 1;
1635 }
1636
1637 /* ZERO WINDOW PROBE
1638 * it is a zero window probe if
1639 * the sequence number is the next expected one
1640 * the window in the other direction is 0
1641 * the segment is exactly 1 byte
1642 */
1643 if( seglen==1
1644 && seq==tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq
1645 && tcpd->rev->window==0 ) {
1646 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1647 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1648 }
1649 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_ZERO_WINDOW_PROBE0x0040;
1650 goto finished_fwd;
1651 }
1652
1653
1654 /* ZERO WINDOW
1655 * a zero window packet has window == 0 but none of the SYN/FIN/RST set
1656 */
1657 if( window==0
1658 && (flags&(TH_RST0x0004|TH_FIN0x0001|TH_SYN0x0002))==0 ) {
1659 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1660 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1661 }
1662 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_ZERO_WINDOW0x0020;
1663 }
1664
1665
1666 /* LOST PACKET
1667 * If this segment is beyond the last seen nextseq we must
1668 * have missed some previous segment
1669 *
1670 * We only check for this if we have actually seen segments prior to this
1671 * one.
1672 * RST packets are not checked for this.
1673 */
1674 if( tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq
1675 && GT_SEQ(seq, tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq)((gint32)((tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq)
- (seq)) < 0)
1676 && (flags&(TH_RST0x0004))==0 ) {
1677 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1678 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1679 }
1680 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_LOST_PACKET0x0002;
1681
1682 /* Disable BiF until an ACK is seen in the other direction */
1683 tcpd->fwd->valid_bif = 0;
1684 }
1685
1686
1687 /* KEEP ALIVE
1688 * a keepalive contains 0 or 1 bytes of data and starts one byte prior
1689 * to what should be the next sequence number.
1690 * SYN/FIN/RST segments are never keepalives
1691 */
1692 if( (seglen==0||seglen==1)
1693 && seq==(tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq-1)
1694 && (flags&(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_FIN0x0001|TH_RST0x0004))==0 ) {
1695 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1696 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1697 }
1698 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_KEEP_ALIVE0x0008;
1699 }
1700
1701 /* WINDOW UPDATE
1702 * A window update is a 0 byte segment with the same SEQ/ACK numbers as
1703 * the previous seen segment and with a new window value
1704 */
1705 if( seglen==0
1706 && window
1707 && window!=tcpd->fwd->window
1708 && seq==tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq
1709 && ack==tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastack
1710 && (flags&(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_FIN0x0001|TH_RST0x0004))==0 ) {
1711 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1712 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1713 }
1714 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_WINDOW_UPDATE0x0800;
1715 }
1716
1717
1718 /* WINDOW FULL
1719 * If we know the window scaling
1720 * and if this segment contains data and goes all the way to the
1721 * edge of the advertised window
1722 * then we mark it as WINDOW FULL
1723 * SYN/RST/FIN packets are never WINDOW FULL
1724 */
1725 if( seglen>0
1726 && tcpd->rev->win_scale!=-1
1727 && (seq+seglen)==(tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastack+(tcpd->rev->window<<(tcpd->rev->win_scale==-2?0:tcpd->rev->win_scale)))
1728 && (flags&(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_FIN0x0001|TH_RST0x0004))==0 ) {
1729 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1730 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1731 }
1732 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_WINDOW_FULL0x1000;
1733 }
1734
1735
1736 /* KEEP ALIVE ACK
1737 * It is a keepalive ack if it repeats the previous ACK and if
1738 * the last segment in the reverse direction was a keepalive
1739 */
1740 if( seglen==0
1741 && window
1742 && window==tcpd->fwd->window
1743 && seq==tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq
1744 && ack==tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastack
1745 && (tcpd->rev->lastsegmentflags&TCP_A_KEEP_ALIVE0x0008)
1746 && (flags&(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_FIN0x0001|TH_RST0x0004))==0 ) {
1747 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1748 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1749 }
1750 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_KEEP_ALIVE_ACK0x0100;
1751 goto finished_fwd;
1752 }
1753
1754
1755 /* ZERO WINDOW PROBE ACK
1756 * It is a zerowindowprobe ack if it repeats the previous ACK and if
1757 * the last segment in the reverse direction was a zerowindowprobe
1758 * It also repeats the previous zero window indication
1759 */
1760 if( seglen==0
1761 && window==0
1762 && window==tcpd->fwd->window
1763 && seq==tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq
1764 && ack==tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastack
1765 && (tcpd->rev->lastsegmentflags&TCP_A_ZERO_WINDOW_PROBE0x0040)
1766 && (flags&(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_FIN0x0001|TH_RST0x0004))==0 ) {
1767 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1768 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1769 }
1770 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_ZERO_WINDOW_PROBE_ACK0x0080;
1771 goto finished_fwd;
1772 }
1773
1774
1775 /* DUPLICATE ACK
1776 * It is a duplicate ack if window/seq/ack is the same as the previous
1777 * segment and if the segment length is 0
1778 */
1779 if( seglen==0
1780 && window
1781 && window==tcpd->fwd->window
1782 && seq==tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq
1783 && ack==tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastack
1784 && (flags&(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_FIN0x0001|TH_RST0x0004))==0 ) {
1785 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->dupacknum++;
1786 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1787 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1788 }
1789 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_DUPLICATE_ACK0x0010;
1790 tcpd->ta->dupack_num=tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->dupacknum;
1791 tcpd->ta->dupack_frame=tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastnondupack;
1792 }
1793
1794
1795
1796finished_fwd:
1797 /* If the ack number changed we must reset the dupack counters */
1798 if( ack != tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastack ) {
1799 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastnondupack=pinfo->num;
1800 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->dupacknum=0;
1801 }
1802
1803
1804 /* ACKED LOST PACKET
1805 * If this segment acks beyond the 'max seq to be acked' in the other direction
1806 * then that means we have missed packets going in the
1807 * other direction
1808 *
1809 * We only check this if we have actually seen some seq numbers
1810 * in the other direction.
1811 */
1812 if( tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->maxseqtobeacked
1813 && GT_SEQ(ack, tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->maxseqtobeacked )((gint32)((tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->maxseqtobeacked
) - (ack)) < 0)
1814 && (flags&(TH_ACK0x0010))!=0 ) {
1815 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1816 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1817 }
1818 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_ACK_LOST_PACKET0x0004;
1819 /* update 'max seq to be acked' in the other direction so we don't get
1820 * this indication again.
1821 */
1822 tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->maxseqtobeacked=tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq;
1823 }
1824
1825
1826 /* RETRANSMISSION/FAST RETRANSMISSION/OUT-OF-ORDER
1827 * If the segment contains data (or is a SYN or a FIN) and
1828 * if it does not advance the sequence number, it must be one
1829 * of these three.
1830 * Only test for this if we know what the seq number should be
1831 * (tcpd->fwd->nextseq)
1832 *
1833 * Note that a simple KeepAlive is not a retransmission
1834 */
1835 if( (seglen>0 || flags&(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_FIN0x0001))
1836 && tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq
1837 && (LT_SEQ(seq, tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq)((gint32)((seq) - (tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->
nextseq)) < 0)) ) {
1838 guint64 t;
1839 guint64 ooo_thres;
1840 if (tcpd->ts_first_rtt.nsecs == 0 && tcpd->ts_first_rtt.secs == 0)
1841 ooo_thres = 3000000;
1842 else
1843 ooo_thres = tcpd->ts_first_rtt.nsecs + tcpd->ts_first_rtt.secs*1000000000;
1844
1845 if(tcpd->ta && (tcpd->ta->flags&TCP_A_KEEP_ALIVE0x0008) ) {
1846 goto finished_checking_retransmission_type;
1847 }
1848
1849 /* If there were >=2 duplicate ACKs in the reverse direction
1850 * (there might be duplicate acks missing from the trace)
1851 * and if this sequence number matches those ACKs
1852 * and if the packet occurs within 20ms of the last
1853 * duplicate ack
1854 * then this is a fast retransmission
1855 */
1856 t=(pinfo->abs_ts.secs-tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastacktime.secs)*1000000000;
1857 t=t+(pinfo->abs_ts.nsecs)-tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastacktime.nsecs;
1858 if( tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->dupacknum>=2
1859 && tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastack==seq
1860 && t<20000000 ) {
1861 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1862 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1863 }
1864 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_FAST_RETRANSMISSION0x0400;
1865 goto finished_checking_retransmission_type;
1866 }
1867
1868 /* If the segment came relatively close since the segment with the highest
1869 * seen sequence number and it doesn't look like a retransmission
1870 * then it is an OUT-OF-ORDER segment.
1871 */
1872 t=(pinfo->abs_ts.secs-tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseqtime.secs)*1000000000;
1873 t=t+(pinfo->abs_ts.nsecs)-tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseqtime.nsecs;
1874 if( t < ooo_thres
1875 && tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq != seq + seglen ) {
1876 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1877 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1878 }
1879 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_OUT_OF_ORDER0x0200;
1880 goto finished_checking_retransmission_type;
1881 }
1882
1883 /* Check for spurious retransmission. If the current seq + segment length
1884 * is less than or equal to the receiver's lastack, the packet contains
1885 * duplicate data and may be considered spurious.
1886 */
1887 if ( seq + seglen <= tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastack ) {
1888 if(!tcpd->ta){
1889 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1890 }
1891 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_SPURIOUS_RETRANSMISSION0x4000;
1892 goto finished_checking_retransmission_type;
1893 }
1894
1895 /* Then it has to be a generic retransmission */
1896 if(!tcpd->ta) {
1897 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1898 }
1899 tcpd->ta->flags|=TCP_A_RETRANSMISSION0x0001;
1900 nstime_delta(&tcpd->ta->rto_ts, &pinfo->abs_ts, &tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseqtime);
1901 tcpd->ta->rto_frame=tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseqframe;
1902 }
1903
1904finished_checking_retransmission_type:
1905
1906 nextseq = seq+seglen;
1907 if ((seglen || flags&(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_FIN0x0001)) && tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->segment_count < TCP_MAX_UNACKED_SEGMENTS1000) {
1908 /* Add this new sequence number to the fwd list. But only if there
1909 * aren't "too many" unacked segments (e.g., we're not seeing the ACKs).
1910 */
1911 ual = wmem_new(wmem_file_scope(), tcp_unacked_t)((tcp_unacked_t*)wmem_alloc((wmem_file_scope()), sizeof(tcp_unacked_t
)));
1912 ual->next=tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->segments;
1913 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->segments=ual;
1914 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->segment_count++;
1915 ual->frame=pinfo->num;
1916 ual->seq=seq;
1917 ual->ts=pinfo->abs_ts;
1918
1919 /* next sequence number is seglen bytes away, plus SYN/FIN which counts as one byte */
1920 if( (flags&(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_FIN0x0001)) ) {
1921 nextseq+=1;
1922 }
1923 ual->nextseq=nextseq;
1924 }
1925
1926 /* Store the highest number seen so far for nextseq so we can detect
1927 * when we receive segments that arrive with a "hole"
1928 * If we don't have anything since before, just store what we got.
1929 * ZeroWindowProbes are special and don't really advance the nextseq
1930 */
1931 if(GT_SEQ(nextseq, tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq)((gint32)((tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq)
- (nextseq)) < 0) || !tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq) {
1932 if( !tcpd->ta || !(tcpd->ta->flags&TCP_A_ZERO_WINDOW_PROBE0x0040) ) {
1933 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq=nextseq;
1934 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseqframe=pinfo->num;
1935 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseqtime.secs=pinfo->abs_ts.secs;
1936 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseqtime.nsecs=pinfo->abs_ts.nsecs;
1937 }
1938 }
1939
1940 /* Store the highest continuous seq number seen so far for 'max seq to be acked',
1941 so we can detect TCP_A_ACK_LOST_PACKET condition
1942 */
1943 if(EQ_SEQ(seq, tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->maxseqtobeacked)(seq) == (tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->maxseqtobeacked
) || !tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->maxseqtobeacked) {
1944 if( !tcpd->ta || !(tcpd->ta->flags&TCP_A_ZERO_WINDOW_PROBE0x0040) ) {
1945 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->maxseqtobeacked=tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->nextseq;
1946 }
1947 }
1948
1949
1950 /* remember what the ack/window is so we can track window updates and retransmissions */
1951 tcpd->fwd->window=window;
1952 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastack=ack;
1953 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastacktime.secs=pinfo->abs_ts.secs;
1954 tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->lastacktime.nsecs=pinfo->abs_ts.nsecs;
1955
1956
1957 /* if there were any flags set for this segment we need to remember them
1958 * we only remember the flags for the very last segment though.
1959 */
1960 if(tcpd->ta) {
1961 tcpd->fwd->lastsegmentflags=tcpd->ta->flags;
1962 } else {
1963 tcpd->fwd->lastsegmentflags=0;
1964 }
1965
1966
1967 /* remove all segments this ACKs and we don't need to keep around any more
1968 */
1969 ackcount=0;
1970 prevual = NULL((void*)0);
1971 ual = tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->segments;
1972 while(ual) {
1973 tcp_unacked_t *tmpual;
1974
1975 /* If this ack matches the segment, process accordingly */
1976 if(ack==ual->nextseq) {
1977 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
1978 tcpd->ta->frame_acked=ual->frame;
1979 nstime_delta(&tcpd->ta->ts, &pinfo->abs_ts, &ual->ts);
1980 }
1981 /* If this acknowledges part of the segment, adjust the segment info for the acked part */
1982 else if (GT_SEQ(ack, ual->seq)((gint32)((ual->seq) - (ack)) < 0) && LE_SEQ(ack, ual->nextseq)((gint32)((ack) - (ual->nextseq)) <= 0)) {
1983 ual->seq = ack;
1984 continue;
1985 }
1986 /* If this acknowledges a segment prior to this one, leave this segment alone and move on */
1987 else if (GT_SEQ(ual->nextseq,ack)((gint32)((ack) - (ual->nextseq)) < 0)) {
1988 prevual = ual;
1989 ual = ual->next;
1990 continue;
1991 }
1992
1993 /* This segment is old, or an exact match. Delete the segment from the list */
1994 ackcount++;
1995 tmpual=ual->next;
1996
1997 if (tcpd->rev->scps_capable) {
1998 /* Track largest segment successfully sent for SNACK analysis*/
1999 if ((ual->nextseq - ual->seq) > tcpd->fwd->maxsizeacked) {
2000 tcpd->fwd->maxsizeacked = (ual->nextseq - ual->seq);
2001 }
2002 }
2003
2004 if (!prevual) {
2005 tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->segments = tmpual;
2006 }
2007 else{
2008 prevual->next = tmpual;
2009 }
2010 wmem_free(wmem_file_scope(), ual);
2011 ual = tmpual;
2012 tcpd->rev->tcp_analyze_seq_info->segment_count--;
2013 }
2014
2015 /* how many bytes of data are there in flight after this frame
2016 * was sent
2017 */
2018 ual=tcpd->fwd->tcp_analyze_seq_info->segments;
2019 if (tcp_track_bytes_in_flight && seglen!=0 && ual && tcpd->fwd->valid_bif) {
2020 guint32 first_seq, last_seq, in_flight;
2021
2022 first_seq = ual->seq - tcpd->fwd->base_seq;
2023 last_seq = ual->nextseq - tcpd->fwd->base_seq;
2024 while (ual) {
2025 if ((ual->nextseq-tcpd->fwd->base_seq)>last_seq) {
2026 last_seq = ual->nextseq-tcpd->fwd->base_seq;
2027 }
2028 if ((ual->seq-tcpd->fwd->base_seq)<first_seq) {
2029 first_seq = ual->seq-tcpd->fwd->base_seq;
2030 }
2031 ual = ual->next;
2032 }
2033 in_flight = last_seq-first_seq;
2034
2035 if (in_flight>0 && in_flight<2000000000) {
2036 if(!tcpd->ta) {
2037 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
2038 }
2039 tcpd->ta->bytes_in_flight = in_flight;
2040 }
2041
2042 if((flags & TH_PUSH0x0008) && !tcpd->fwd->push_set_last) {
2043 tcpd->fwd->push_bytes_sent += seglen;
2044 tcpd->fwd->push_set_last = TRUE(!(0));
2045 } else if ((flags & TH_PUSH0x0008) && tcpd->fwd->push_set_last) {
2046 tcpd->fwd->push_bytes_sent = seglen;
2047 tcpd->fwd->push_set_last = TRUE(!(0));
2048 } else if (tcpd->fwd->push_set_last) {
2049 tcpd->fwd->push_bytes_sent = seglen;
2050 tcpd->fwd->push_set_last = FALSE(0);
2051 } else {
2052 tcpd->fwd->push_bytes_sent += seglen;
2053 }
2054 if(!tcpd->ta) {
2055 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->fd->num, seq, ack, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd);
2056 }
2057 tcpd->ta->push_bytes_sent = tcpd->fwd->push_bytes_sent;
2058 }
2059
2060}

)->finfo))->flags = (((flags_item)->finfo))->flags
| (0x00000002); } while(0); } while(0);

| (0x00000002); } while(0); } while(0);

2266/* Generate the initial data sequence number and MPTCP connection token from the key. */
2267static void
2268mptcp_cryptodata_sha1(const guint64 key, guint32 *token, guint64 *idsn)
2269{
2270 guint8 digest_buf[SHA1_DIGEST_LEN20];
2271 guint64 pseudokey = GUINT64_TO_BE(key)(((__extension__ ({ guint64 __v, __x = ((guint64) (key)); if (
__builtin_constant_p (__x)) __v = ((guint64) ( (((guint64) (__x
) & (guint64) (0x00000000000000ffUL)) << 56) | (((guint64
) (__x) & (guint64) (0x000000000000ff00UL)) << 40) |
(((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x0000000000ff0000UL)) <<
24) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x00000000ff000000UL
)) << 8) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x000000ff00000000UL
)) >> 8) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x0000ff0000000000UL
)) >> 24) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x00ff000000000000UL
)) >> 40) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0xff00000000000000UL
)) >> 56))); else __asm__ ("bswapq %0" : "=r" (__v) : "0"
(__x)); __v; }))));
2272 sha1_context sha1_ctx;
2273 guint32 _token;
2274 guint64 _isdn;
2275
2276 sha1_starts(&sha1_ctx);
2277 sha1_update(&sha1_ctx, (const guint8 *)&pseudokey, 8);
2278 sha1_finish(&sha1_ctx, digest_buf);
2279
2280 /* memcpy to prevent -Wstrict-aliasing errors with GCC 4 */
2281 memcpy(&_token, &digest_buf[0], sizeof(_token));
2282 *token = GUINT32_FROM_BE(_token)((((__extension__ ({ guint32 __v, __x = ((guint32) (_token));
if (__builtin_constant_p (__x)) __v = ((guint32) ( (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0x000000ffU) << 24) | (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0x0000ff00U) << 8) | (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0x00ff0000U) >> 8) | (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0xff000000U) >> 24))); else __asm__
("bswapl %0" : "=r" (__v) : "0" (__x)); __v; })))));
2283 memcpy(&_isdn, &digest_buf[SHA1_DIGEST_LEN20-8], sizeof(_isdn));
2284 *idsn = GUINT64_FROM_BE(_isdn)((((__extension__ ({ guint64 __v, __x = ((guint64) (_isdn)); if
(__builtin_constant_p (__x)) __v = ((guint64) ( (((guint64) (
__x) & (guint64) (0x00000000000000ffUL)) << 56) | (
((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x000000000000ff00UL)) <<
40) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x0000000000ff0000UL
)) << 24) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x00000000ff000000UL
)) << 8) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x000000ff00000000UL
)) >> 8) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x0000ff0000000000UL
)) >> 24) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0x00ff000000000000UL
)) >> 40) | (((guint64) (__x) & (guint64) (0xff00000000000000UL
)) >> 56))); else __asm__ ("bswapq %0" : "=r" (__v) : "0"
(__x)); __v; })))));
2285}

2289static void
2290mptcp_analysis_add_subflows(packet_info *pinfo _U___attribute__((unused)), tvbuff_t *tvb,
2291 proto_tree *parent_tree, struct mptcp_analysis* mptcpd)

2298 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
2299
2300 tree=proto_item_add_subtree(item, ett_mptcp_analysis_subflows);
2301
2302 /* for the analysis, we set each subflow tcp stream id */
2303 for(it = wmem_list_head(mptcpd->subflows); it != NULL((void*)0); it = wmem_list_frame_next(it)) {

2306 subflow_item=proto_tree_add_uint(tree, hf_mptcp_analysis_subflows_stream_id, tvb, 0, 0, sf->stream);
2307 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(subflow_item)do { if (subflow_item) do { if (((subflow_item)->finfo)) (
((subflow_item)->finfo))->flags = (((subflow_item)->
finfo))->flags | (0x00000001); } while(0); } while(0);
2308
2309 proto_item_append_text(item, " %d", sf->stream);
2310 }
2311
2312 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
2313}

2315/* Compute raw dsn if relative tcp seq covered by DSS mapping */
2316static gboolean
2317mptcp_map_relssn_to_rawdsn(mptcp_dss_mapping_t *mapping, guint32 relssn, guint64 *dsn)
2318{
2319 if( (relssn < mapping->ssn_low) || (relssn > mapping->ssn_high)) {
2320 return FALSE(0);
2321 }
2322
2323 *dsn = mapping->rawdsn + (relssn - mapping->ssn_low);
2324 return TRUE(!(0));
2325}

2327
2328/* Add duplicated data */
2329static mptcp_dsn2packet_mapping_t *
2330mptcp_add_duplicated_dsn(packet_info *pinfo _U___attribute__((unused)), proto_tree *tree, tvbuff_t *tvb, struct mptcp_subflow *subflow,
2331guint64 rawdsn64low, guint64 rawdsn64high
2332)
2333{
2334 wmem_list_t *results = NULL((void*)0);
2335 wmem_list_frame_t *packet_it = NULL((void*)0);
2336 mptcp_dsn2packet_mapping_t *packet = NULL((void*)0);
2337 proto_item *item = NULL((void*)0);
2338
2339 results = wmem_itree_find_intervals(subflow->mappings,
2340 wmem_packet_scope(),
2341 rawdsn64low,
2342 rawdsn64high
2343 );
2344

, 2351, "packet")))));

2354 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);

2391/* Lookup mappings that describe the packet and then converts the tcp seq number
2392 * into the MPTCP Data Sequence Number (DSN)
2393 */
2394static void
2395mptcp_analysis_dsn_lookup(packet_info *pinfo , tvbuff_t *tvb,
2396 proto_tree *parent_tree, struct tcp_analysis* tcpd, struct tcpheader * tcph, mptcp_per_packet_data_t *mptcppd)
2397{
2398 struct mptcp_analysis* mptcpd = tcpd->mptcp_analysis;
2399 proto_item *item = NULL((void*)0);
2400 mptcp_dss_mapping_t *mapping = NULL((void*)0);
2401 guint32 relseq;
2402 guint64 rawdsn = 0;
2403 enum mptcp_dsn_conversion convert;
2404
2405 if(!mptcp_analyze_mappings)
2406 {
2407 /* abort analysis */
2408 return;
2409 }
2410
2411 /* for this to work, we need to know the original seq number from the SYN, not from a subsequent packet
2412 * hence, we abort if we didn't capture the SYN
2413 */
2414 if(!(tcpd->fwd->static_flags & ~TCP_S_BASE_SEQ_SET0x01 & (TCP_S_SAW_SYN0x03 | TCP_S_SAW_SYNACK0x05))) {
2415 return;
2416 }
2417
2418 /* if seq not relative yet, we compute it */
2419 relseq = (tcp_relative_seq) ? tcph->th_seq : tcph->th_seq - tcpd->fwd->base_seq;
2420
2421 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(mptcpd)((void) ((mptcpd) ? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf
(wmem_packet_scope(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\"", "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 2421, "mptcpd")))));
2422 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(mptcppd)((void) ((mptcppd) ? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf
(wmem_packet_scope(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\"", "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 2422, "mptcppd")))));
2423
2424 /* in case of a SYN, there is no mapping covering the DSN */
2425 if(tcph->th_flags & TH_SYN0x0002) {
2426
2427 rawdsn = tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->base_dsn;
2428 convert = DSN_CONV_NONE;
2429 }
2430 else {
2431 /* display packets that conveyed the mappings covering the data range */
2432 mapping = mptcp_add_matching_dss_on_subflow(pinfo, parent_tree, tvb,
2433 tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow, relseq,
2434 (tcph->th_have_seglen) ? tcph->th_seglen : 0
2435 );
2436 if(mapping == NULL((void*)0)) {
2437 expert_add_info(pinfo, parent_tree, &ei_mptcp_mapping_missing);
2438 return;
2439 }
2440 else {
2441 mptcppd->mapping = mapping;
2442 }
2443
2444 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(mapping)((void) ((mapping) ? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf
(wmem_packet_scope(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\"", "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 2444, "mapping")))));
2445
2446 convert = (mapping->extended_dsn) ? DSN_CONV_NONE : DSN_CONV_32_TO_64;
2447 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(mptcp_map_relssn_to_rawdsn(mapping, relseq, &rawdsn))((void) ((mptcp_map_relssn_to_rawdsn(mapping, relseq, &rawdsn
)) ? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf
(wmem_packet_scope(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\"", "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 2447, "mptcp_map_relssn_to_rawdsn(mapping, relseq, &rawdsn)"
)))));
2448 }
2449
2450 /* Make sure we have the 64bit raw DSN */
2451 if(mptcp_convert_dsn(rawdsn, tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta,
2452 convert, FALSE(0), &tcph->th_mptcp->mh_rawdsn64)) {
2453
2454 /* always display the rawdsn64 (helpful for debug) */
2455 item = proto_tree_add_uint64(parent_tree, hf_mptcp_rawdsn64, tvb, 0, 0, tcph->th_mptcp->mh_rawdsn64);
2456
2457 /* converts to relative if required */
2458 if (mptcp_relative_seq
2459 && mptcp_convert_dsn(tcph->th_mptcp->mh_rawdsn64, tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta, DSN_CONV_NONE, TRUE(!(0)), &tcph->th_mptcp->mh_dsn)) {
2460 item = proto_tree_add_uint64(parent_tree, hf_mptcp_dsn, tvb, 0, 0, tcph->th_mptcp->mh_dsn);
2461 proto_item_append_text(item, " (Relative)");
2462 }
2463
2464 /* register */
2465 if (!PINFO_FD_VISITED(pinfo)((pinfo)->fd->flags.visited))
2466 {
2467 mptcp_dsn2packet_mapping_t *packet;
2468 packet = wmem_new0(wmem_file_scope(), mptcp_dsn2packet_mapping_t)((mptcp_dsn2packet_mapping_t*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_file_scope())
, sizeof(mptcp_dsn2packet_mapping_t)));
2469 packet->frame = pinfo->fd->num;
2470 packet->subflow = tcpd;
2471
2472 /* tcph->th_mptcp->mh_rawdsn64 */
2473 if (tcph->th_have_seglen) {
2474 wmem_itree_insert(tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->dsn_map,
2475 tcph->th_mptcp->mh_rawdsn64,
2476 tcph->th_mptcp->mh_rawdsn64 + (tcph->th_seglen - 1 ),
2477 packet
2478 );
2479 }
2480 }
2481 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
2482
2483 /* We can do this only if rawdsn64 is valid !
2484 if enabled, look for overlapping mappings on other subflows */
2485 if(mptcp_intersubflows_retransmission) {
2486
2487 wmem_list_frame_t *subflow_it = NULL((void*)0);
2488
2489 /* results should be some kind of in case 2 DSS are needed to cover this packet */
2490 for(subflow_it = wmem_list_head(mptcpd->subflows); subflow_it != NULL((void*)0); subflow_it = wmem_list_frame_next(subflow_it)) {
2491 struct tcp_analysis *sf_tcpd = (struct tcp_analysis *)wmem_list_frame_data(subflow_it);
2492 struct mptcp_subflow *sf = mptcp_select_subflow_from_meta(sf_tcpd, tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta);
2493
2494 /* for current subflow */
2495 if (sf == tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow) {
2496 /* skip, was done just before */
2497 }
2498 /* in case there were retransmissions on other subflows */
2499 else {
2500 mptcp_add_duplicated_dsn(pinfo, parent_tree, tvb, sf,
2501 tcph->th_mptcp->mh_rawdsn64,
2502 tcph->th_mptcp->mh_rawdsn64 + tcph->th_seglen-1);
2503 }
2504 }
2505 }
2506 }
2507 else {
2508 /* ignore and continue */
2509 }
2510
2511}

))->flags = (((tree)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);

2540

2586static void
2587tcp_print_sequence_number_analysis(packet_info *pinfo, tvbuff_t *tvb, proto_tree *parent_tree,

2599 tcp_analyze_get_acked_struct(pinfo->num, seq, ack, FALSE(0), tcpd);
2600 }

2603 return;
2604 }

2607 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
2608 tree=proto_item_add_subtree(item, ett_tcp_analysis);
2609

2611 data we actually have */
2612 if(ta->frame_acked) {

2614 tvb, 0, 0, ta->frame_acked);
2615 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
2616

2618 if( ta->ts.secs || ta->ts.nsecs ) {

2620 tvb, 0, 0, &ta->ts);
2621 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
2622 }

2626 tvb, 0, 0, &(tcpd->ts_first_rtt));
2627 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);

2628 }
