2666static void
2667print_tcp_fragment_tree(fragment_head *ipfd_head, proto_tree *tree, proto_tree *tcp_tree, packet_info *pinfo, tvbuff_t *next_tvb)
2668{
2669 proto_item *tcp_tree_item, *frag_tree_item;
2670
2671 /*
2672 * The subdissector thought it was completely
2673 * desegmented (although the stuff at the
2674 * end may, in turn, require desegmentation),
2675 * so we show a tree with all segments.
2676 */
2677 show_fragment_tree(ipfd_head, &tcp_segment_items,
2678 tree, pinfo, next_tvb, &frag_tree_item);
2679 /*
2680 * The toplevel fragment subtree is now
2681 * behind all desegmented data; move it
2682 * right behind the TCP tree.
2683 */
2684 tcp_tree_item = proto_tree_get_parent(tcp_tree);
2685 if(frag_tree_item && tcp_tree_item) {
2686 proto_tree_move_item(tree, tcp_tree_item, frag_tree_item);
2687 }
2688}
2689
2690/* **************************************************************************
2691 * End of tcp sequence number analysis
2692 * **************************************************************************/
2693
2694
2695/* Minimum TCP header length. */
2696#define TCPH_MIN_LEN20 20
2697
2698/* Desegmentation of TCP streams */
2699static reassembly_table tcp_reassembly_table;
2700
2701/* functions to trace tcp segments */
2702/* Enable desegmenting of TCP streams */
2703static gboolean tcp_desegment = TRUE(!(0));
2704
2705static void
2706desegment_tcp(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, int offset,
2707 guint32 seq, guint32 nxtseq,
2708 guint32 sport, guint32 dport,
2709 proto_tree *tree, proto_tree *tcp_tree,
2710 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd, struct tcpinfo *tcpinfo)
2711{
2712 fragment_head *ipfd_head;
2713 int last_fragment_len;
2714 gboolean must_desegment;
2715 gboolean called_dissector;
2716 int another_pdu_follows;
2717 int deseg_offset;
2718 guint32 deseg_seq;
2719 gint nbytes;
2720 proto_item *item;
2721 struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *msp;
2722 gboolean cleared_writable = col_get_writable(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL);
2723
2724again:
2725 ipfd_head = NULL((void*)0);
2726 last_fragment_len = 0;
2727 must_desegment = FALSE(0);
2728 called_dissector = FALSE(0);
2729 another_pdu_follows = 0;
2730 msp = NULL((void*)0);
2731
2732 /*
2733 * Initialize these to assume no desegmentation.
2734 * If that's not the case, these will be set appropriately
2735 * by the subdissector.
2736 */
2737 pinfo->desegment_offset = 0;
2738 pinfo->desegment_len = 0;
2739
2740 /*
2741 * Initialize this to assume that this segment will just be
2742 * added to the middle of a desegmented chunk of data, so
2743 * that we should show it all as data.
2744 * If that's not the case, it will be set appropriately.
2745 */
2746 deseg_offset = offset;
2747
2748 if (tcpd) {
2749 /* Have we seen this PDU before (and is it the start of a multi-
2750 * segment PDU)?
2751 */
2752 if ((msp = (struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *)wmem_tree_lookup32(tcpd->fwd->multisegment_pdus, seq))) {
2753 const char* str;
2754
2755 /* Yes. This could be because we've dissected this frame before
2756 * or because this is a retransmission of a previously-seen
2757 * segment. Either way, we don't need to hand it off to the
2758 * subdissector and we certainly don't want to re-add it to the
2759 * multisegment_pdus list: if we did, subsequent lookups would
2760 * find this retransmission instead of the original transmission
2761 * (breaking desegmentation if we'd already linked other segments
2762 * to the original transmission's entry).
2763 */
2764
2765 if (msp->first_frame == pinfo->num) {
2766 str = "";
2767 col_set_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "[TCP segment of a reassembled PDU]");
2768 } else {
2769 str = "Retransmitted ";
2770 /* TCP analysis already flags this (in COL_INFO) as a retransmission--if it's enabled */
2771 }
2772
2773 /* Fix for bug 3264: look up ipfd for this (first) segment,
2774 so can add tcp.reassembled_in generated field on this code path. */
2775 ipfd_head = fragment_get(&tcp_reassembly_table, pinfo, pinfo->num, NULL((void*)0));
2776 if (ipfd_head) {
2777 if (ipfd_head->reassembled_in != 0) {
2778 item = proto_tree_add_uint(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_reassembled_in, tvb, 0,
2779 0, ipfd_head->reassembled_in);
2780 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
2781 }
2782 }
2783
2784 nbytes = tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset);
2785
2786 proto_tree_add_bytes_format(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_segment_data, tvb, offset,
2787 nbytes, NULL((void*)0), "%sTCP segment data (%u byte%s)", str, nbytes,
2788 plurality(nbytes, "", "s")((nbytes) == 1 ? ("") : ("s")));
2789 return;
2790 }
2791
2792 /* The above code only finds retransmission if the PDU boundaries and the seq coincide I think
2793 * If we have sequence analysis active use the TCP_A_RETRANSMISSION flag.
2794 * XXXX Could the above code be improved?
2795 */
2796 if((tcpd->ta) && ((tcpd->ta->flags&TCP_A_RETRANSMISSION0x0001) == TCP_A_RETRANSMISSION0x0001)){
2797 const char* str = "Retransmitted ";
2798 nbytes = tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset);
2799 proto_tree_add_bytes_format(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_segment_data, tvb, offset,
2800 nbytes, NULL((void*)0), "%sTCP segment data (%u byte%s)", str, nbytes,
2801 plurality(nbytes, "", "s")((nbytes) == 1 ? ("") : ("s")));
2802 return;
2803 }
2804 /* Else, find the most previous PDU starting before this sequence number */
2805 msp = (struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *)wmem_tree_lookup32_le(tcpd->fwd->multisegment_pdus, seq-1);
2806 }
2807
2808 if (msp && msp->seq <= seq && msp->nxtpdu > seq) {
2809 int len;
2810
2811 if (!PINFO_FD_VISITED(pinfo)((pinfo)->fd->flags.visited)) {
2812 msp->last_frame=pinfo->num;
2813 msp->last_frame_time=pinfo->abs_ts;
2814 }
2815
2816 /* OK, this PDU was found, which means the segment continues
2817 * a higher-level PDU and that we must desegment it.
2818 */
2819 if (msp->flags&MSP_FLAGS_REASSEMBLE_ENTIRE_SEGMENT0x00000001) {
2820 /* The dissector asked for the entire segment */
2821 len = tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, offset);
2822 } else {
2823 len = MIN(nxtseq, msp->nxtpdu)(((nxtseq) < (msp->nxtpdu)) ? (nxtseq) : (msp->nxtpdu
)) - seq;
2824 }
2825 last_fragment_len = len;
2826
2827 ipfd_head = fragment_add(&tcp_reassembly_table, tvb, offset,
2828 pinfo, msp->first_frame, NULL((void*)0),
2829 seq - msp->seq, len,
2830 (LT_SEQ (nxtseq,msp->nxtpdu)((gint32)((nxtseq) - (msp->nxtpdu)) < 0)) );
2831
2832 if (!PINFO_FD_VISITED(pinfo)((pinfo)->fd->flags.visited)
2833 && msp->flags & MSP_FLAGS_REASSEMBLE_ENTIRE_SEGMENT0x00000001) {
2834 msp->flags &= (~MSP_FLAGS_REASSEMBLE_ENTIRE_SEGMENT0x00000001);
2835
2836 /* If we consumed the entire segment there is no
2837 * other pdu starting anywhere inside this segment.
2838 * So update nxtpdu to point at least to the start
2839 * of the next segment.
2840 * (If the subdissector asks for even more data we
2841 * will advance nxtpdu even further later down in
2842 * the code.)
2843 */
2844 msp->nxtpdu = nxtseq;
2845 }
2846
2847 if( (msp->nxtpdu < nxtseq)
2848 && (msp->nxtpdu >= seq)
2849 && (len > 0)) {
2850 another_pdu_follows=msp->nxtpdu - seq;
2851 }
2852 } else {
2853 /* This segment was not found in our table, so it doesn't
2854 * contain a continuation of a higher-level PDU.
2855 * Call the normal subdissector.
2856 */
2857
2858 /*
2859 * Supply the sequence number of this segment. We set this here
2860 * because this segment could be after another in the same packet,
2861 * in which case seq was incremented at the end of the loop.
2862 */
2863 tcpinfo->seq = seq;
2864
2865 process_tcp_payload(tvb, offset, pinfo, tree, tcp_tree,
2866 sport, dport, 0, 0, FALSE(0), tcpd, tcpinfo);
2867 called_dissector = TRUE(!(0));
2868
2869 /* Did the subdissector ask us to desegment some more data
2870 * before it could handle the packet?
2871 * If so we have to create some structures in our table but
2872 * this is something we only do the first time we see this
2873 * packet.
2874 */
2875 if(pinfo->desegment_len) {
2876 if (!PINFO_FD_VISITED(pinfo)((pinfo)->fd->flags.visited))
2877 must_desegment = TRUE(!(0));
2878
2879 /*
2880 * Set "deseg_offset" to the offset in "tvb"
2881 * of the first byte of data that the
2882 * subdissector didn't process.
2883 */
2884 deseg_offset = offset + pinfo->desegment_offset;
2885 }
2886
2887 /* Either no desegmentation is necessary, or this is
2888 * segment contains the beginning but not the end of
2889 * a higher-level PDU and thus isn't completely
2890 * desegmented.
2891 */
2892 ipfd_head = NULL((void*)0);
2893 }
2894
2895
2896 /* is it completely desegmented? */
2897 if (ipfd_head) {
2898 /*
2899 * Yes, we think it is.
2900 * We only call subdissector for the last segment.
2901 * Note that the last segment may include more than what
2902 * we needed.
2903 */
2904 if(ipfd_head->reassembled_in == pinfo->num) {
2905 /*
2906 * OK, this is the last segment.
2907 * Let's call the subdissector with the desegmented
2908 * data.
2909 */
2910 tvbuff_t *next_tvb;
2911 int old_len;
2912
2913 /* create a new TVB structure for desegmented data */
2914 next_tvb = tvb_new_chain(tvb, ipfd_head->tvb_data);
2915
2916 /* add desegmented data to the data source list */
2917 add_new_data_source(pinfo, next_tvb, "Reassembled TCP");
2918
2919 /*
2920 * Supply the sequence number of the first of the
2921 * reassembled bytes.
2922 */
2923 tcpinfo->seq = msp->seq;
2924
2925 /* indicate that this is reassembled data */
2926 tcpinfo->is_reassembled = TRUE(!(0));
2927
2928 /* call subdissector */
2929 process_tcp_payload(next_tvb, 0, pinfo, tree, tcp_tree, sport,
2930 dport, 0, 0, FALSE(0), tcpd, tcpinfo);
2931 called_dissector = TRUE(!(0));
2932
2933 /*
2934 * OK, did the subdissector think it was completely
2935 * desegmented, or does it think we need even more
2936 * data?
2937 */
2938 old_len = (int)(tvb_reported_length(next_tvb) - last_fragment_len);
2939 if (pinfo->desegment_len &&
2940 pinfo->desegment_offset<=old_len) {
2941 /*
2942 * "desegment_len" isn't 0, so it needs more
2943 * data for something - and "desegment_offset"
2944 * is before "old_len", so it needs more data
2945 * to dissect the stuff we thought was
2946 * completely desegmented (as opposed to the
2947 * stuff at the beginning being completely
2948 * desegmented, but the stuff at the end
2949 * being a new higher-level PDU that also
2950 * needs desegmentation).
2951 */
2952 remove_last_data_source(pinfo);
2953 fragment_set_partial_reassembly(&tcp_reassembly_table,
2954 pinfo, msp->first_frame, NULL((void*)0));
2955
2956 /* Update msp->nxtpdu to point to the new next
2957 * pdu boundary.
2958 */
2959 if (pinfo->desegment_len == DESEGMENT_ONE_MORE_SEGMENT0x0fffffff) {
2960 /* We want reassembly of at least one
2961 * more segment so set the nxtpdu
2962 * boundary to one byte into the next
2963 * segment.
2964 * This means that the next segment
2965 * will complete reassembly even if it
2966 * is only one single byte in length.
2967 */
2968 msp->nxtpdu = seq + tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset) + 1;
2969 msp->flags |= MSP_FLAGS_REASSEMBLE_ENTIRE_SEGMENT0x00000001;
2970 } else if (pinfo->desegment_len == DESEGMENT_UNTIL_FIN0x0ffffffe) {
2971 tcpd->fwd->flags |= TCP_FLOW_REASSEMBLE_UNTIL_FIN0x0001;
2972 } else {
2973 msp->nxtpdu=seq + last_fragment_len + pinfo->desegment_len;
2974 }
2975
2976 /* Since we need at least some more data
2977 * there can be no pdu following in the
2978 * tail of this segment.
2979 */
2980 another_pdu_follows = 0;
2981 offset += last_fragment_len;
2982 seq += last_fragment_len;
2983 if (tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, offset) > 0)
2984 goto again;
2985 } else {
2986 /*
2987 * Show the stuff in this TCP segment as
2988 * just raw TCP segment data.
2989 */
2990 nbytes = another_pdu_follows > 0
2991 ? another_pdu_follows
2992 : tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset);
2993 proto_tree_add_bytes_format(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_segment_data, tvb, offset,
2994 nbytes, NULL((void*)0), "TCP segment data (%u byte%s)", nbytes,
2995 plurality(nbytes, "", "s")((nbytes) == 1 ? ("") : ("s")));
2996
2997 print_tcp_fragment_tree(ipfd_head, tree, tcp_tree, pinfo, next_tvb);
2998
2999 /* Did the subdissector ask us to desegment
3000 * some more data? This means that the data
3001 * at the beginning of this segment completed
3002 * a higher-level PDU, but the data at the
3003 * end of this segment started a higher-level
3004 * PDU but didn't complete it.
3005 *
3006 * If so, we have to create some structures
3007 * in our table, but this is something we
3008 * only do the first time we see this packet.
3009 */
3010 if(pinfo->desegment_len) {
3011 if (!PINFO_FD_VISITED(pinfo)((pinfo)->fd->flags.visited))
3012 must_desegment = TRUE(!(0));
3013
3014 /* The stuff we couldn't dissect
3015 * must have come from this segment,
3016 * so it's all in "tvb".
3017 *
3018 * "pinfo->desegment_offset" is
3019 * relative to the beginning of
3020 * "next_tvb"; we want an offset
3021 * relative to the beginning of "tvb".
3022 *
3023 * First, compute the offset relative
3024 * to the *end* of "next_tvb" - i.e.,
3025 * the number of bytes before the end
3026 * of "next_tvb" at which the
3027 * subdissector stopped. That's the
3028 * length of "next_tvb" minus the
3029 * offset, relative to the beginning
3030 * of "next_tvb, at which the
3031 * subdissector stopped.
3032 */
3033 deseg_offset = ipfd_head->datalen - pinfo->desegment_offset;
3034
3035 /* "tvb" and "next_tvb" end at the
3036 * same byte of data, so the offset
3037 * relative to the end of "next_tvb"
3038 * of the byte at which we stopped
3039 * is also the offset relative to
3040 * the end of "tvb" of the byte at
3041 * which we stopped.
3042 *
3043 * Convert that back into an offset
3044 * relative to the beginning of
3045 * "tvb", by taking the length of
3046 * "tvb" and subtracting the offset
3047 * relative to the end.
3048 */
3049 deseg_offset = tvb_reported_length(tvb) - deseg_offset;
3050 }
3051 }
3052 }
3053 }
3054
3055 if (must_desegment) {
3056 /* If the dissector requested "reassemble until FIN"
3057 * just set this flag for the flow and let reassembly
3058 * proceed at normal. We will check/pick up these
3059 * reassembled PDUs later down in dissect_tcp() when checking
3060 * for the FIN flag.
3061 */
3062 if (tcpd && pinfo->desegment_len == DESEGMENT_UNTIL_FIN0x0ffffffe) {
3063 tcpd->fwd->flags |= TCP_FLOW_REASSEMBLE_UNTIL_FIN0x0001;
3064 }
3065 /*
3066 * The sequence number at which the stuff to be desegmented
3067 * starts is the sequence number of the byte at an offset
3068 * of "deseg_offset" into "tvb".
3069 *
3070 * The sequence number of the byte at an offset of "offset"
3071 * is "seq", i.e. the starting sequence number of this
3072 * segment, so the sequence number of the byte at
3073 * "deseg_offset" is "seq + (deseg_offset - offset)".
3074 */
3075 deseg_seq = seq + (deseg_offset - offset);
3076
3077 if (tcpd && ((nxtseq - deseg_seq) <= 1024*1024)
3078 && (!PINFO_FD_VISITED(pinfo)((pinfo)->fd->flags.visited))) {
3079 if(pinfo->desegment_len == DESEGMENT_ONE_MORE_SEGMENT0x0fffffff) {
3080 /* The subdissector asked to reassemble using the
3081 * entire next segment.
3082 * Just ask reassembly for one more byte
3083 * but set this msp flag so we can pick it up
3084 * above.
3085 */
3086 msp = pdu_store_sequencenumber_of_next_pdu(pinfo, deseg_seq,
3087 nxtseq+1, tcpd->fwd->multisegment_pdus);
3088 msp->flags |= MSP_FLAGS_REASSEMBLE_ENTIRE_SEGMENT0x00000001;
3089 } else {
3090 msp = pdu_store_sequencenumber_of_next_pdu(pinfo,
3091 deseg_seq, nxtseq+pinfo->desegment_len, tcpd->fwd->multisegment_pdus);
3092 }
3093
3094 /* add this segment as the first one for this new pdu */
3095 fragment_add(&tcp_reassembly_table, tvb, deseg_offset,
3096 pinfo, msp->first_frame, NULL((void*)0),
3097 0, nxtseq - deseg_seq,
3098 LT_SEQ(nxtseq, msp->nxtpdu)((gint32)((nxtseq) - (msp->nxtpdu)) < 0));
3099 }
3100 }
3101
3102 if (!called_dissector || pinfo->desegment_len != 0) {
3103 if (ipfd_head != NULL((void*)0) && ipfd_head->reassembled_in != 0 &&
3104 !(ipfd_head->flags & FD_PARTIAL_REASSEMBLY0x0040)) {
3105 /*
3106 * We know what frame this PDU is reassembled in;
3107 * let the user know.
3108 */
3109 item = proto_tree_add_uint(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_reassembled_in, tvb, 0,
3110 0, ipfd_head->reassembled_in);
3111 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
3112 }
3113
3114 /*
3115 * Either we didn't call the subdissector at all (i.e.,
3116 * this is a segment that contains the middle of a
3117 * higher-level PDU, but contains neither the beginning
3118 * nor the end), or the subdissector couldn't dissect it
3119 * all, as some data was missing (i.e., it set
3120 * "pinfo->desegment_len" to the amount of additional
3121 * data it needs).
3122 */
3123 if (pinfo->desegment_offset == 0) {
3124 /*
3125 * It couldn't, in fact, dissect any of it (the
3126 * first byte it couldn't dissect is at an offset
3127 * of "pinfo->desegment_offset" from the beginning
3128 * of the payload, and that's 0).
3129 * Just mark this as TCP.
3130 */
3131 col_set_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL, "TCP");
3132 col_set_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "[TCP segment of a reassembled PDU]");
3133 }
3134
3135 /*
3136 * Show what's left in the packet as just raw TCP segment
3137 * data.
3138 * XXX - remember what protocol the last subdissector
3139 * was, and report it as a continuation of that, instead?
3140 */
3141 nbytes = tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, deseg_offset);
3142
3143 proto_tree_add_bytes_format(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_segment_data, tvb, deseg_offset,
3144 -1, NULL((void*)0), "TCP segment data (%u byte%s)", nbytes,
3145 plurality(nbytes, "", "s")((nbytes) == 1 ? ("") : ("s")));
3146 }
3147 pinfo->can_desegment = 0;
3148 pinfo->desegment_offset = 0;
3149 pinfo->desegment_len = 0;
3150
3151 if(another_pdu_follows) {
3152 /* there was another pdu following this one. */
3153 pinfo->can_desegment = 2;
3154 /* we also have to prevent the dissector from changing the
3155 * PROTOCOL and INFO columns since what follows may be an
3156 * incomplete PDU and we don't want it be changed back from
3157 * <Protocol> to <TCP>
3158 */
3159 col_set_fence(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO);
3160 cleared_writable |= col_get_writable(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL);
3161 col_set_writable(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL, FALSE(0));
3162 offset += another_pdu_follows;
3163 seq += another_pdu_follows;
3164 goto again;
3165 } else {
3166 /* remove any blocking set above otherwise the
3167 * proto,colinfo tap will break
3168 */
3169 if(cleared_writable) {
3170 col_set_writable(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL, TRUE(!(0)));
3171 }
3172 }
3173}
3174
3175void
3176tcp_dissect_pdus(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *tree,
3177 gboolean proto_desegment, guint fixed_len,
3178 guint (*get_pdu_len)(packet_info *, tvbuff_t *, int, void*),
3179 dissector_t dissect_pdu, void* dissector_data)
3180{
3181 volatile int offset = 0;
3182 int offset_before;
3183 guint captured_length_remaining;
3184 volatile guint plen;
3185 guint length;
3186 tvbuff_t *next_tvb;
3187 proto_item *item=NULL((void*)0);
3188 const char *saved_proto;
3189 guint8 curr_layer_num;
3190 wmem_list_frame_t *frame;
3191
3192 while (tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset) > 0) {
3193 /*
3194 * We use "tvb_ensure_captured_length_remaining()" to make
3195 * sure there actually *is* data remaining. The protocol
3196 * we're handling could conceivably consists of a sequence of
3197 * fixed-length PDUs, and therefore the "get_pdu_len" routine
3198 * might not actually fetch anything from the tvbuff, and thus
3199 * might not cause an exception to be thrown if we've run past
3200 * the end of the tvbuff.
3201 *
3202 * This means we're guaranteed that "captured_length_remaining" is positive.
3203 */
3204 captured_length_remaining = tvb_ensure_captured_length_remaining(tvb, offset);
3205
3206 /*
3207 * Can we do reassembly?
3208 */
3209 if (proto_desegment && pinfo->can_desegment) {
3210 /*
3211 * Yes - is the fixed-length part of the PDU split across segment
3212 * boundaries?
3213 */
3214 if (captured_length_remaining < fixed_len) {
3215 /*
3216 * Yes. Tell the TCP dissector where the data for this message
3217 * starts in the data it handed us and that we need "some more
3218 * data." Don't tell it exactly how many bytes we need because
3219 * if/when we ask for even more (after the header) that will
3220 * break reassembly.
3221 */
3222 pinfo->desegment_offset = offset;
3223 pinfo->desegment_len = DESEGMENT_ONE_MORE_SEGMENT0x0fffffff;
3224 return;
3225 }
3226 }
3227
3228 /*
3229 * Get the length of the PDU.
3230 */
3231 plen = (*get_pdu_len)(pinfo, tvb, offset, dissector_data);
3232 if (plen == 0) {
3233 /*
3234 * Support protocols which have a variable length which cannot
3235 * always be determined within the given fixed_len.
3236 */
3237 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(proto_desegment && pinfo->can_desegment)((void) ((proto_desegment && pinfo->can_desegment)
? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\"", "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 3237, "proto_desegment && pinfo->can_desegment")
))));
3238 pinfo->desegment_offset = offset;
3239 pinfo->desegment_len = DESEGMENT_ONE_MORE_SEGMENT0x0fffffff;
3240 return;
3241 }
3242 if (plen < fixed_len) {
3243 /*
3244 * Either:
3245 *
3246 * 1) the length value extracted from the fixed-length portion
3247 * doesn't include the fixed-length portion's length, and
3248 * was so large that, when the fixed-length portion's
3249 * length was added to it, the total length overflowed;
3250 *
3251 * 2) the length value extracted from the fixed-length portion
3252 * includes the fixed-length portion's length, and the value
3253 * was less than the fixed-length portion's length, i.e. it
3254 * was bogus.
3255 *
3256 * Report this as a bounds error.
3257 */
3258 show_reported_bounds_error(tvb, pinfo, tree);
3259 return;
3260 }
3261
3262 /* give a hint to TCP where the next PDU starts
3263 * so that it can attempt to find it in case it starts
3264 * somewhere in the middle of a segment.
3265 */
3266 if(!pinfo->fd->flags.visited && tcp_analyze_seq) {
3267 guint remaining_bytes;
3268 remaining_bytes = tvb_reported_length_remaining(tvb, offset);
3269 if(plen>remaining_bytes) {
3270 pinfo->want_pdu_tracking=2;
3271 pinfo->bytes_until_next_pdu=plen-remaining_bytes;
3272 }
3273 }
3274
3275 /*
3276 * Can we do reassembly?
3277 */
3278 if (proto_desegment && pinfo->can_desegment) {
3279 /*
3280 * Yes - is the PDU split across segment boundaries?
3281 */
3282 if (captured_length_remaining < plen) {
3283 /*
3284 * Yes. Tell the TCP dissector where the data for this message
3285 * starts in the data it handed us, and how many more bytes we
3286 * need, and return.
3287 */
3288 pinfo->desegment_offset = offset;
3289 pinfo->desegment_len = plen - captured_length_remaining;
3290 return;
3291 }
3292 }
3293
3294 curr_layer_num = pinfo->curr_layer_num-1;
3295 frame = wmem_list_frame_prev(wmem_list_tail(pinfo->layers));
3296 while (frame && (proto_tcp != (gint) GPOINTER_TO_UINT(wmem_list_frame_data(frame))((guint) (gulong) (wmem_list_frame_data(frame))))) {
3297 frame = wmem_list_frame_prev(frame);
3298 curr_layer_num--;
3299 }
3300#if 0
3301 if (captured_length_remaining >= plen || there are more packets)
3302 {
3303#endif
3304 /*
3305 * Display the PDU length as a field
3306 */
3307 item=proto_tree_add_uint((proto_tree *)p_get_proto_data(pinfo->pool, pinfo, proto_tcp, curr_layer_num),
3308 hf_tcp_pdu_size,
3309 tvb, offset, plen, plen);
3310 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
3311#if 0
3312 } else {
3313 item = proto_tree_add_expert_format((proto_tree *)p_get_proto_data(pinfo->pool, pinfo, proto_tcp, curr_layer_num),
3314 tvb, offset, -1,
3315 "PDU Size: %u cut short at %u",plen,captured_length_remaining);
3316 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
3317 }
3318#endif
3319
3320 /*
3321 * Construct a tvbuff containing the amount of the payload we have
3322 * available. Make its reported length the amount of data in the PDU.
3323 */
3324 length = captured_length_remaining;
3325 if (length > plen)
3326 length = plen;
3327 next_tvb = tvb_new_subset(tvb, offset, length, plen);
3328
3329 /*
3330 * Dissect the PDU.
3331 *
3332 * If it gets an error that means there's no point in
3333 * dissecting any more PDUs, rethrow the exception in
3334 * question.
3335 *
3336 * If it gets any other error, report it and continue, as that
3337 * means that PDU got an error, but that doesn't mean we should
3338 * stop dissecting PDUs within this frame or chunk of reassembled
3339 * data.
3340 */
3341 saved_proto = pinfo->current_proto;
3342 TRY{ except_t *volatile exc; volatile int except_state = 0; static
const except_id_t catch_spec[] = { { 1, 0 } }; { struct except_stacknode
except_sn; struct except_catch except_ch; except_setup_try(&
except_sn, &except_ch, catch_spec, 1); if (_setjmp (except_ch
.except_jmp)) *(&exc) = &except_ch.except_obj; else *
(&exc) = 0; if(except_state & 1) except_state |= 2; except_state
&= ~1; if (except_state == 0 && exc == 0) {
3343 (*dissect_pdu)(next_tvb, pinfo, tree, dissector_data);
3344 }
3345 CATCH_NONFATAL_ERRORSif (except_state == 0 && exc != 0 && (exc->
except_id.except_code == (2) || exc->except_id.except_code
== (6) || exc->except_id.except_code == (8)) && (
except_state|=1)) {
3346 show_exception(tvb, pinfo, tree, EXCEPT_CODE((exc)->except_id.except_code), GET_MESSAGE((exc)->except_message));
3347
3348 /*
3349 * Restore the saved protocol as well; we do this after
3350 * show_exception(), so that the "Malformed packet" indication
3351 * shows the protocol for which dissection failed.
3352 */
3353 pinfo->current_proto = saved_proto;
3354 }
3355 ENDTRYif(!(except_state&1) && exc != 0) except_rethrow(
exc); except_free(except_ch.except_obj.except_dyndata); except_pop
(); };};
3356
3357 /*
3358 * Step to the next PDU.
3359 * Make sure we don't overflow.
3360 */
3361 offset_before = offset;
3362 offset += plen;
3363 if (offset <= offset_before)
3364 break;
3365 }
3366}
3367
3368static void
3369tcp_info_append_uint(packet_info *pinfo, const char *abbrev, guint32 val)
3370{
3371 /* fstr(" %s=%u", abbrev, val) */
3372 col_append_str_uint(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, abbrev, val, " ");
3373}
3374
3375static void
3376dissect_tcpopt_tfo_payload(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, guint optlen,
3377 packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *exp_tree, void *data)
3378{
3379 proto_item *hidden_item, *ti;
3380 struct tcpheader *tcph = (struct tcpheader*)data;
3381
3382 hidden_item = proto_tree_add_item(exp_tree, hf_tcp_option_fast_open,
3383 tvb, offset, 2, ENC_NA0x00000000);
3384 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(hidden_item)do { if (hidden_item) do { if (((hidden_item)->finfo)) (((
hidden_item)->finfo))->flags = (((hidden_item)->finfo
))->flags | (0x00000001); } while(0); } while(0);
3385 if (optlen == 2) {
3386 /* Fast Open Cookie Request */
3387 proto_tree_add_item(exp_tree, hf_tcp_option_fast_open_cookie_request,
3388 tvb, offset, 2, ENC_NA0x00000000);
3389 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " TFO=R");
3390 } else if (optlen > 2) {
3391 /* Fast Open Cookie */
3392 ti = proto_tree_add_item(exp_tree, hf_tcp_option_fast_open_cookie,
3393 tvb, offset + 2, optlen - 2, ENC_NA0x00000000);
3394 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " TFO=C");
3395 if(tcph->th_flags & TH_SYN0x0002) {
3396 if((tcph->th_flags & TH_ACK0x0010) == 0) {
3397 expert_add_info(pinfo, ti, &ei_tcp_analysis_tfo_syn);
3398 }
3399 }
3400 }
3401}
3402
3403static void
3404dissect_tcpopt_tfo(const ip_tcp_opt *optp _U___attribute__((unused)), tvbuff_t *tvb,
3405 int offset, guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data)
3406{
3407 proto_item *item;
3408 proto_tree *exp_tree;
3409
3410 item = proto_tree_add_item(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_tfo, tvb,
3411 offset, optlen, ENC_NA0x00000000);
3412 exp_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(item, ett_tcp_option_exp);
3413 proto_tree_add_item(exp_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3414 proto_tree_add_item(exp_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb, offset + 1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3415
3416 dissect_tcpopt_tfo_payload(tvb, offset, optlen, pinfo, exp_tree, data);
3417}
3418static void
3419dissect_tcpopt_exp(const ip_tcp_opt *optp _U___attribute__((unused)), tvbuff_t *tvb,
3420 int offset, guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data )
3421{
3422 proto_item *item;
3423 proto_tree *exp_tree;
3424 guint16 magic;
3425
3426 item = proto_tree_add_item(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_exp, tvb,
3427 offset, optlen, ENC_NA0x00000000);
3428 exp_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(item, ett_tcp_option_exp);
3429 proto_tree_add_item(exp_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3430 proto_tree_add_item(exp_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb, offset + 1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3431 if (tcp_exp_options_with_magic && ((optlen - 2) > 0)) {
3432 magic = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + 2);
3433 proto_tree_add_item(exp_tree, hf_tcp_option_exp_magic_number, tvb,
3434 offset + 2, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3435 switch (magic) {
3436 case 0xf989: /* RFC7413, TCP Fast Open */
3437 dissect_tcpopt_tfo_payload(tvb, offset+2, optlen-2, pinfo, exp_tree, data);
3438 break;
3439 default:
3440 /* Unknown magic number */
3441 break;
3442 }
3443 } else {
3444 proto_tree_add_item(exp_tree, hf_tcp_option_exp_data, tvb,
3445 offset + 2, optlen - 2, ENC_NA0x00000000);
3446 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "Expxx", TRUE(!(0)));
3447 }
3448}

3483/* The window scale extension is defined in RFC 1323 */
3484static void
3485dissect_tcpopt_wscale(const ip_tcp_opt *optp _U___attribute__((unused)), tvbuff_t *tvb,
3486 int offset, guint optlen _U___attribute__((unused)), packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
3487{
3488 guint8 val;
3489 guint32 shift;
3490 proto_item *wscale_pi, *shift_pi, *gen_pi;
3491 proto_tree *wscale_tree;
3492 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd=NULL((void*)0);
3493
3494 tcpd=get_tcp_conversation_data(NULL((void*)0),pinfo);
3495
3496 wscale_tree = proto_tree_add_subtree(opt_tree, tvb, offset, 3, ett_tcp_option_wscale, &wscale_pi, "Window scale: ");
3497
3498 proto_tree_add_item(wscale_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3499 offset += 1;
3500
3501 proto_tree_add_item(wscale_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3502 offset += 1;
3503
3504 shift_pi = proto_tree_add_item_ret_uint(wscale_tree, hf_tcp_option_wscale_shift, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000, &shift);
3505 if (shift > 14) {
3506 /* RFC 1323: "If a Window Scale option is received with a shift.cnt
3507 * value exceeding 14, the TCP should log the error but use 14 instead
3508 * of the specified value." */
3509 shift = 14;
3510 expert_add_info(pinfo, shift_pi, &ei_tcp_option_wscale_shift_invalid);
3511 }
3512
3513 gen_pi = proto_tree_add_uint(wscale_tree, hf_tcp_option_wscale_multiplier, tvb,
3514 offset, 1, 1 << shift);
3515 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(gen_pi)do { if (gen_pi) do { if (((gen_pi)->finfo)) (((gen_pi)->
finfo))->flags = (((gen_pi)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002
); } while(0); } while(0);
3516 val = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
3517
3518 proto_item_append_text(wscale_pi, "%u (multiply by %u)", val, 1 << shift);
3519
3520 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "WS", 1 << shift);
3521
3522 if(!pinfo->fd->flags.visited) {
3523 pdu_store_window_scale_option(shift, tcpd);
3524 }
3525}
3526
3527static void
3528dissect_tcpopt_sack(const ip_tcp_opt *optp, tvbuff_t *tvb,
3529 int offset, guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data)
3530{
3531 proto_tree *field_tree = NULL((void*)0);
3532 proto_item *tf;
3533 proto_item *hidden_item;
3534 guint32 leftedge, rightedge;
3535 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd=NULL((void*)0);
3536 struct tcpheader *tcph = (struct tcpheader *)data;
3537 guint32 base_ack=0;
3538 guint num_sack_ranges = 0;
3539
3540 if(tcp_analyze_seq && tcp_relative_seq) {
3541 /* find(or create if needed) the conversation for this tcp session */
3542 tcpd=get_tcp_conversation_data(NULL((void*)0),pinfo);
3543
3544 if (tcpd) {
3545 base_ack=tcpd->rev->base_seq;
3546 }
3547 }
3548
3549 field_tree = proto_tree_add_subtree_format(opt_tree, tvb, offset, optlen,
3550 *optp->subtree_index, NULL((void*)0), "%s:", optp->name);
3551
3552 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb,
3553 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3554 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb,
3555 offset + 1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3556
3557 hidden_item = proto_tree_add_boolean(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_sack, tvb,
3558 offset, optlen, TRUE(!(0)));
3559 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(hidden_item)do { if (hidden_item) do { if (((hidden_item)->finfo)) (((
hidden_item)->finfo))->flags = (((hidden_item)->finfo
))->flags | (0x00000001); } while(0); } while(0);
3560
3561 offset += 2; /* skip past type and length */
3562 optlen -= 2; /* subtract size of type and length */
3563
3564 while (optlen > 0) {
3565 if (optlen < 4) {
3566 proto_tree_add_expert(field_tree, pinfo, &ei_tcp_suboption_malformed, tvb, offset, optlen);
3567 break;
3568 }
3569 leftedge = tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset)-base_ack;
3570 proto_tree_add_uint_format(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_sack_sle, tvb,
3571 offset, 4, leftedge,
3572 "left edge = %u%s", leftedge,
3573 tcp_relative_seq ? " (relative)" : "");
3574
3575 optlen -= 4;
3576 if (optlen < 4) {
3577 proto_tree_add_expert(field_tree, pinfo, &ei_tcp_suboption_malformed, tvb, offset, optlen);
3578 break;
3579 }
3580 /* XXX - check whether it goes past end of packet */
3581 rightedge = tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset + 4)-base_ack;
3582 optlen -= 4;
3583 proto_tree_add_uint_format(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_sack_sre, tvb,
3584 offset+4, 4, rightedge,
3585 "right edge = %u%s", rightedge,
3586 tcp_relative_seq ? " (relative)" : "");
3587 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "SLE", leftedge);
3588 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "SRE", rightedge);
3589 num_sack_ranges++;
3590
3591 /* Update tap info */
3592 if (tcph != NULL((void*)0) && (tcph->num_sack_ranges < MAX_TCP_SACK_RANGES4)) {
3593 tcph->sack_left_edge[tcph->num_sack_ranges] = leftedge;
3594 tcph->sack_right_edge[tcph->num_sack_ranges] = rightedge;
3595 tcph->num_sack_ranges++;
3596 }
3597
3598 proto_item_append_text(field_tree, " %u-%u", leftedge, rightedge);
3599 offset += 8;
3600 }
3601
3602 /* Show number of SACK ranges in this option as a generated field */
3603 tf = proto_tree_add_uint(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_sack_range_count,
3604 tvb, 0, 0, num_sack_ranges);
3605 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(tf)do { if (tf) do { if (((tf)->finfo)) (((tf)->finfo))->
flags = (((tf)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
3606}

3665static struct mptcp_analysis*
3666mptcp_alloc_analysis(struct tcp_analysis* tcpd) {
3667
3668 struct mptcp_analysis* mptcpd;
3669
3670 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(tcpd->mptcp_analysis == 0)((void) ((tcpd->mptcp_analysis == 0) ? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug
(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\""
, "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 3670, "tcpd->mptcp_analysis == 0")))));
3671
3672 mptcpd = (struct mptcp_analysis*)wmem_new0(wmem_file_scope(), struct mptcp_analysis)((struct mptcp_analysis*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_file_scope()), sizeof
(struct mptcp_analysis)));
3673 mptcpd->subflows = wmem_list_new(wmem_file_scope());
3674
3675 mptcpd->stream = mptcp_stream_count++;
3676 tcpd->mptcp_analysis = mptcpd;
3677
3678 memset(&mptcpd->meta_flow, 0, 2*sizeof(mptcp_meta_flow_t));
3679
3680 /* arbitrary assignment. Callers may override this */
3681 tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta = &mptcpd->meta_flow[0];
3682 tcpd->rev->mptcp_subflow->meta = &mptcpd->meta_flow[1];
3683
3684 return mptcpd;
3685}

3687
3688/* will create necessary structure if fails to find a match on the token */
3689static struct mptcp_analysis*
3690mptcp_get_meta_from_token(struct tcp_analysis* tcpd, tcp_flow_t *tcp_flow, guint32 token) {
3691
3692 struct mptcp_analysis* result = NULL((void*)0);
3693 struct mptcp_analysis* mptcpd = tcpd->mptcp_analysis;
3694 guint8 assignedMetaId = 0; /* array id < 2 */
3695
3696 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(tcp_flow == tcpd->fwd || tcp_flow == tcpd->rev)((void) ((tcp_flow == tcpd->fwd || tcp_flow == tcpd->rev
) ? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(
wmem_packet_scope(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\"", "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 3696, "tcp_flow == tcpd->fwd || tcp_flow == tcpd->rev"
)))));
3697
3698
3699
3700 /* if token already set for this meta */
3701 if( tcp_flow->mptcp_subflow->meta && (tcp_flow->mptcp_subflow->meta->static_flags & MPTCP_META_HAS_TOKEN0x04)) {
3702 return mptcpd;
3703 }
3704
3705 /* else look for a registered meta with this token */
3706 result = (struct mptcp_analysis*)wmem_tree_lookup32(mptcp_tokens, token);
3707
3708 /* if token already registered than just share it across TCP connections */
3709 if(result) {
3710 mptcpd = result;
3711 mptcp_attach_subflow(mptcpd, tcpd);
3712 }
3713 else {
3714 /* we create it if this connection */
3715 if(!mptcpd) {
3716 /* don't care which meta to choose assign each meta to a direction */
3717 mptcpd = mptcp_alloc_analysis(tcpd);
3718 mptcp_attach_subflow(mptcpd, tcpd);
3719 }
3720 else {
3721
3722 /* already exists, thus some meta may already have been configured */
3723 if(mptcpd->meta_flow[0].static_flags & MPTCP_META_HAS_TOKEN0x04) {
3724 assignedMetaId = 1;
3725 }
3726 else if(mptcpd->meta_flow[1].static_flags & MPTCP_META_HAS_TOKEN0x04) {
3727 assignedMetaId = 0;
3728 }
3729 else {
3730 DISSECTOR_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED()(proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"DISSECTOR_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED\""
, "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 3730)));
3731 }
3732 tcp_flow->mptcp_subflow->meta = &mptcpd->meta_flow[assignedMetaId];
3733 }
3734 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(tcp_flow->mptcp_subflow->meta)((void) ((tcp_flow->mptcp_subflow->meta) ? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug
(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\""
, "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 3734, "tcp_flow->mptcp_subflow->meta")))));
3735
3736 tcp_flow->mptcp_subflow->meta->token = token;
3737 tcp_flow->mptcp_subflow->meta->static_flags |= MPTCP_META_HAS_TOKEN0x04;
3738
3739 wmem_tree_insert32(mptcp_tokens, token, mptcpd);
3740 }
3741
3742 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(mptcpd)((void) ((mptcpd) ? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf
(wmem_packet_scope(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\"", "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 3742, "mptcpd")))));
3743
3744
3745 /* compute the meta id assigned to tcp_flow */
3746 assignedMetaId = (tcp_flow->mptcp_subflow->meta == &mptcpd->meta_flow[0]) ? 0 : 1;
3747
3748 /* computes the metaId tcpd->fwd should be assigned to */
3749 assignedMetaId = (tcp_flow == tcpd->fwd) ? assignedMetaId : (assignedMetaId +1) %2;
3750
3751 tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta = &mptcpd->meta_flow[ (assignedMetaId) ];
3752 tcpd->rev->mptcp_subflow->meta = &mptcpd->meta_flow[ (assignedMetaId +1) %2];
3753
3754 return mptcpd;
3755}
3756
3757/* setup from_key */
3758static
3759struct mptcp_analysis*
3760get_or_create_mptcpd_from_key(struct tcp_analysis* tcpd, tcp_flow_t *fwd, guint64 key, guint8 hmac_algo _U___attribute__((unused))) {
3761
3762 guint32 token = 0;
3763 guint64 expected_idsn= 0;
3764 struct mptcp_analysis* mptcpd = tcpd->mptcp_analysis;
3765
3766 if(fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta && (fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->static_flags & MPTCP_META_HAS_KEY0x03)) {
3767 return mptcpd;
3768 }
3769
3770 /* MPTCP only standardizes SHA1 for now. */
3771 mptcp_cryptodata_sha1(key, &token, &expected_idsn);
3772
3773 mptcpd = mptcp_get_meta_from_token(tcpd, fwd, token);
3774
3775 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta)((void) ((fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta) ? (void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug
(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\""
, "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 3775, "fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta")))));
3776
3777 fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->key = key;
3778 fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->static_flags |= MPTCP_META_HAS_KEY0x03;
3779 fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->base_dsn = expected_idsn;
3780 return mptcpd;
3781}
3782
3783
3784/*
3785 * The TCP Extensions for Multipath Operation with Multiple Addresses
3786 * are defined in RFC 6824
3787 *
3788 * <http://http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6824>
3789 *
3790 * Author: Andrei Maruseac <andrei.maruseac@intel.com>
3791 * Matthieu Coudron <matthieu.coudron@lip6.fr>
3792 *
3793 * This function just generates the mptcpheader, i.e. the generation of
3794 * datastructures is delayed/delegated to mptcp_analyze
3795 */
3796static void
3797dissect_tcpopt_mptcp(const ip_tcp_opt *optp _U___attribute__((unused)), tvbuff_t *tvb,
3798 int offset, guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data)
3799{
3800 proto_item *item,*main_item;
3801 proto_tree *mptcp_tree;
3802
3803 guint8 subtype;
3804 guint8 ipver;
3805 int start_offset = offset;
3806 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd = NULL((void*)0);
3807 struct mptcp_analysis* mptcpd = NULL((void*)0);
3808 struct tcpheader *tcph = (struct tcpheader *)data;
3809
3810 /* There may be several MPTCP options per packet, don't duplicate the structure */
3811 struct mptcpheader* mph = tcph->th_mptcp;
3812
3813 if(!mph) {
3814 mph = wmem_new0(wmem_packet_scope(), struct mptcpheader)((struct mptcpheader*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_packet_scope()), sizeof
(struct mptcpheader)));
3815 tcph->th_mptcp = mph;
3816 }
3817
3818 tcpd=get_tcp_conversation_data(NULL((void*)0),pinfo);
3819 mptcpd=tcpd->mptcp_analysis;
3820
3821 /* seeing an MPTCP packet on the subflow automatically qualifies it as an mptcp subflow */
3822 if(!tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow) {
3823 mptcp_init_subflow(tcpd->fwd);
3824 }
3825 if(!tcpd->rev->mptcp_subflow) {
3826 mptcp_init_subflow(tcpd->rev);
3827 }
3828
3829 col_set_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_PROTOCOL, "MPTCP");
3830 main_item = proto_tree_add_item(opt_tree, hf_mptcp, tvb, offset, optlen, ENC_NA0x00000000);
3831
3832 mptcp_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(main_item, ett_tcp_option_mptcp);
3833
3834 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3835 offset += 1;
3836
3837 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3838 offset += 1;
3839
3840 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_subtype, tvb,
3841 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3842
3843 subtype = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset) >> 4;
3844 proto_item_append_text(main_item, ": %s", val_to_str(subtype, mptcp_subtype_vs, "Unknown (%d)"));
3845
3846 /** preemptively allocate mptcpd when subtype won't allow to find a meta */
3847 if(!mptcpd && (subtype > TCPOPT_MPTCP_MP_JOIN0x1)) {
3848 mptcpd = mptcp_alloc_analysis(tcpd);
3849 }
3850
3851 switch (subtype) {
3852 case TCPOPT_MPTCP_MP_CAPABLE0x0:
3853 mph->mh_mpc = TRUE(!(0));
3854
3855 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_version, tvb,
3856 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3857 offset += 1;
3858
3859 item = proto_tree_add_bitmask(mptcp_tree, tvb, offset, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_flags,
3860 ett_tcp_option_mptcp, tcp_option_mptcp_capable_flags,
3861 ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3862 mph->mh_capable_flags = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
3863 if ((mph->mh_capable_flags & MPTCP_CAPABLE_CRYPTO_MASK0x3F) == 0) {
3864 expert_add_info(pinfo, item, &ei_mptcp_analysis_missing_algorithm);
3865 }
3866 if ((mph->mh_capable_flags & MPTCP_CAPABLE_CRYPTO_MASK0x3F) != MPTCP_HMAC_SHA1) {
3867 expert_add_info(pinfo, item, &ei_mptcp_analysis_unsupported_algorithm);
3868 }
3869 offset += 1;
3870
3871 /* optlen == 12 => SYN or SYN/ACK; optlen == 20 => ACK */
3872 if (optlen == 12 || optlen == 20) {
3873
3874 mph->mh_key = tvb_get_ntoh64(tvb,offset);
3875 proto_tree_add_uint64(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_sender_key, tvb, offset, 8, mph->mh_key);
3876 offset += 8;
3877
3878 mptcpd = get_or_create_mptcpd_from_key(tcpd, tcpd->fwd, mph->mh_key, mph->mh_capable_flags & MPTCP_CAPABLE_CRYPTO_MASK0x3F);
3879 mptcpd->master = tcpd;
3880
3881 item = proto_tree_add_uint(mptcp_tree,
3882 hf_mptcp_expected_token, tvb, offset, 0, tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->token);
3883 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
3884
3885 item = proto_tree_add_uint64_format_value(mptcp_tree,
3886 hf_mptcp_expected_idsn, tvb, offset, 0, tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->base_dsn, "%" G_GINT64_MODIFIER"l" "u (64bits version)", tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->base_dsn);
3887 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
3888
3889 /* last ACK of 3WHS, repeats both keys */
3890 if (optlen == 20) {
3891 guint64 recv_key = tvb_get_ntoh64(tvb,offset);
3892 proto_tree_add_uint64(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_recv_key, tvb, offset, 8, recv_key);
3893
3894 if(tcpd->rev->mptcp_subflow->meta
3895 && (tcpd->rev->mptcp_subflow->meta->static_flags & MPTCP_META_HAS_KEY0x03)) {
3896
3897 /* compare the echoed key with the server key */
3898 if(tcpd->rev->mptcp_subflow->meta->key != recv_key) {
3899 expert_add_info(pinfo, item, &ei_mptcp_analysis_echoed_key_mismatch);
3900 }
3901 }
3902 else {
3903 mptcpd = get_or_create_mptcpd_from_key(tcpd, tcpd->rev, recv_key, mph->mh_capable_flags & MPTCP_CAPABLE_CRYPTO_MASK0x3F);
3904 }
3905 }
3906 }
3907 break;
3908
3909 case TCPOPT_MPTCP_MP_JOIN0x1:
3910 mph->mh_join = TRUE(!(0));
3911 if(optlen != 12 && !mptcpd) {
3912 mptcpd = mptcp_alloc_analysis(tcpd);
3913 }
3914 switch (optlen) {
3915 /* Syn */
3916 case 12:
3917 {
3918 proto_tree_add_bitmask(mptcp_tree, tvb, offset, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_flags,
3919 ett_tcp_option_mptcp, tcp_option_mptcp_join_flags,
3920 ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3921 offset += 1;
3922 tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->address_id = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset);
3923 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_address_id, tvb, offset,
3924 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3925 offset += 1;
3926
3927 proto_tree_add_item_ret_uint(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_recv_token, tvb, offset,
3928 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000, &mph->mh_token);
3929 offset += 4;
3930
3931 mptcpd = mptcp_get_meta_from_token(tcpd, tcpd->rev, mph->mh_token);
3932
3933 proto_tree_add_item_ret_uint(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_sender_rand, tvb, offset,
3934 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000, &tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->nonce);
3935
3936 }
3937 break;
3938
3939
3940 case 16: /* Syn/Ack */
3941 proto_tree_add_bitmask(mptcp_tree, tvb, offset, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_flags,
3942 ett_tcp_option_mptcp, tcp_option_mptcp_join_flags,
3943 ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3944 offset += 1;
3945
3946 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_address_id, tvb, offset,
3947 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3948 offset += 1;
3949
3950 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_sender_trunc_hmac, tvb, offset,
3951 8, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3952 offset += 8;
3953
3954 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_sender_rand, tvb, offset,
3955 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3956 break;
3957
3958 case 24: /* Ack */
3959 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_reserved, tvb, offset,
3960 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3961 offset += 2;
3962
3963 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_sender_hmac, tvb, offset,
3964 20, ENC_NA0x00000000);
3965 break;
3966
3967 default:
3968 break;
3969 }
3970 break;
3971
3972 /* display only *raw* values since it is harder to guess a correct value than for TCP.
3973 One needs to enable mptcp_analysis to get more interesting data
3974 */
3975 case TCPOPT_MPTCP_DSS0x2:
3976 mph->mh_dss = TRUE(!(0));
3977
3978 offset += 1;
3979 mph->mh_dss_flags = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset) & 0x1F;
3980
3981 proto_tree_add_bitmask(mptcp_tree, tvb, offset, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_flags,
3982 ett_tcp_option_mptcp, tcp_option_mptcp_dss_flags,
3983 ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
3984 offset += 1;
3985
3986 /* displays "raw" DataAck , ie does not convert it to its 64 bits form
3987 to do so you need to enable
3988 */
3989 if (mph->mh_dss_flags & MPTCP_DSS_FLAG_DATA_ACK_PRESENT0x01) {
3990
3991 guint64 dack64;
3992
3993 /* 64bits ack */
3994 if (mph->mh_dss_flags & MPTCP_DSS_FLAG_DATA_ACK_8BYTES0x02) {
3995
3996 mph->mh_dss_rawack = tvb_get_ntoh64(tvb,offset);
3997 proto_tree_add_uint64_format_value(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_data_ack_raw, tvb, offset, 8, mph->mh_dss_rawack, "%" G_GINT64_MODIFIER"l" "u (64bits)", mph->mh_dss_rawack);
3998 offset += 8;
3999 }
4000 /* 32bits ack */
4001 else {
4002 mph->mh_dss_rawack = tvb_get_ntohl(tvb,offset);
4003 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_data_ack_raw, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4004 offset += 4;
4005 }
4006
4007 if(mptcp_convert_dsn(mph->mh_dss_rawack, tcpd->rev->mptcp_subflow->meta,
4008 (mph->mh_dss_flags & MPTCP_DSS_FLAG_DATA_ACK_8BYTES0x02) ? DSN_CONV_NONE : DSN_CONV_32_TO_64, mptcp_relative_seq, &dack64)) {
4009 item = proto_tree_add_uint64(mptcp_tree, hf_mptcp_ack, tvb, 0, 0, dack64);
4010 if (mptcp_relative_seq) {
4011 proto_item_append_text(item, " (Relative)");
4012 }
4013
4014 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
4015 }
4016 else {
4017 /* ignore and continue */
4018 }
4019
4020 }
4021
4022 /* Mapping present */
4023 if (mph->mh_dss_flags & MPTCP_DSS_FLAG_MAPPING_PRESENT0x04) {
4024
4025 guint64 dsn;
4026
4027 if (mph->mh_dss_flags & MPTCP_DSS_FLAG_DSN_8BYTES0x08) {
4028
4029 dsn = tvb_get_ntoh64(tvb,offset);
4030 proto_tree_add_uint64_format_value(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_data_seq_no_raw, tvb, offset, 8, dsn, "%" G_GINT64_MODIFIER"l" "u (64bits version)", dsn);
4031
4032 /* if we have the opportunity to complete the 32 Most Significant Bits of the
4033 *
4034 */
4035 if(!(tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->static_flags & MPTCP_META_HAS_BASE_DSN_MSB0x01)) {
4036 tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->static_flags |= MPTCP_META_HAS_BASE_DSN_MSB0x01;
4037 tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->base_dsn |= (dsn & (guint32) 0);
4038 }
4039 offset += 8;
4040 } else {
4041 dsn = tvb_get_ntohl(tvb,offset);
4042 proto_tree_add_uint64_format_value(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_data_seq_no_raw, tvb, offset, 4, dsn, "%" G_GINT64_MODIFIER"l" "u (32bits version)", dsn);
4043 offset += 4;
4044 }
4045 mph->mh_dss_rawdsn = dsn;
4046
4047 proto_tree_add_item_ret_uint(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_subflow_seq_no, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000, &mph->mh_dss_ssn);
4048 offset += 4;
4049
4050 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_data_lvl_len, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4051 mph->mh_dss_length = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb,offset);
4052 offset += 2;
4053
4054 if(mph->mh_dss_length == 0) {
4055 expert_add_info(pinfo, mptcp_tree, &ei_mptcp_infinite_mapping);
4056 }
4057
4058 /* print head & tail dsn */
4059 if(mptcp_convert_dsn(mph->mh_dss_rawdsn, tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta,
4060 (mph->mh_dss_flags & MPTCP_DSS_FLAG_DATA_ACK_8BYTES0x02) ? DSN_CONV_NONE : DSN_CONV_32_TO_64, mptcp_relative_seq, &dsn)) {
4061 item = proto_tree_add_uint64(mptcp_tree, hf_mptcp_dss_dsn, tvb, 0, 0, dsn);
4062 if (mptcp_relative_seq) {
4063 proto_item_append_text(item, " (Relative)");
4064 }
4065
4066 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
4067 }
4068 else {
4069 /* ignore and continue */
4070 }
4071
4072 /* if mapping analysis enabled and not a */
4073 if(mptcp_analyze_mappings && mph->mh_dss_length)
4074 {
4075
4076 if (!PINFO_FD_VISITED(pinfo)((pinfo)->fd->flags.visited))
4077 {
4078
4079 /* register SSN range described by the mapping into a subflow interval_tree */
4080 mptcp_dss_mapping_t *mapping = NULL((void*)0);
4081 mapping = wmem_new0(wmem_file_scope(), mptcp_dss_mapping_t)((mptcp_dss_mapping_t*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_file_scope()), sizeof
(mptcp_dss_mapping_t)));
4082
4083 mapping->rawdsn = mph->mh_dss_rawdsn;
4084 mapping->extended_dsn = (mph->mh_dss_flags & MPTCP_DSS_FLAG_DATA_ACK_8BYTES0x02);
4085 mapping->frame = pinfo->fd->num;
4086 mapping->ssn_low = mph->mh_dss_ssn;
4087 mapping->ssn_high = mph->mh_dss_ssn + mph->mh_dss_length-1;
4088
4089 wmem_itree_insert(tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->mappings,
4090 mph->mh_dss_ssn,
4091 mapping->ssn_high,
4092 mapping
4093 );
4094 }
4095 }
4096
4097 if ((int)optlen >= offset-start_offset+4)
4098 {
4099 proto_tree_add_checksum(mptcp_tree, tvb, offset, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_checksum, -1, NULL((void*)0), pinfo, 0, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000, PROTO_CHECKSUM_NO_FLAGS0x00);
4100 }
4101 }
4102 break;
4103
4104 case TCPOPT_MPTCP_ADD_ADDR0x3:
4105 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4106 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_ipver, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4107 ipver = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset) & 0x0F;
4108 offset += 1;
4109
4110 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4111 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_address_id, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4112 offset += 1;
4113
4114 switch (ipver) {
4115 case 4:
4116 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4117 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_ipv4, tvb, offset, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4118 offset += 4;
4119 break;
4120
4121 case 6:
4122 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4123 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_ipv6, tvb, offset, 16, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4124 offset += 16;
4125 break;
4126
4127 default:
4128 break;
4129 }
4130
4131 if (optlen % 4 == 2) {
4132 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4133 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_port, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4134 offset += 2;
4135 }
4136
4137 if (optlen == 16 || optlen == 18 || optlen == 28 || optlen == 30) {
4138 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4139 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_addaddr_trunc_hmac, tvb, offset, 8, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4140 }
4141 break;
4142
4143 case TCPOPT_MPTCP_REMOVE_ADDR0x4:
4144 item = proto_tree_add_uint(mptcp_tree, hf_mptcp_number_of_removed_addresses, tvb, start_offset+2,
4145 1, optlen - 3);
4146 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo
))->flags = (((item)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002);
} while(0); } while(0);
4147 offset += 1;
4148 while(offset < start_offset + (int)optlen) {
4149 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_address_id, tvb, offset,
4150 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4151 offset += 1;
4152 }
4153 break;
4154
4155 case TCPOPT_MPTCP_MP_PRIO0x5:
4156 proto_tree_add_bitmask(mptcp_tree, tvb, offset, hf_tcp_option_mptcp_flags,
4157 ett_tcp_option_mptcp, tcp_option_mptcp_join_flags,
4158 ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4159 offset += 1;
4160
4161 if (optlen == 4) {
4162 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4163 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_address_id, tvb, offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4164 }
4165 break;
4166
4167 case TCPOPT_MPTCP_MP_FAIL0x6:
4168 mph->mh_fail = TRUE(!(0));
4169 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4170 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_reserved, tvb, offset,2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4171 offset += 2;
4172
4173 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4174 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_data_seq_no_raw, tvb, offset, 8, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4175 break;
4176
4177 case TCPOPT_MPTCP_MP_FASTCLOSE0x7:
4178 mph->mh_fastclose = TRUE(!(0));
4179 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4180 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_reserved, tvb, offset, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4181 offset += 2;
4182
4183 proto_tree_add_item(mptcp_tree,
4184 hf_tcp_option_mptcp_recv_key, tvb, offset, 8, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4185 mph->mh_key = tvb_get_ntoh64(tvb,offset);
4186 break;
4187
4188 default:
4189 break;
4190 }
4191
4192 if(!mptcpd || !tcpd->mptcp_analysis) {
4193 return;
4194 }
4195
4196 /* if mptcpd just got allocated, remember the initial addresses
4197 * which will serve as identifiers for the conversation filter
4198 */
4199 if(tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->ip_src.len == 0) {
4200
4201 copy_address_wmem(wmem_file_scope(), &tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->ip_src, &tcph->ip_src);
4202 copy_address_wmem(wmem_file_scope(), &tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->ip_dst, &tcph->ip_dst);
4203
4204 copy_address_shallow(&tcpd->rev->mptcp_subflow->meta->ip_src, &tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->ip_dst);
4205 copy_address_shallow(&tcpd->rev->mptcp_subflow->meta->ip_dst, &tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->ip_src);
4206
4207 tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->sport = tcph->th_sport;
4208 tcpd->fwd->mptcp_subflow->meta->dport = tcph->th_dport;
4209 }
4210
4211 mph->mh_stream = tcpd->mptcp_analysis->stream;
4212}
4213
4214static void
4215dissect_tcpopt_cc(const ip_tcp_opt *optp, tvbuff_t *tvb,
4216 int offset, guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
4217{
4218 proto_tree *field_tree;
4219 proto_item *hidden_item;
4220 guint32 cc;
4221
4222 cc = tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset + 2);
4223 hidden_item = proto_tree_add_boolean(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_cc, tvb, offset,
4224 optlen, TRUE(!(0)));
4225 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(hidden_item)do { if (hidden_item) do { if (((hidden_item)->finfo)) (((
hidden_item)->finfo))->flags = (((hidden_item)->finfo
))->flags | (0x00000001); } while(0); } while(0);
4226 field_tree = proto_tree_add_subtree_format(opt_tree, tvb, offset, optlen,
4227 ett_tcp_opt_cc, NULL((void*)0), "%s: %u", optp->name, cc);
4228 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "CC", cc);
4229 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb,
4230 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4231 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb,
4232 offset + 1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4233}

4235static void
4236dissect_tcpopt_qs(const ip_tcp_opt *optp, tvbuff_t *tvb,
4237 int offset, guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
4238{
4239 proto_tree *field_tree;
4240 proto_item *hidden_item;
4241
4242 guint8 rate = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset + 2) & 0x0f;
4243
4244 hidden_item = proto_tree_add_boolean(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_qs, tvb, offset,
4245 optlen, TRUE(!(0)));
4246 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(hidden_item)do { if (hidden_item) do { if (((hidden_item)->finfo)) (((
hidden_item)->finfo))->flags = (((hidden_item)->finfo
))->flags | (0x00000001); } while(0); } while(0);
4247 field_tree = proto_tree_add_subtree_format(opt_tree, tvb, offset, optlen,
4248 ett_tcp_opt_qs, NULL((void*)0), "%s: Rate response, %s, TTL diff %u ", optp->name,
4249 val_to_str_ext_const(rate, &qs_rate_vals_ext, "Unknown"),
4250 tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset + 3));
4251 col_append_lstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO,
4252 " QSresp=", val_to_str_ext_const(rate, &qs_rate_vals_ext, "Unknown"),
4253 COL_ADD_LSTR_TERMINATOR(const char *) -1);
4254 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb,
4255 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4256 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb,
4257 offset + 1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4258}
4259
4260
4261static void
4262dissect_tcpopt_scps(const ip_tcp_opt *optp _U___attribute__((unused)), tvbuff_t *tvb,
4263 int offset, guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo,
4264 proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
4265{
4266 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd;
4267 proto_tree *field_tree = NULL((void*)0);
4268 tcp_flow_t *flow;
4269 int direction;
4270 proto_item *tf = NULL((void*)0), *hidden_item;
4271 guint8 capvector;
4272 guint8 connid;
4273
4274 tcpd = get_tcp_conversation_data(NULL((void*)0),pinfo);
4275
4276 /* check direction and get ua lists */
4277 direction=cmp_address(&pinfo->src, &pinfo->dst);
4278
4279 /* if the addresses are equal, match the ports instead */
4280 if(direction==0) {
4281 direction= (pinfo->srcport > pinfo->destport) ? 1 : -1;
4282 }
4283
4284 if(direction>=0)
4285 flow =&(tcpd->flow1);
4286 else
4287 flow =&(tcpd->flow2);
4288
4289 /* If the option length == 4, this is a real SCPS capability option
4290 * See "CCSDS 714.0-B-2 (CCSDS Recommended Standard for SCPS Transport Protocol
4291 * (SCPS-TP)" Section 3.2.3 for definition.
4292 */
4293 if (optlen == 4) {
4294 hidden_item = proto_tree_add_boolean(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_scps,
4295 tvb, offset, optlen, TRUE(!(0)));
4296 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(hidden_item)do { if (hidden_item) do { if (((hidden_item)->finfo)) (((
hidden_item)->finfo))->flags = (((hidden_item)->finfo
))->flags | (0x00000001); } while(0); } while(0);
4297
4298 capvector = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset + 2);
4299 connid = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset + 3);
4300
4301 tf = proto_tree_add_item(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_scps_vector, tvb,
4302 offset + 2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4303 field_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(tf, ett_tcp_option_scps);
4304 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb,
4305 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4306 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb,
4307 offset + 1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4308 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_scpsoption_flags_bets, tvb,
4309 offset + 2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4310 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_scpsoption_flags_snack1, tvb,
4311 offset + 2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4312 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_scpsoption_flags_snack2, tvb,
4313 offset + 2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4314 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_scpsoption_flags_compress, tvb,
4315 offset + 2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4316 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_scpsoption_flags_nlts, tvb,
4317 offset + 2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4318 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_scpsoption_flags_reserved, tvb,
4319 offset + 2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4320
4321 if (capvector) {
4322 struct capvec
4323 {
4324 guint8 mask;
4325 const gchar *str;
4326 } capvecs[] = {
4327 {0x80, "BETS"},
4328 {0x40, "SNACK1"},
4329 {0x20, "SNACK2"},
4330 {0x10, "COMP"},
4331 {0x08, "NLTS"},
4332 {0x07, "RESERVED"}
4333 };
4334 gboolean anyflag = FALSE(0);
4335 guint i;
4336
4337 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " SCPS[");
4338 for (i = 0; i < sizeof(capvecs)/sizeof(struct capvec); i++) {
4339 if (capvector & capvecs[i].mask) {
4340 proto_item_append_text(tf, "%s%s", anyflag ? ", " : " (",
4341 capvecs[i].str);
4342 col_append_lstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO,
4343 anyflag ? ", " : "",
4344 capvecs[i].str,
4345 COL_ADD_LSTR_TERMINATOR(const char *) -1);
4346 anyflag = TRUE(!(0));
4347 }
4348 }
4349 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "]");
4350 proto_item_append_text(tf, ")");
4351 }
4352
4353 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_scpsoption_connection_id, tvb,
4354 offset + 3, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4355 flow->scps_capable = 1;
4356
4357 if (connid)
4358 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "Connection ID", connid);
4359 } else {
4360 /* The option length != 4, so this is an infamous "extended capabilities
4361 * option. See "CCSDS 714.0-B-2 (CCSDS Recommended Standard for SCPS
4362 * Transport Protocol (SCPS-TP)" Section 3.2.5 for definition.
4363 *
4364 * As the format of this option is only partially defined (it is
4365 * a community (or more likely vendor) defined format beyond that, so
4366 * at least for now, we only parse the standardized portion of the option.
4367 */
4368 guint8 local_offset = 2;
4369 guint8 binding_space;
4370 guint8 extended_cap_length;
4371
4372 if (flow->scps_capable != 1) {
4373 /* There was no SCPS capabilities option preceding this */
4374 tf = proto_tree_add_uint_format(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_scps_vector,
4375 tvb, offset, optlen, 0,
4376 "Illegal SCPS Extended Capabilities (%d bytes)",
4377 optlen);
4378 field_tree=proto_item_add_subtree(tf, ett_tcp_option_scps_extended);
4379 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb,
4380 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4381 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb,
4382 offset + 1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4383 } else {
4384 tf = proto_tree_add_uint_format(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_scps_vector,
4385 tvb, offset, optlen, 0,
4386 "SCPS Extended Capabilities (%d bytes)",
4387 optlen);
4388 field_tree=proto_item_add_subtree(tf, ett_tcp_option_scps_extended);
4389 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb,
4390 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4391 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb,
4392 offset + 1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4393
4394 /* There may be multiple binding spaces included in a single option,
4395 * so we will semi-parse each of the stacked binding spaces - skipping
4396 * over the octets following the binding space identifier and length.
4397 */
4398 while (optlen > local_offset) {
4399
4400 /* 1st octet is Extended Capability Binding Space */
4401 binding_space = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, (offset + local_offset));
4402
4403 /* 2nd octet (upper 4-bits) has binding space length in 16-bit words.
4404 * As defined by the specification, this length is exclusive of the
4405 * octets containing the extended capability type and length
4406 */
4407 extended_cap_length =
4408 (tvb_get_guint8(tvb, (offset + local_offset + 1)) >> 4);
4409
4410 /* Convert the extended capabilities length into bytes for display */
4411 extended_cap_length = (extended_cap_length << 1);
4412
4413 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_scps_binding, tvb, offset + local_offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4414 proto_tree_add_uint(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_scps_binding_len, tvb, offset + local_offset + 1, 1, extended_cap_length);
4415
4416 /* Step past the binding space and length octets */
4417 local_offset += 2;
4418
4419 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_scps_binding_data, tvb, offset + local_offset, extended_cap_length, ENC_NA0x00000000);
4420
4421 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "EXCAP", binding_space);
4422
4423 /* Step past the Extended capability data
4424 * Treat the extended capability data area as opaque;
4425 * If one desires to parse the extended capability data
4426 * (say, in a vendor aware build of wireshark), it would
4427 * be triggered here.
4428 */
4429 local_offset += extended_cap_length;
4430 }
4431 }
4432 }
4433}
4434
4435static void
4436dissect_tcpopt_user_to(const ip_tcp_opt *optp, tvbuff_t *tvb,
4437 int offset, guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
4438{
4439 proto_item *hidden_item, *tf;
4440 proto_tree *field_tree;
4441 gboolean g;
4442 guint16 to;
4443
4444 proto_tree_add_item(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb,
4445 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4446 proto_tree_add_item(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb,
4447 offset + 1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4448
4449 g = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + 2) & 0x8000;
4450 to = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + 2) & 0x7FFF;
4451 hidden_item = proto_tree_add_boolean(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_user_to, tvb, offset,
4452 optlen, TRUE(!(0)));
4453 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(hidden_item)do { if (hidden_item) do { if (((hidden_item)->finfo)) (((
hidden_item)->finfo))->flags = (((hidden_item)->finfo
))->flags | (0x00000001); } while(0); } while(0);
4454
4455 tf = proto_tree_add_uint_format(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_user_to_val, tvb, offset,
4456 optlen, to, "%s: %u %s", optp->name, to, g ? "minutes" : "seconds");
4457 field_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(tf, *optp->subtree_index);
4458 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_user_to_granularity, tvb, offset + 2, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4459 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_user_to_val, tvb, offset + 2, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4460
4461 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "USER_TO", to);
4462}
4463
4464/* This is called for SYN+ACK packets and the purpose is to verify that
4465 * the SCPS capabilities option has been successfully negotiated for the flow.
4466 * If the SCPS capabilities option was offered by only one party, the
4467 * proactively set scps_capable attribute of the flow (set upon seeing
4468 * the first instance of the SCPS option) is revoked.
4469 */
4470static void
4471verify_scps(packet_info *pinfo, proto_item *tf_syn, struct tcp_analysis *tcpd)
4472{
4473 tf_syn = 0x0;
4474
4475 if(tcpd) {
4476 if ((!(tcpd->flow1.scps_capable)) || (!(tcpd->flow2.scps_capable))) {
4477 tcpd->flow1.scps_capable = 0;
4478 tcpd->flow2.scps_capable = 0;
4479 } else {
4480 expert_add_info(pinfo, tf_syn, &ei_tcp_scps_capable);
4481 }
4482 }
4483}
4484
4485/* See "CCSDS 714.0-B-2 (CCSDS Recommended Standard for SCPS
4486 * Transport Protocol (SCPS-TP)" Section 3.5 for definition of the SNACK option
4487 */
4488static void
4489dissect_tcpopt_snack(const ip_tcp_opt *optp _U___attribute__((unused)), tvbuff_t *tvb,
4490 int offset, guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo,
4491 proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
4492{
4493 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd=NULL((void*)0);
4494 guint16 relative_hole_offset;
4495 guint16 relative_hole_size;
4496 guint16 base_mss = 0;
4497 guint32 ack;
4498 guint32 hole_start;
4499 guint32 hole_end;
4500 char null_modifier[] = "\0";
4501 char relative_modifier[] = "(relative)";
4502 char *modifier = null_modifier;
4503 proto_item *hidden_item;
4504
4505 proto_tree_add_item(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb,
4506 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4507 proto_tree_add_item(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb,
4508 offset + 1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4509
4510 tcpd = get_tcp_conversation_data(NULL((void*)0),pinfo);
4511
4512 /* The SNACK option reports missing data with a granularity of segments. */
4513 relative_hole_offset = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + 2);
4514 relative_hole_size = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + 4);
4515
4516 hidden_item = proto_tree_add_boolean(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_snack, tvb,
4517 offset, optlen, TRUE(!(0)));
4518 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(hidden_item)do { if (hidden_item) do { if (((hidden_item)->finfo)) (((
hidden_item)->finfo))->flags = (((hidden_item)->finfo
))->flags | (0x00000001); } while(0); } while(0);
4519
4520 proto_tree_add_uint(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_snack_offset,
4521 tvb, offset, optlen, relative_hole_offset);
4522
4523 proto_tree_add_uint(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_snack_size,
4524 tvb, offset, optlen, relative_hole_size);
4525
4526 ack = tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, 8);
4527
4528 if (tcp_relative_seq) {
4529 ack -= tcpd->rev->base_seq;
4530 modifier = relative_modifier;
4531 }
4532
4533 /* To aid analysis, we can use a simple but generally effective heuristic
4534 * to report the most likely boundaries of the missing data. If the
4535 * flow is scps_capable, we track the maximum sized segment that was
4536 * acknowledged by the receiver and use that as the reporting granularity.
4537 * This may be different from the negotiated MTU due to PMTUD or flows
4538 * that do not send max-sized segments.
4539 */
4540 base_mss = tcpd->fwd->maxsizeacked;
4541
4542 if (base_mss) {
4543 /* Scale the reported offset and hole size by the largest segment acked */
4544 hole_start = ack + (base_mss * relative_hole_offset);
4545 hole_end = hole_start + (base_mss * relative_hole_size);
4546
4547 hidden_item = proto_tree_add_uint(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_snack_le,
4548 tvb, offset, optlen, hole_start);
4549 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(hidden_item)do { if (hidden_item) do { if (((hidden_item)->finfo)) (((
hidden_item)->finfo))->flags = (((hidden_item)->finfo
))->flags | (0x00000001); } while(0); } while(0);
4550
4551 hidden_item = proto_tree_add_uint(opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_snack_re,
4552 tvb, offset, optlen, hole_end);
4553 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(hidden_item)do { if (hidden_item) do { if (((hidden_item)->finfo)) (((
hidden_item)->finfo))->flags = (((hidden_item)->finfo
))->flags | (0x00000001); } while(0); } while(0);
4554
4555 proto_tree_add_expert_format(opt_tree, pinfo, &ei_tcp_option_snack_sequence, tvb, offset, optlen,
4556 "SNACK Sequence %u - %u %s", hole_start, hole_end, modifier);
4557
4558 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "SNLE", hole_start);
4559 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "SNRE", hole_end);
4560 }
4561}
4562
4563enum
4564{
4565 PROBE_VERSION_UNSPEC = 0,
4566 PROBE_VERSION_1 = 1,
4567 PROBE_VERSION_2 = 2,
4568 PROBE_VERSION_MAX
4569};
4570
4571/* Probe type definition. */
4572enum
4573{
4574 PROBE_QUERY = 0,
4575 PROBE_RESPONSE = 1,
4576 PROBE_INTERNAL = 2,
4577 PROBE_TRACE = 3,
4578 PROBE_QUERY_SH = 4,
4579 PROBE_RESPONSE_SH = 5,
4580 PROBE_QUERY_INFO = 6,
4581 PROBE_RESPONSE_INFO = 7,
4582 PROBE_QUERY_INFO_SH = 8,
4583 PROBE_QUERY_INFO_SID = 9,
4584 PROBE_RST = 10,
4585 PROBE_TYPE_MAX
4586};
4587
4588static const value_string rvbd_probe_type_vs[] = {
4589 { PROBE_QUERY, "Probe Query" },
4590 { PROBE_RESPONSE, "Probe Response" },
4591 { PROBE_INTERNAL, "Probe Internal" },
4592 { PROBE_TRACE, "Probe Trace" },
4593 { PROBE_QUERY_SH, "Probe Query SH" },
4594 { PROBE_RESPONSE_SH, "Probe Response SH" },
4595 { PROBE_QUERY_INFO, "Probe Query Info" },
4596 { PROBE_RESPONSE_INFO, "Probe Response Info" },
4597 { PROBE_QUERY_INFO_SH, "Probe Query Info SH" },
4598 { PROBE_QUERY_INFO_SID, "Probe Query Info Store ID" },
4599 { PROBE_RST, "Probe Reset" },
4600 { 0, NULL((void*)0) }
4601};
4602
4603
4604#define PROBE_OPTLEN_OFFSET1 1
4605
4606#define PROBE_VERSION_TYPE_OFFSET2 2
4607#define PROBE_V1_RESERVED_OFFSET3 3
4608#define PROBE_V1_PROBER_OFFSET4 4
4609#define PROBE_V1_APPLI_VERSION_OFFSET8 8
4610#define PROBE_V1_PROXY_ADDR_OFFSET8 8
4611#define PROBE_V1_PROXY_PORT_OFFSET12 12
4612#define PROBE_V1_SH_CLIENT_ADDR_OFFSET8 8
4613#define PROBE_V1_SH_PROXY_ADDR_OFFSET12 12
4614#define PROBE_V1_SH_PROXY_PORT_OFFSET16 16
4615
4616#define PROBE_V2_INFO_OFFSET3 3
4617
4618#define PROBE_V2_INFO_CLIENT_ADDR_OFFSET4 4
4619#define PROBE_V2_INFO_STOREID_OFFSET4 4
4620
4621#define PROBE_VERSION_MASK0x01 0x01
4622
4623/* Probe Query Extra Info flags */
4624#define RVBD_FLAGS_PROBE_LAST0x01 0x01
4625#define RVBD_FLAGS_PROBE_NCFE0x04 0x04
4626
4627/* Probe Response Extra Info flags */
4628#define RVBD_FLAGS_PROBE_SERVER0x01 0x01
4629#define RVBD_FLAGS_PROBE_SSLCERT0x02 0x02
4630#define RVBD_FLAGS_PROBE0x10 0x10
4631
4632static void
4633rvbd_probe_decode_version_type(const guint8 vt, guint8 *ver, guint8 *type)
4634{
4635 if (vt & PROBE_VERSION_MASK0x01) {
4636 *ver = PROBE_VERSION_1;
4637 *type = vt >> 4;
4638 } else {
4639 *ver = PROBE_VERSION_2;
4640 *type = vt >> 1;
4641 }
4642}
