4644static void
4645rvbd_probe_resp_add_info(proto_item *pitem, packet_info *pinfo, tvbuff_t *tvb, int ip_offset, guint16 port)
4646{
4647 proto_item_append_text(pitem, ", Server Steelhead: %s:%u", tvb_ip_to_str(tvb, ip_offset)tvb_address_to_str(wmem_packet_scope(), tvb, AT_IPv4, ip_offset
), port);
4648
4649 col_prepend_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "SA+, ");
4650}
4651
4652static void
4653dissect_tcpopt_rvbd_probe(const ip_tcp_opt *optp _U___attribute__((unused)), tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset,
4654 guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo, proto_tree *opt_tree,
4655 void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
4656{
4657 guint8 ver, type;
4658 proto_tree *field_tree;
4659 proto_item *pitem;
4660
4661 rvbd_probe_decode_version_type(
4662 tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset + PROBE_VERSION_TYPE_OFFSET2),
4663 &ver, &type);
4664
4665 pitem = proto_tree_add_boolean_format_value(
4666 opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe, tvb, offset, optlen, 1,
4667 "%s", val_to_str_const(type, rvbd_probe_type_vs, "Probe Unknown"));
4668
4669 if (type >= PROBE_TYPE_MAX)
4670 return;
4671
4672 /* optlen, type, ver are common for all probes */
4673 field_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(pitem, ett_tcp_opt_rvbd_probe);
4674 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb,
4675 offset + PROBE_OPTLEN_OFFSET1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4676 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb,
4677 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4678 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_optlen, tvb,
4679 offset + PROBE_OPTLEN_OFFSET1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4680
4681 if (ver == PROBE_VERSION_1) {
4682 guint16 port;
4683
4684 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_type1, tvb,
4685 offset + PROBE_VERSION_TYPE_OFFSET2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4686 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_version1, tvb,
4687 offset + PROBE_VERSION_TYPE_OFFSET2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4688
4689 if (type == PROBE_INTERNAL)
4690 return;
4691
4692 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_reserved, tvb, offset + PROBE_V1_RESERVED_OFFSET3, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4693
4694 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_prober, tvb,
4695 offset + PROBE_V1_PROBER_OFFSET4, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4696
4697 switch (type) {
4698
4699 case PROBE_QUERY:
4700 case PROBE_QUERY_SH:
4701 case PROBE_TRACE:
4702 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_appli_ver, tvb,
4703 offset + PROBE_V1_APPLI_VERSION_OFFSET8, 2,
4704 ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4705
4706 proto_item_append_text(pitem, ", CSH IP: %s", tvb_ip_to_str(tvb, offset + PROBE_V1_PROBER_OFFSET)tvb_address_to_str(wmem_packet_scope(), tvb, AT_IPv4, offset +
4));
4707
4708 {
4709 /* Small look-ahead hack to distinguish S+ from S+* */
4710#define PROBE_V1_QUERY_LEN10 10
4711 const guint8 qinfo_hdr[] = { 0x4c, 0x04, 0x0c };
4712 int not_cfe = 0;
4713 /* tvb_memeql seems to be the only API that doesn't throw
4714 an exception in case of an error */
4715 if (tvb_memeql(tvb, offset + PROBE_V1_QUERY_LEN10,
4716 qinfo_hdr, sizeof(qinfo_hdr)) == 0) {
4717 not_cfe = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset + PROBE_V1_QUERY_LEN10 +
4718 (int)sizeof(qinfo_hdr)) & RVBD_FLAGS_PROBE_NCFE0x04;
4719 }
4720 col_prepend_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "S%s, ",
4721 type == PROBE_TRACE ? "#" :
4722 not_cfe ? "+*" : "+");
4723 }
4724 break;
4725
4726 case PROBE_RESPONSE:
4727 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_proxy, tvb,
4728 offset + PROBE_V1_PROXY_ADDR_OFFSET8, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4729
4730 port = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + PROBE_V1_PROXY_PORT_OFFSET12);
4731 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_proxy_port, tvb,
4732 offset + PROBE_V1_PROXY_PORT_OFFSET12, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4733
4734 rvbd_probe_resp_add_info(pitem, pinfo, tvb, offset + PROBE_V1_PROXY_ADDR_OFFSET8, port);
4735 break;
4736
4737 case PROBE_RESPONSE_SH:
4738 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree,
4739 hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_client, tvb,
4740 offset + PROBE_V1_SH_CLIENT_ADDR_OFFSET8, 4,
4741 ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4742
4743 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_proxy, tvb,
4744 offset + PROBE_V1_SH_PROXY_ADDR_OFFSET12, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4745
4746 port = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + PROBE_V1_SH_PROXY_PORT_OFFSET16);
4747 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_proxy_port, tvb,
4748 offset + PROBE_V1_SH_PROXY_PORT_OFFSET16, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4749
4750 rvbd_probe_resp_add_info(pitem, pinfo, tvb, offset + PROBE_V1_SH_PROXY_ADDR_OFFSET12, port);
4751 break;
4752 }
4753 }
4754 else if (ver == PROBE_VERSION_2) {
4755 proto_item *ver_pi;
4756 proto_item *flag_pi;
4757 proto_tree *flag_tree;
4758 guint8 flags;
4759
4760 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_type2, tvb,
4761 offset + PROBE_VERSION_TYPE_OFFSET2, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4762
4763 proto_tree_add_uint_format_value(
4764 field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_version2, tvb,
4765 offset + PROBE_VERSION_TYPE_OFFSET2, 1, ver, "%u", ver);
4766 /* Use version1 for filtering purposes because version2 packet
4767 value is 0, but filtering is usually done for value 2 */
4768 ver_pi = proto_tree_add_uint(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_version1, tvb,
4769 offset + PROBE_VERSION_TYPE_OFFSET2, 1, ver);
4770 PROTO_ITEM_SET_HIDDEN(ver_pi)do { if (ver_pi) do { if (((ver_pi)->finfo)) (((ver_pi)->
finfo))->flags = (((ver_pi)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000001
); } while(0); } while(0);
4771
4772 switch (type) {
4773
4774 case PROBE_QUERY_INFO:
4775 case PROBE_QUERY_INFO_SH:
4776 case PROBE_QUERY_INFO_SID:
4777 flags = tvb_get_guint8(tvb, offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_OFFSET3);
4778 flag_pi = proto_tree_add_uint(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_flags,
4779 tvb, offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_OFFSET3,
4780 1, flags);
4781
4782 flag_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(flag_pi, ett_tcp_opt_rvbd_probe_flags);
4783 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree,
4784 hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_flag_not_cfe,
4785 tvb, offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_OFFSET3, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4786 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree,
4787 hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_flag_last_notify,
4788 tvb, offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_OFFSET3, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4789
4790 if (type == PROBE_QUERY_INFO_SH)
4791 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree,
4792 hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_client, tvb,
4793 offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_CLIENT_ADDR_OFFSET4,
4794 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4795 else if (type == PROBE_QUERY_INFO_SID)
4796 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree,
4797 hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_storeid, tvb,
4798 offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_STOREID_OFFSET4,
4799 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4800
4801 if (type != PROBE_QUERY_INFO_SID &&
4802 (tvb_get_guint8(tvb, 13) & (TH_SYN0x0002|TH_ACK0x0010)) == (TH_SYN0x0002|TH_ACK0x0010) &&
4803 (flags & RVBD_FLAGS_PROBE_LAST0x01)) {
4804 col_prepend_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "SA++, ");
4805 }
4806
4807 break;
4808
4809 case PROBE_RESPONSE_INFO:
4810 flag_pi = proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_flags,
4811 tvb, offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_OFFSET3,
4812 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4813
4814 flag_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(flag_pi, ett_tcp_opt_rvbd_probe_flags);
4815 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree,
4816 hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_flag_probe_cache,
4817 tvb, offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_OFFSET3, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4818 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree,
4819 hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_flag_sslcert,
4820 tvb, offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_OFFSET3, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4821 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree,
4822 hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_flag_server_connected,
4823 tvb, offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_OFFSET3, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4824 break;
4825
4826 case PROBE_RST:
4827 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_flags,
4828 tvb, offset + PROBE_V2_INFO_OFFSET3,
4829 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4830 break;
4831 }
4832 }
4833}
4834
4835enum {
4836 TRPY_OPTNUM_OFFSET = 0,
4837 TRPY_OPTLEN_OFFSET = 1,
4838
4839 TRPY_OPTIONS_OFFSET = 2,
4840 TRPY_SRC_ADDR_OFFSET = 4,
4841 TRPY_DST_ADDR_OFFSET = 8,
4842 TRPY_SRC_PORT_OFFSET = 12,
4843 TRPY_DST_PORT_OFFSET = 14,
4844 TRPY_CLIENT_PORT_OFFSET = 16
4845};

4847/* Trpy Flags */
4848#define RVBD_FLAGS_TRPY_MODE0x0001 0x0001
4849#define RVBD_FLAGS_TRPY_OOB0x0002 0x0002
4850#define RVBD_FLAGS_TRPY_CHKSUM0x0004 0x0004
4851#define RVBD_FLAGS_TRPY_FW_RST0x0100 0x0100
4852#define RVBD_FLAGS_TRPY_FW_RST_INNER0x0200 0x0200
4853#define RVBD_FLAGS_TRPY_FW_RST_PROBE0x0400 0x0400
4854
4855static const true_false_string trpy_mode_str = {
4856 "Port Transparency",
4857 "Full Transparency"
4858};
4859
4860static void
4861dissect_tcpopt_rvbd_trpy(const ip_tcp_opt *optp _U___attribute__((unused)), tvbuff_t *tvb,
4862 int offset, guint optlen, packet_info *pinfo,
4863 proto_tree *opt_tree, void *data _U___attribute__((unused)))
4864{
4865 proto_tree *field_tree;
4866 proto_tree *flag_tree;
4867 proto_item *pitem;
4868 proto_item *flag_pi;
4869 guint16 sport, dport, flags;
4870
4871 col_prepend_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, "TRPY, ");
4872
4873 pitem = proto_tree_add_boolean_format_value(
4874 opt_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy, tvb, offset, optlen, 1,
4875 "%s", "");
4876
4877 field_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(pitem, ett_tcp_opt_rvbd_trpy);
4878 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_len, tvb,
4879 offset + PROBE_OPTLEN_OFFSET1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4880 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_kind, tvb,
4881 offset, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4882 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_probe_optlen, tvb,
4883 offset + PROBE_OPTLEN_OFFSET1, 1, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4884
4885 flags = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + TRPY_OPTIONS_OFFSET);
4886 flag_pi = proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_flags,
4887 tvb, offset + TRPY_OPTIONS_OFFSET,
4888 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4889
4890 flag_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(flag_pi, ett_tcp_opt_rvbd_trpy_flags);
4891 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_flag_fw_rst_probe,
4892 tvb, offset + TRPY_OPTIONS_OFFSET, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4893 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_flag_fw_rst_inner,
4894 tvb, offset + TRPY_OPTIONS_OFFSET, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4895 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_flag_fw_rst,
4896 tvb, offset + TRPY_OPTIONS_OFFSET, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4897 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_flag_chksum,
4898 tvb, offset + TRPY_OPTIONS_OFFSET, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4899 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_flag_oob,
4900 tvb, offset + TRPY_OPTIONS_OFFSET, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4901 proto_tree_add_item(flag_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_flag_mode,
4902 tvb, offset + TRPY_OPTIONS_OFFSET, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4903
4904 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_src,
4905 tvb, offset + TRPY_SRC_ADDR_OFFSET, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4906
4907 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_dst,
4908 tvb, offset + TRPY_DST_ADDR_OFFSET, 4, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4909
4910 sport = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + TRPY_SRC_PORT_OFFSET);
4911 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_src_port,
4912 tvb, offset + TRPY_SRC_PORT_OFFSET, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4913
4914 dport = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + TRPY_DST_PORT_OFFSET);
4915 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_dst_port,
4916 tvb, offset + TRPY_DST_PORT_OFFSET, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4917
4918 proto_item_append_text(pitem, "%s:%u -> %s:%u",
4919 tvb_ip_to_str(tvb, offset + TRPY_SRC_ADDR_OFFSET)tvb_address_to_str(wmem_packet_scope(), tvb, AT_IPv4, offset +
TRPY_SRC_ADDR_OFFSET), sport,
4920 tvb_ip_to_str(tvb, offset + TRPY_DST_ADDR_OFFSET)tvb_address_to_str(wmem_packet_scope(), tvb, AT_IPv4, offset +
TRPY_DST_ADDR_OFFSET), dport);
4921
4922 /* Client port only set on SYN: optlen == 18 */
4923 if ((flags & RVBD_FLAGS_TRPY_OOB0x0002) && (optlen > TCPOLEN_RVBD_TRPY_MIN16))
4924 proto_tree_add_item(field_tree, hf_tcp_option_rvbd_trpy_client_port,
4925 tvb, offset + TRPY_CLIENT_PORT_OFFSET, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000);
4926
4927 /* Despite that we have the right TCP ports for other protocols,
4928 * the data is related to the Riverbed Optimization Protocol and
4929 * not understandable by normal protocol dissectors. If the sport
4930 * protocol is available then use that, otherwise just output it
4931 * as a hex-dump.
4932 */
4933 if (sport_handle != NULL((void*)0)) {
4934 conversation_t *conversation;
4935 conversation = find_conversation(pinfo->num,
4936 &pinfo->src, &pinfo->dst, pinfo->ptype,
4937 pinfo->srcport, pinfo->destport, 0);
4938 if (conversation == NULL((void*)0)) {
4939 conversation = conversation_new(pinfo->num,
4940 &pinfo->src, &pinfo->dst, pinfo->ptype,
4941 pinfo->srcport, pinfo->destport, 0);
4942 }
4943 if (conversation_get_dissector(conversation, pinfo->num) != sport_handle) {
4944 conversation_set_dissector(conversation, sport_handle);
4945 }
4946 } else if (data_handle != NULL((void*)0)) {
4947 conversation_t *conversation;
4948 conversation = find_conversation(pinfo->num,
4949 &pinfo->src, &pinfo->dst, pinfo->ptype,
4950 pinfo->srcport, pinfo->destport, 0);
4951 if (conversation == NULL((void*)0)) {
4952 conversation = conversation_new(pinfo->num,
4953 &pinfo->src, &pinfo->dst, pinfo->ptype,
4954 pinfo->srcport, pinfo->destport, 0);
4955 }
4956 if (conversation_get_dissector(conversation, pinfo->num) != data_handle) {
4957 conversation_set_dissector(conversation, data_handle);
4958 }
4959 }
4960}

5165#define N_TCP_OPTS(sizeof tcpopts / sizeof tcpopts[0]) array_length(tcpopts)(sizeof tcpopts / sizeof tcpopts[0])

5167static ip_tcp_opt_type TCP_OPT_TYPES = {&hf_tcp_option_type, &ett_tcp_option_type,
5168 &hf_tcp_option_type_copy, &hf_tcp_option_type_class, &hf_tcp_option_type_number};
5169
5170/* Determine if there is a sub-dissector and call it; return TRUE
5171 if there was a sub-dissector, FALSE otherwise.
5172
5173 This has been separated into a stand alone routine to other protocol
5174 dissectors can call to it, e.g., SOCKS. */
5175
5176static gboolean try_heuristic_first = FALSE(0);
5177
5178
5179/* this function can be called with tcpd==NULL as from the msproxy dissector */
5180gboolean
5181decode_tcp_ports(tvbuff_t *tvb, int offset, packet_info *pinfo,
5182 proto_tree *tree, int src_port, int dst_port,
5183 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd, struct tcpinfo *tcpinfo)
5184{
5185 tvbuff_t *next_tvb;
5186 int low_port, high_port;
5187 int save_desegment_offset;
5188 guint32 save_desegment_len;
5189 heur_dtbl_entry_t *hdtbl_entry;
5190
5191 /* Don't call subdissectors for keepalives. Even though they do contain
5192 * payload "data", it's just garbage. Display any data the keepalive
5193 * packet might contain though.
5194 */
5195 if(tcpd && tcpd->ta) {
5196 if(tcpd->ta->flags&TCP_A_KEEP_ALIVE0x0008) {
5197 next_tvb = tvb_new_subset_remaining(tvb, offset);
5198 call_dissector(data_handle, next_tvb, pinfo, tree);
5199 return TRUE(!(0));
5200 }
5201 }
5202
5203 if (tcp_no_subdissector_on_error && tcpd && tcpd->ta && tcpd->ta->flags & (TCP_A_RETRANSMISSION0x0001 | TCP_A_OUT_OF_ORDER0x0200)) {
5204 /* Don't try to dissect a retransmission high chance that it will mess
5205 * subdissectors for protocols that require in-order delivery of the
5206 * PDUs. (i.e. DCE/RPCoverHTTP and encryption)
5207 */
5208 return FALSE(0);
5209 }
5210 next_tvb = tvb_new_subset_remaining(tvb, offset);
5211
5212 save_desegment_offset = pinfo->desegment_offset;
5213 save_desegment_len = pinfo->desegment_len;
5214
5215/* determine if this packet is part of a conversation and call dissector */
5216/* for the conversation if available */
5217
5218 if (try_conversation_dissector(&pinfo->src, &pinfo->dst, PT_TCP,
5219 src_port, dst_port, next_tvb, pinfo, tree, tcpinfo)) {
5220 pinfo->want_pdu_tracking -= !!(pinfo->want_pdu_tracking);
5221 return TRUE(!(0));
5222 }
5223
5224 if (try_heuristic_first) {
5225 /* do lookup with the heuristic subdissector table */
5226 if (dissector_try_heuristic(heur_subdissector_list, next_tvb, pinfo, tree, &hdtbl_entry, tcpinfo)) {
5227 pinfo->want_pdu_tracking -= !!(pinfo->want_pdu_tracking);
5228 return TRUE(!(0));
5229 }
5230 }
5231
5232 /* Do lookups with the subdissector table.
5233 Try the server port captured on the SYN or SYN|ACK packet. After that
5234 try the port number with the lower value first, followed by the
5235 port number with the higher value. This means that, for packets
5236 where a dissector is registered for *both* port numbers:
5237
5238 1) we pick the same dissector for traffic going in both directions;
5239
5240 2) we prefer the port number that's more likely to be the right
5241 one (as that prefers well-known ports to reserved ports);
5242
5243 although there is, of course, no guarantee that any such strategy
5244 will always pick the right port number.
5245
5246 XXX - we ignore port numbers of 0, as some dissectors use a port
5247 number of 0 to disable the port. */
5248
5249 if (tcpd && tcpd->server_port != 0 &&
5250 dissector_try_uint_new(subdissector_table, tcpd->server_port, next_tvb, pinfo, tree, TRUE(!(0)), tcpinfo)) {
5251 pinfo->want_pdu_tracking -= !!(pinfo->want_pdu_tracking);
5252 return TRUE(!(0));
5253 }
5254
5255 if (src_port > dst_port) {
5256 low_port = dst_port;
5257 high_port = src_port;
5258 } else {
5259 low_port = src_port;
5260 high_port = dst_port;
5261 }
5262
5263 if (low_port != 0 &&
5264 dissector_try_uint_new(subdissector_table, low_port, next_tvb, pinfo, tree, TRUE(!(0)), tcpinfo)) {
5265 pinfo->want_pdu_tracking -= !!(pinfo->want_pdu_tracking);
5266 return TRUE(!(0));
5267 }
5268 if (high_port != 0 &&
5269 dissector_try_uint_new(subdissector_table, high_port, next_tvb, pinfo, tree, TRUE(!(0)), tcpinfo)) {
5270 pinfo->want_pdu_tracking -= !!(pinfo->want_pdu_tracking);
5271 return TRUE(!(0));
5272 }
5273
5274 if (!try_heuristic_first) {
5275 /* do lookup with the heuristic subdissector table */
5276 if (dissector_try_heuristic(heur_subdissector_list, next_tvb, pinfo, tree, &hdtbl_entry, tcpinfo)) {
5277 pinfo->want_pdu_tracking -= !!(pinfo->want_pdu_tracking);
5278 return TRUE(!(0));
5279 }
5280 }
5281
5282 /*
5283 * heuristic / conversation / port registered dissectors rejected the packet;
5284 * make sure they didn't also request desegmentation (we could just override
5285 * the request, but rejecting a packet *and* requesting desegmentation is a sign
5286 * of the dissector's code needing clearer thought, so we fail so that the
5287 * problem is made more obvious).
5288 */
5289 DISSECTOR_ASSERT(save_desegment_offset == pinfo->desegment_offset &&((void) ((save_desegment_offset == pinfo->desegment_offset
&& save_desegment_len == pinfo->desegment_len) ? (
void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\"", "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 5290, "save_desegment_offset == pinfo->desegment_offset && save_desegment_len == pinfo->desegment_len"
)))))
5290 save_desegment_len == pinfo->desegment_len)((void) ((save_desegment_offset == pinfo->desegment_offset
&& save_desegment_len == pinfo->desegment_len) ? (
void)0 : (proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"%s\"", "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 5290, "save_desegment_offset == pinfo->desegment_offset && save_desegment_len == pinfo->desegment_len"
)))));
5291
5292 /* Oh, well, we don't know this; dissect it as data. */
5293 call_dissector(data_handle,next_tvb, pinfo, tree);
5294
5295 pinfo->want_pdu_tracking -= !!(pinfo->want_pdu_tracking);
5296 return FALSE(0);
5297}
5298
5299static void
5300process_tcp_payload(tvbuff_t *tvb, volatile int offset, packet_info *pinfo,
5301 proto_tree *tree, proto_tree *tcp_tree, int src_port, int dst_port,
5302 guint32 seq, guint32 nxtseq, gboolean is_tcp_segment,
5303 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd, struct tcpinfo *tcpinfo)
5304{
5305 pinfo->want_pdu_tracking=0;
5306
5307 TRY{ except_t *volatile exc; volatile int except_state = 0; static
const except_id_t catch_spec[] = { { 1, 0 } }; { struct except_stacknode
except_sn; struct except_catch except_ch; except_setup_try(&
except_sn, &except_ch, catch_spec, 1); if (_setjmp (except_ch
.except_jmp)) *(&exc) = &except_ch.except_obj; else *
(&exc) = 0; if(except_state & 1) except_state |= 2; except_state
&= ~1; if (except_state == 0 && exc == 0) {
5308 if(is_tcp_segment) {
5309 /*qqq see if it is an unaligned PDU */
5310 if(tcpd && tcp_analyze_seq && (!tcp_desegment)) {
5311 if(seq || nxtseq) {
5312 offset=scan_for_next_pdu(tvb, tcp_tree, pinfo, offset,
5313 seq, nxtseq, tcpd->fwd->multisegment_pdus);
5314 }
5315 }
5316 }
5317 /* if offset is -1 this means that this segment is known
5318 * to be fully inside a previously detected pdu
5319 * so we don't even need to try to dissect it either.
5320 */
5321 if( (offset!=-1) &&
5322 decode_tcp_ports(tvb, offset, pinfo, tree, src_port,
5323 dst_port, tcpd, tcpinfo) ) {
5324 /*
5325 * We succeeded in handing off to a subdissector.
5326 *
5327 * Is this a TCP segment or a reassembled chunk of
5328 * TCP payload?
5329 */
5330 if(is_tcp_segment) {
5331 /* if !visited, check want_pdu_tracking and
5332 store it in table */
5333 if(tcpd && (!pinfo->fd->flags.visited) &&
5334 tcp_analyze_seq && pinfo->want_pdu_tracking) {
5335 if(seq || nxtseq) {
5336 pdu_store_sequencenumber_of_next_pdu(
5337 pinfo,
5338 seq,
5339 nxtseq+pinfo->bytes_until_next_pdu,
5340 tcpd->fwd->multisegment_pdus);
5341 }
5342 }
5343 }
5344 }
5345 }
5346 CATCH_ALLif (except_state == 0 && exc != 0 && (except_state
|=1)) {
5347 /* We got an exception. At this point the dissection is
5348 * completely aborted and execution will be transferred back
5349 * to (probably) the frame dissector.
5350 * Here we have to place whatever we want the dissector
5351 * to do before aborting the tcp dissection.
5352 */
5353 /*
5354 * Is this a TCP segment or a reassembled chunk of TCP
5355 * payload?
5356 */
5357 if(is_tcp_segment) {
5358 /*
5359 * It's from a TCP segment.
5360 *
5361 * if !visited, check want_pdu_tracking and store it
5362 * in table
5363 */
5364 if(tcpd && (!pinfo->fd->flags.visited) && tcp_analyze_seq && pinfo->want_pdu_tracking) {
5365 if(seq || nxtseq) {
5366 pdu_store_sequencenumber_of_next_pdu(pinfo,
5367 seq,
5368 nxtseq+pinfo->bytes_until_next_pdu,
5369 tcpd->fwd->multisegment_pdus);
5370 }
5371 }
5372 }
5373 RETHROW{ do { if (__builtin_expect (__extension__ ({ int _g_boolean_var_
; if (except_state == 1) _g_boolean_var_ = 1; else _g_boolean_var_
= 0; _g_boolean_var_; }), 1)) ; else g_assertion_message_expr
(((gchar*) 0), "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"
, 5373, ((const char*) (__func__)), "except_state == EXCEPT_CAUGHT"
); } while (0); longjmp(except_ch.except_jmp,1); };
5374 }
5375 ENDTRYif(!(except_state&1) && exc != 0) except_rethrow(
exc); except_free(except_ch.except_obj.except_dyndata); except_pop
(); };};
5376}
5377
5378void
5379dissect_tcp_payload(tvbuff_t *tvb, packet_info *pinfo, int offset, guint32 seq,
5380 guint32 nxtseq, guint32 sport, guint32 dport,
5381 proto_tree *tree, proto_tree *tcp_tree,
5382 struct tcp_analysis *tcpd, struct tcpinfo *tcpinfo)
5383{
5384 gboolean save_fragmented;
5385
5386 /* Can we desegment this segment? */
5387 if (pinfo->can_desegment) {
5388 /* Yes. */
5389 desegment_tcp(tvb, pinfo, offset, seq, nxtseq, sport, dport, tree,
5390 tcp_tree, tcpd, tcpinfo);
5391 } else {
5392 /* No - just call the subdissector.
5393 Mark this as fragmented, so if somebody throws an exception,
5394 we don't report it as a malformed frame. */
5395 save_fragmented = pinfo->fragmented;
5396 pinfo->fragmented = TRUE(!(0));
5397
5398 process_tcp_payload(tvb, offset, pinfo, tree, tcp_tree, sport, dport,
5399 seq, nxtseq, TRUE(!(0)), tcpd, tcpinfo);
5400 pinfo->fragmented = save_fragmented;
5401 }
5402}
5403
5404static const char *
5405tcp_flags_to_str(const struct tcpheader *tcph)
5406{
5407 static const char flags[][4] = { "FIN", "SYN", "RST", "PSH", "ACK", "URG", "ECN", "CWR", "NS" };
5408 const int maxlength = 64; /* upper bounds, max 53B: 8 * 3 + 2 + strlen("Reserved") + 9 * 2 + 1 */
5409
5410 char *pbuf;
5411 const char *buf;
5412
5413 int i;
5414
5415 buf = pbuf = (char *) wmem_alloc(wmem_packet_scope(), maxlength);
5416 *pbuf = '\0';
5417
5418 for (i = 0; i < 9; i++) {
5419 if (tcph->th_flags & (1 << i)) {
5420 if (buf[0])
5421 pbuf = g_stpcpy(pbuf, ", ");
5422 pbuf = g_stpcpy(pbuf, flags[i]);
5423 }
5424 }
5425
5426 if (tcph->th_flags & TH_RES0x0E00) {
5427 if (buf[0])
5428 pbuf = g_stpcpy(pbuf, ", ");
5429 g_stpcpy(pbuf, "Reserved");
5430 }
5431
5432 if (buf[0] == '\0')
5433 buf = "<None>";
5434
5435 return buf;
5436}
5437static const char *
5438tcp_flags_to_str_first_letter(const struct tcpheader *tcph)
5439{
5440 wmem_strbuf_t *buf = wmem_strbuf_new(wmem_packet_scope(), "");
5441 unsigned i;
5442 const unsigned flags_count = 12;
5443 const char first_letters[] = "RRRNCEUAPRSF";
5444
5445 /* upper three bytes are marked as reserved ('R'). */
5446 for (i = 0; i < flags_count; i++) {
5447 if (((tcph->th_flags >> (flags_count - 1 - i)) & 1)) {
5448 wmem_strbuf_append_c(buf, first_letters[i]);
5449 } else {
5450 wmem_strbuf_append(buf, UTF8_MIDDLE_DOT"\xc2\xb7");
5451 }
5452 }
5453
5454 return wmem_strbuf_finalize(buf);
5455}

5457static gboolean
5458capture_tcp(const guchar *pd, int offset, int len, capture_packet_info_t *cpinfo, const union wtap_pseudo_header *pseudo_header)
5459{
5460 guint16 src_port, dst_port, low_port, high_port;
5461
5462 if (!BYTES_ARE_IN_FRAME(offset, len, 4)((guint)(offset) + (guint)(4) > (guint)(offset) &&
(guint)(offset) + (guint)(4) <= (guint)(len)))
5463 return FALSE(0);
5464
5465 capture_dissector_increment_count(cpinfo, proto_tcp);
5466
5467 src_port = pntoh16(&pd[offset])((guint16) ((guint16)*((const guint8 *)(&pd[offset])+0)<<
8| (guint16)*((const guint8 *)(&pd[offset])+1)<<0));
5468 dst_port = pntoh16(&pd[offset+2])((guint16) ((guint16)*((const guint8 *)(&pd[offset+2])+0)
<<8| (guint16)*((const guint8 *)(&pd[offset+2])+1)<<
0));
5469
5470 if (src_port > dst_port) {
5471 low_port = dst_port;
5472 high_port = src_port;
5473 } else {
5474 low_port = src_port;
5475 high_port = dst_port;
5476 }
5477

5484 return TRUE(!(0));

5487 return TRUE(!(0));

5611 * mission later.

5634 * mission later.

5685 * ICMP and ICMPv6 dissectors could set a "this is how big the IP

5691 *
5692 * We also can't determine the segment length if the reported length
5693 * of the TCP packet is less than the TCP header length.
5694 */
5695 reported_len = tvb_reported_length(tvb);
5696
5697 if (!pinfo->fragmented && !pinfo->flags.in_error_pkt) {
5698 if (reported_len < tcph->th_hlen) {
5699 proto_tree_add_expert_format(tcp_tree, pinfo, &ei_tcp_short_segment, tvb, offset, 0,
5700 "Short segment. Segment/fragment does not contain a full TCP header"
5701 " (might be NMAP or someone else deliberately sending unusual packets)");
5702 tcph->th_have_seglen = FALSE(0);
5703 } else {
5704 /* Compute the length of data in this segment. */
5705 tcph->th_seglen = reported_len - tcph->th_hlen;
5706 tcph->th_have_seglen = TRUE(!(0));
5707
5708 if (tree) {
5709 proto_item *pi;
5710
5711 pi = proto_tree_add_uint(ti, hf_tcp_len, tvb, offset+12, 1, tcph->th_seglen);
5712 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(pi)do { if (pi) do { if (((pi)->finfo)) (((pi)->finfo))->
flags = (((pi)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
5713
5714 }
5715
5716
5717 /* handle TCP seq# analysis parse all new segments we see */
5718 if(tcp_analyze_seq) {
5719 if(!(pinfo->fd->flags.visited)) {
5720 tcp_analyze_sequence_number(pinfo, tcph->th_seq, tcph->th_ack, tcph->th_seglen, tcph->th_flags, tcph->th_win, tcpd);
5721 }
5722 if(tcpd && tcp_relative_seq) {
5723 (tcph->th_seq) -= tcpd->fwd->base_seq;
5724 if (tcph->th_flags & TH_ACK0x0010) {
5725 (tcph->th_ack) -= tcpd->rev->base_seq;
5726 }
5727 }
5728 }
5729
5730 /* re-calculate window size, based on scaling factor */
5731 if (!(tcph->th_flags&TH_SYN0x0002)) { /* SYNs are never scaled */
5732 if (tcpd && (tcpd->fwd->win_scale>=0)) {
5733 (tcph->th_win)<<=tcpd->fwd->win_scale;
5734 }
5735 else {
5736 /* Don't have it stored, so use preference setting instead! */
5737 if (tcp_default_window_scaling>=0) {
5738 (tcph->th_win)<<=tcp_default_window_scaling;
5739 }
5740 }
5741 }
5742
5743 /* Compute the sequence number of next octet after this segment. */
5744 nxtseq = tcph->th_seq + tcph->th_seglen;
5745 if ((tcph->th_flags&(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_FIN0x0001)) && (tcph->th_seglen > 0)) {
5746 nxtseq += 1;
5747 }
5748 }
5749 } else
5750 tcph->th_have_seglen = FALSE(0);
5751
5752 flags_str = tcp_flags_to_str(tcph);
5753 flags_str_first_letter = tcp_flags_to_str_first_letter(tcph);
5754
5755 col_append_lstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO,
5756 " [", flags_str, "]",
5757 COL_ADD_LSTR_TERMINATOR(const char *) -1);
5758 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "Seq", tcph->th_seq);
5759 if (tcph->th_flags&TH_ACK0x0010)
5760 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "Ack", tcph->th_ack);
5761
5762 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "Win", tcph->th_win);
5763
5764 if (tree) {
5765 if (tcp_summary_in_tree) {
5766 proto_item_append_text(ti, ", Seq: %u", tcph->th_seq);
5767 }
5768 if(tcp_relative_seq) {
5769 proto_tree_add_uint_format_value(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_seq, tvb, offset + 4, 4, tcph->th_seq, "%u (relative sequence number)", tcph->th_seq);
5770 } else {
5771 proto_tree_add_uint(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_seq, tvb, offset + 4, 4, tcph->th_seq);
5772 }
5773 }
5774
5775 if (tcph->th_hlen < TCPH_MIN_LEN20) {
5776 /* Give up at this point; we put the source and destination port in
5777 the tree, before fetching the header length, so that they'll
5778 show up if this is in the failing packet in an ICMP error packet,
5779 but it's now time to give up if the header length is bogus. */
5780 col_append_fstr(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, ", bogus TCP header length (%u, must be at least %u)",
5781 tcph->th_hlen, TCPH_MIN_LEN20);
5782 if (tree) {
5783 proto_tree_add_uint_format_value(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_hdr_len, tvb, offset + 12, 1, tcph->th_hlen,
5784 "%u bytes (bogus, must be at least %u)", tcph->th_hlen,
5785 TCPH_MIN_LEN20);
5786 }
5787 return offset+12;
5788 }
5789
5790 if (tree) {
5791 if (tcp_summary_in_tree) {
5792 if(tcph->th_flags&TH_ACK0x0010) {
5793 proto_item_append_text(ti, ", Ack: %u", tcph->th_ack);
5794 }
5795 if (tcph->th_have_seglen)
5796 proto_item_append_text(ti, ", Len: %u", tcph->th_seglen);
5797 }
5798 proto_item_set_len(ti, tcph->th_hlen);
5799 if (tcph->th_have_seglen) {
5800 if (nxtseq != tcph->th_seq) {
5801 if(tcp_relative_seq) {
5802 tf=proto_tree_add_uint_format_value(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_nxtseq, tvb, offset, 0, nxtseq, "%u (relative sequence number)", nxtseq);
5803 } else {
5804 tf=proto_tree_add_uint(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_nxtseq, tvb, offset, 0, nxtseq);
5805 }
5806 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(tf)do { if (tf) do { if (((tf)->finfo)) (((tf)->finfo))->
flags = (((tf)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
5807 }
5808 }
5809 }
5810
5811 tf = proto_tree_add_uint(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_ack, tvb, offset + 8, 4, tcph->th_ack);
5812 if (tcph->th_flags & TH_ACK0x0010) {
5813 if (tcp_relative_seq) {
5814 proto_item_append_text(tf, " (relative ack number)");
5815 }
5816 } else {
5817 /* Note if the ACK field is non-zero */
5818 if (tvb_get_ntohl(tvb, offset+8) != 0) {

5823 if (tree) {
5824 proto_tree_add_uint_format_value(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_hdr_len, tvb, offset + 12, 1, tcph->th_hlen,
5825 "%u bytes", tcph->th_hlen);
5826 tf = proto_tree_add_uint_format(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_flags, tvb, offset + 12, 2,
5827 tcph->th_flags, "Flags: 0x%03x (%s)", tcph->th_flags, flags_str);

5830 proto_tree_add_boolean(field_tree, hf_tcp_flags_ns, tvb, offset + 12, 1, tcph->th_flags);
5831 proto_tree_add_boolean(field_tree, hf_tcp_flags_cwr, tvb, offset + 13, 1, tcph->th_flags);
5832 proto_tree_add_boolean(field_tree, hf_tcp_flags_ecn, tvb, offset + 13, 1, tcph->th_flags);
5833 proto_tree_add_boolean(field_tree, hf_tcp_flags_urg, tvb, offset + 13, 1, tcph->th_flags);
5834 proto_tree_add_boolean(field_tree, hf_tcp_flags_ack, tvb, offset + 13, 1, tcph->th_flags);
5835 proto_tree_add_boolean(field_tree, hf_tcp_flags_push, tvb, offset + 13, 1, tcph->th_flags);
5836 tf_rst = proto_tree_add_boolean(field_tree, hf_tcp_flags_reset, tvb, offset + 13, 1, tcph->th_flags);
5837 tf_syn = proto_tree_add_boolean(field_tree, hf_tcp_flags_syn, tvb, offset + 13, 1, tcph->th_flags);
5838 tf_fin = proto_tree_add_boolean(field_tree, hf_tcp_flags_fin, tvb, offset + 13, 1, tcph->th_flags);
5839
5840 tf = proto_tree_add_string(field_tree, hf_tcp_flags_str, tvb, offset + 12, 2, flags_str_first_letter);
5841 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(tf)do { if (tf) do { if (((tf)->finfo)) (((tf)->finfo))->
flags = (((tf)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
5842 /* As discussed in bug 5541, it is better to use two separate
5843 * fields for the real and calculated window size.
5844 */
5845 proto_tree_add_uint(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_window_size_value, tvb, offset + 14, 2, real_window);
5846 scaled_pi = proto_tree_add_uint(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_window_size, tvb, offset + 14, 2, tcph->th_win);
5847 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(scaled_pi)do { if (scaled_pi) do { if (((scaled_pi)->finfo)) (((scaled_pi
)->finfo))->flags = (((scaled_pi)->finfo))->flags
| (0x00000002); } while(0); } while(0);
5848
5849 if( !(tcph->th_flags&TH_SYN0x0002) && tcpd ) {
5850 switch (tcpd->fwd->win_scale) {
5851
5852 case -1:
5853 {
5854 gint16 win_scale = tcpd->fwd->win_scale;
5855 gboolean override_with_pref = FALSE(0);
5856

5858 if (tcp_default_window_scaling != WindowScaling_NotKnown) {

| (0x00000002); } while(0); } while(0);

5873 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(scaled_pi)do { if (scaled_pi) do { if (((scaled_pi)->finfo)) (((scaled_pi
)->finfo))->flags = (((scaled_pi)->finfo))->flags
| (0x00000002); } while(0); } while(0);
5874 break;
5875
5876 default:
5877 scaled_pi = proto_tree_add_int_format_value(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_window_size_scalefactor, tvb, offset + 14, 2, 1<<tcpd->fwd->win_scale, "%d", 1<<tcpd->fwd->win_scale);
5878 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(scaled_pi)do { if (scaled_pi) do { if (((scaled_pi)->finfo)) (((scaled_pi
)->finfo))->flags = (((scaled_pi)->finfo))->flags
| (0x00000002); } while(0); } while(0);

5880 }
5881 }
5882
5883 if(tcph->th_flags & TH_SYN0x0002) {
5884 if(tcph->th_flags & TH_ACK0x0010) {
5885 expert_add_info_format(pinfo, tf_syn, &ei_tcp_connection_sack,
5886 "Connection establish acknowledge (SYN+ACK): server port %u", tcph->th_sport);
5887 /* Save the server port to help determine dissector used */
5888 tcpd->server_port = tcph->th_sport;
5889 }
5890 else {
5891 expert_add_info_format(pinfo, tf_syn, &ei_tcp_connection_syn,
5892 "Connection establish request (SYN): server port %u", tcph->th_dport);
5893 /* Save the server port to help determine dissector used */
5894 tcpd->server_port = tcph->th_dport;
5895 tcpd->ts_mru_syn = pinfo->abs_ts;
5896 }
5897 }
5898 if(tcph->th_flags & TH_FIN0x0001) {
5899 /* XXX - find a way to know the server port and output only that one */
5900 expert_add_info(pinfo, tf_fin, &ei_tcp_connection_fin);
5901 }
5902 if(tcph->th_flags & TH_RST0x0004)
5903 /* XXX - find a way to know the server port and output only that one */
5904 expert_add_info(pinfo, tf_rst, &ei_tcp_connection_rst);
5905
5906 if(tcp_analyze_seq
5907 && (tcph->th_flags & (TH_SYN0x0002|TH_ACK0x0010)) == TH_ACK0x0010
5908 && !nstime_is_zero(&tcpd->ts_mru_syn)
5909 && nstime_is_zero(&tcpd->ts_first_rtt)) {
5910 /* If all of the following:
5911 * - we care (the pref is set)
5912 * - this is a pure ACK
5913 * - we have a timestamp for the most-recently-transmitted SYN
5914 * - we haven't seen a pure ACK yet (no ts_first_rtt stored)
5915 * then assume it's the last part of the handshake and store the initial
5916 * RTT time
5917 */
5918 nstime_delta(&(tcpd->ts_first_rtt), &(pinfo->abs_ts), &(tcpd->ts_mru_syn));
5919 }
5920
5921 /* Supply the sequence number of the first byte and of the first byte
5922 after the segment. */
5923 tcpinfo.seq = tcph->th_seq;
5924 tcpinfo.nxtseq = nxtseq;
5925 tcpinfo.lastackseq = tcph->th_ack;
5926
5927 /* Assume we'll pass un-reassembled data to subdissectors. */
5928 tcpinfo.is_reassembled = FALSE(0);
5929
5930 /*
5931 * Assume, initially, that we can't desegment.
5932 */
5933 pinfo->can_desegment = 0;
5934 th_sum = tvb_get_ntohs(tvb, offset + 16);
5935 if (!pinfo->fragmented && tvb_bytes_exist(tvb, 0, reported_len)) {
5936 /* The packet isn't part of an un-reassembled fragmented datagram
5937 and isn't truncated. This means we have all the data, and thus
5938 can checksum it and, unless it's being returned in an error
5939 packet, are willing to allow subdissectors to request reassembly
5940 on it. */
5941
5942 if (tcp_check_checksum) {
5943 /* We haven't turned checksum checking off; checksum it. */
5944
5945 /* Set up the fields of the pseudo-header. */
5946 SET_CKSUM_VEC_PTR(cksum_vec[0], (const guint8 *)pinfo->src.data, pinfo->src.len)do { cksum_vec[0].ptr = ((const guint8 *)pinfo->src.data);
cksum_vec[0].len = (pinfo->src.len); } while (0);
5947 SET_CKSUM_VEC_PTR(cksum_vec[1], (const guint8 *)pinfo->dst.data, pinfo->dst.len)do { cksum_vec[1].ptr = ((const guint8 *)pinfo->dst.data);
cksum_vec[1].len = (pinfo->dst.len); } while (0);
5948 switch (pinfo->src.type) {
5949
5950 case AT_IPv4:
5951 phdr[0] = g_htonl((IP_PROTO_TCP<<16) + reported_len)((((__extension__ ({ guint32 __v, __x = ((guint32) ((6<<
16) + reported_len)); if (__builtin_constant_p (__x)) __v = (
(guint32) ( (((guint32) (__x) & (guint32) 0x000000ffU) <<
24) | (((guint32) (__x) & (guint32) 0x0000ff00U) <<
8) | (((guint32) (__x) & (guint32) 0x00ff0000U) >>
8) | (((guint32) (__x) & (guint32) 0xff000000U) >>
24))); else __asm__ ("bswapl %0" : "=r" (__v) : "0" (__x)); __v
; })))));
5952 SET_CKSUM_VEC_PTR(cksum_vec[2], (const guint8 *)phdr, 4)do { cksum_vec[2].ptr = ((const guint8 *)phdr); cksum_vec[2].
len = (4); } while (0);
5953 break;
5954
5955 case AT_IPv6:
5956 phdr[0] = g_htonl(reported_len)((((__extension__ ({ guint32 __v, __x = ((guint32) (reported_len
)); if (__builtin_constant_p (__x)) __v = ((guint32) ( (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0x000000ffU) << 24) | (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0x0000ff00U) << 8) | (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0x00ff0000U) >> 8) | (((guint32
) (__x) & (guint32) 0xff000000U) >> 24))); else __asm__
("bswapl %0" : "=r" (__v) : "0" (__x)); __v; })))));
5957 phdr[1] = g_htonl(IP_PROTO_TCP)((((__extension__ ({ guint32 __v, __x = ((guint32) (6)); if (
__builtin_constant_p (__x)) __v = ((guint32) ( (((guint32) (__x
) & (guint32) 0x000000ffU) << 24) | (((guint32) (__x
) & (guint32) 0x0000ff00U) << 8) | (((guint32) (__x
) & (guint32) 0x00ff0000U) >> 8) | (((guint32) (__x
) & (guint32) 0xff000000U) >> 24))); else __asm__ (
"bswapl %0" : "=r" (__v) : "0" (__x)); __v; })))));
5958 SET_CKSUM_VEC_PTR(cksum_vec[2], (const guint8 *)phdr, 8)do { cksum_vec[2].ptr = ((const guint8 *)phdr); cksum_vec[2].
len = (8); } while (0);

5960
5961 default:
5962 /* TCP runs only atop IPv4 and IPv6.... */
5963 DISSECTOR_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED()(proto_report_dissector_bug(wmem_strdup_printf(wmem_packet_scope
(), "%s:%u: failed assertion \"DISSECTOR_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED\""
, "/home/remnux/Desktop/Thesis-Experiments/Third_Experiment/SAST_With_SRE/CVEs/CVE-2018-11360_Wireshark/Wireshark/epan/dissectors/packet-tcp.c"

5965 }
5966 SET_CKSUM_VEC_TVB(cksum_vec[3], tvb, offset, reported_len)do { cksum_vec[3].len = (reported_len); cksum_vec[3].ptr = tvb_get_ptr
((tvb), (offset), cksum_vec[3].len); } while (0);
5967 computed_cksum = in_cksum(cksum_vec, 4);
5968 if (computed_cksum == 0 && th_sum == 0xffff) {
5969 item = proto_tree_add_uint_format_value(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_checksum, tvb,
5970 offset + 16, 2, th_sum,
5971 "0x%04x [should be 0x0000 (see RFC 1624)]", th_sum);
5972
5973 checksum_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(item, ett_tcp_checksum);
5974 item = proto_tree_add_uint(checksum_tree, hf_tcp_checksum_calculated, tvb,
5975 offset + 16, 2, 0x0000);
5976 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(item)do { if (item) do { if (((item)->finfo)) (((item)->finfo

5977 /* XXX - What should this special status be? */

5983 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " [TCP CHECKSUM 0xFFFF]");

5985 /* Checksum is treated as valid on most systems, so we're willing to desegment it. */
5986 desegment_ok = TRUE(!(0));
5987 } else {
5988 proto_item* calc_item;
5989 item = proto_tree_add_checksum(tcp_tree, tvb, offset+16, hf_tcp_checksum, hf_tcp_checksum_status, &ei_tcp_checksum_bad, pinfo, computed_cksum,
5990 ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000, PROTO_CHECKSUM_VERIFY0x01|PROTO_CHECKSUM_IN_CKSUM0x04);
5991

5993 offset + 16, 2, in_cksum_shouldbe(th_sum, computed_cksum));
5994 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(calc_item)do { if (calc_item) do { if (((calc_item)->finfo)) (((calc_item
)->finfo))->flags = (((calc_item)->finfo))->flags
| (0x00000002); } while(0); } while(0);
5995
5996 /* Checksum is valid, so we're willing to desegment it. */
5997 if (computed_cksum == 0) {

5999 } else {
6000 proto_item_append_text(item, "(maybe caused by \"TCP checksum offload\"?)");
6001
6002 /* Checksum is invalid, so we're not willing to desegment it. */
6003 desegment_ok = FALSE(0);
6004 pinfo->noreassembly_reason = " [incorrect TCP checksum]";
6005 col_append_str(pinfo->cinfo, COL_INFO, " [TCP CHECKSUM INCORRECT]");
6006 }
6007 }
6008 } else {
6009 proto_tree_add_checksum(tcp_tree, tvb, offset+16, hf_tcp_checksum, hf_tcp_checksum_status, &ei_tcp_checksum_bad, pinfo, 0,
6010 ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000, PROTO_CHECKSUM_NO_FLAGS0x00);

6012 /* We didn't check the checksum, and don't care if it's valid,
6013 so we're willing to desegment it. */
6014 desegment_ok = TRUE(!(0));
6015 }
6016 } else {
6017 /* We don't have all the packet data, so we can't checksum it... */
6018 proto_tree_add_checksum(tcp_tree, tvb, offset+16, hf_tcp_checksum, hf_tcp_checksum_status, &ei_tcp_checksum_bad, pinfo, 0,
6019 ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000, PROTO_CHECKSUM_NO_FLAGS0x00);
6020
6021 /* ...and aren't willing to desegment it. */
6022 desegment_ok = FALSE(0);
6023 }
6024
6025 if (desegment_ok) {
6026 /* We're willing to desegment this. Is desegmentation enabled? */
6027 if (tcp_desegment) {
6028 /* Yes - is this segment being returned in an error packet? */
6029 if (!pinfo->flags.in_error_pkt) {
6030 /* No - indicate that we will desegment.
6031 We do NOT want to desegment segments returned in error
6032 packets, as they're not part of a TCP connection. */
6033 pinfo->can_desegment = 2;
6034 }
6035 }
6036 }
6037
6038 item = proto_tree_add_item_ret_uint(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_urgent_pointer, tvb, offset + 18, 2, ENC_BIG_ENDIAN0x00000000, &th_urp);
6039
6040 if (IS_TH_URG(tcph->th_flags)(tcph->th_flags & 0x0020)) {
6041 /* Export the urgent pointer, for the benefit of protocols such as
6042 rlogin. */
6043 tcpinfo.urgent_pointer = (guint16)th_urp;
6044 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "Urg", th_urp);
6045 } else {
6046 if (th_urp) {
6047 /* Note if the urgent pointer field is non-zero */
6048 expert_add_info(pinfo, item, &ei_tcp_urgent_pointer_non_zero);
6049 }
6050 }
6051
6052 if (tcph->th_have_seglen)
6053 tcp_info_append_uint(pinfo, "Len", tcph->th_seglen);
6054
6055 /* If there's more than just the fixed-length header (20 bytes), create
6056 a protocol tree item for the options. (We already know there's
6057 not less than the fixed-length header - we checked that above.)
6058
6059 We ensure that we don't throw an exception here, so that we can
6060 do some analysis before we dissect the options and possibly
6061 throw an exception. (Trying to avoid throwing an exception when
6062 dissecting options is not something we should do.) */
6063 optlen = tcph->th_hlen - TCPH_MIN_LEN20; /* length of options, in bytes */
6064 options_item = NULL((void*)0);
6065 options_tree = NULL((void*)0);
6066 if (optlen != 0) {
6067 guint bc = (guint)tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, offset + 20);
6068
6069 if (tcp_tree != NULL((void*)0)) {
6070 options_item = proto_tree_add_item(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_options, tvb, offset + 20,
6071 bc < optlen ? bc : optlen, ENC_NA0x00000000);
6072 proto_item_set_text(options_item, "Options: (%u bytes)", optlen);
6073 options_tree = proto_item_add_subtree(options_item, ett_tcp_options);
6074 }
6075 }
6076
6077 tcph->num_sack_ranges = 0;
6078
6079 /* handle TCP seq# analysis, print any extra SEQ/ACK data for this segment*/
6080 if(tcp_analyze_seq) {
6081 guint32 use_seq = tcph->th_seq;
6082 guint32 use_ack = tcph->th_ack;
6083 /* May need to recover absolute values here... */
6084 if (tcp_relative_seq) {
6085 use_seq += tcpd->fwd->base_seq;
6086 if (tcph->th_flags & TH_ACK0x0010) {
6087 use_ack += tcpd->rev->base_seq;
6088 }
6089 }
6090 tcp_print_sequence_number_analysis(pinfo, tvb, tcp_tree, tcpd, use_seq, use_ack);
6091 }
6092
6093 /* handle conversation timestamps */
6094 if(tcp_calculate_ts) {
6095 tcp_print_timestamps(pinfo, tvb, tcp_tree, tcpd, tcppd);
6096 }
6097
6098 /* Now dissect the options. */
6099 if (optlen) {
6100 dissect_ip_tcp_options(tvb, offset + 20, optlen, tcpopts, N_TCP_OPTS(sizeof tcpopts / sizeof tcpopts[0]),
6101 TCPOPT_EOL0, &TCP_OPT_TYPES,
6102 &ei_tcp_opt_len_invalid, pinfo, options_tree,
6103 options_item, tcph);
6104 }
6105
6106 if(!pinfo->fd->flags.visited) {
6107 if((tcph->th_flags & TH_SYN0x0002)==TH_SYN0x0002) {
6108 /* Check the validity of the window scale value
6109 */
6110 verify_tcp_window_scaling((tcph->th_flags&TH_ACK0x0010)==TH_ACK0x0010,tcpd);
6111 }
6112
6113 if((tcph->th_flags & (TH_SYN0x0002|TH_ACK0x0010))==(TH_SYN0x0002|TH_ACK0x0010)) {
6114 /* If the SYN or the SYN+ACK offered SCPS capabilities,
6115 * validate the flow's bidirectional scps capabilities.
6116 * The or protects against broken implementations offering
6117 * SCPS capabilities on SYN+ACK even if it wasn't offered with the SYN
6118 */
6119 if(tcpd && ((tcpd->rev->scps_capable) || (tcpd->fwd->scps_capable))) {
6120 verify_scps(pinfo, tf_syn, tcpd);
6121 }
6122
6123 }
6124 }
6125
6126 if (tcph->th_mptcp) {
6127
6128 if (tcp_analyze_mptcp) {
6129 mptcp_add_analysis_subtree(pinfo, tvb, tcp_tree, tcpd, tcpd->mptcp_analysis, tcph );
6130 }
6131 }
6132
6133 /* Skip over header + options */
6134 offset += tcph->th_hlen;
6135
6136 /* Check the packet length to see if there's more data
6137 (it could be an ACK-only packet) */
6138 captured_length_remaining = tvb_captured_length_remaining(tvb, offset);
6139
6140 if (tcph->th_have_seglen) {
6141 if(have_tap_listener(tcp_follow_tap)) {
6142 tcp_follow_tap_data_t* follow_data = wmem_new0(wmem_packet_scope(), tcp_follow_tap_data_t)((tcp_follow_tap_data_t*)wmem_alloc0((wmem_packet_scope()), sizeof
(tcp_follow_tap_data_t)));
6143
6144 follow_data->tvb = tvb_new_subset_remaining(tvb, offset);
6145 follow_data->tcph = tcph;
6146 follow_data->tcpd = tcpd;
6147
6148 tap_queue_packet(tcp_follow_tap, pinfo, follow_data);
6149 }
6150 }
6151
6152 tap_queue_packet(tcp_tap, pinfo, tcph);
6153
6154 /* if it is an MPTCP packet */
6155 if(tcpd->mptcp_analysis) {
6156 tap_queue_packet(mptcp_tap, pinfo, tcpd);
6157 }
6158
6159 /* If we're reassembling something whose length isn't known
6160 * beforehand, and that runs all the way to the end of
6161 * the data stream, a FIN indicates the end of the data
6162 * stream and thus the completion of reassembly, so we
6163 * need to explicitly check for that here.
6164 */
6165 if(tcph->th_have_seglen && tcpd && (tcph->th_flags & TH_FIN0x0001)
6166 && (tcpd->fwd->flags&TCP_FLOW_REASSEMBLE_UNTIL_FIN0x0001) ) {
6167 struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *msp;
6168
6169 /* Is this the FIN that ended the data stream or is it a
6170 * retransmission of that FIN?
6171 */
6172 if (tcpd->fwd->fin == 0 || tcpd->fwd->fin == pinfo->num) {
6173 /* Either we haven't seen a FIN for this flow or we
6174 * have and it's this frame. Note that this is the FIN
6175 * for this flow, terminate reassembly and dissect the
6176 * results. */
6177 tcpd->fwd->fin = pinfo->num;
6178 msp=(struct tcp_multisegment_pdu *)wmem_tree_lookup32_le(tcpd->fwd->multisegment_pdus, tcph->th_seq-1);
6179 if(msp) {
6180 fragment_head *ipfd_head;
6181
6182 ipfd_head = fragment_add(&tcp_reassembly_table, tvb, offset,
6183 pinfo, msp->first_frame, NULL((void*)0),
6184 tcph->th_seq - msp->seq,
6185 tcph->th_seglen,
6186 FALSE(0) );
6187 if(ipfd_head) {
6188 tvbuff_t *next_tvb;
6189
6190 /* create a new TVB structure for desegmented data
6191 * datalen-1 to strip the dummy FIN byte off
6192 */
6193 next_tvb = tvb_new_chain(tvb, ipfd_head->tvb_data);
6194
6195 /* add desegmented data to the data source list */
6196 add_new_data_source(pinfo, next_tvb, "Reassembled TCP");
6197
6198 /* Show details of the reassembly */
6199 print_tcp_fragment_tree(ipfd_head, tree, tcp_tree, pinfo, next_tvb);
6200
6201 /* call the payload dissector
6202 * but make sure we don't offer desegmentation any more
6203 */
6204 pinfo->can_desegment = 0;
6205
6206 process_tcp_payload(next_tvb, 0, pinfo, tree, tcp_tree, tcph->th_sport, tcph->th_dport, tcph->th_seq,
6207 nxtseq, FALSE(0), tcpd, &tcpinfo);
6208
6209 return tvb_captured_length(tvb);
6210 }
6211 }
6212 } else {
6213 /* Yes. This is a retransmission of the final FIN (or it's
6214 * the final FIN transmitted via a different path).
6215 * XXX - we need to flag retransmissions a bit better.
6216 */
6217 proto_tree_add_uint(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_fin_retransmission, tvb, 0, 0, tcpd->fwd->fin);
6218 }
6219 }
6220
6221 if (tcp_display_process_info && tcpd && ((tcpd->fwd && tcpd->fwd->process_info && tcpd->fwd->process_info->command) ||
6222 (tcpd->rev && tcpd->rev->process_info && tcpd->rev->process_info->command))) {
6223 field_tree = proto_tree_add_subtree(tcp_tree, tvb, offset, 0, ett_tcp_process_info, &ti, "Process Information");
6224 PROTO_ITEM_SET_GENERATED(ti)do { if (ti) do { if (((ti)->finfo)) (((ti)->finfo))->
flags = (((ti)->finfo))->flags | (0x00000002); } while(
0); } while(0);
6225 if (tcpd->fwd && tcpd->fwd->process_info && tcpd->fwd->process_info->command) {
6226 proto_tree_add_uint(field_tree, hf_tcp_proc_dst_uid, tvb, 0, 0, tcpd->fwd->process_info->process_uid);
6227 proto_tree_add_uint(field_tree, hf_tcp_proc_dst_pid, tvb, 0, 0, tcpd->fwd->process_info->process_pid);
6228 proto_tree_add_string(field_tree, hf_tcp_proc_dst_uname, tvb, 0, 0, tcpd->fwd->process_info->username);
6229 proto_tree_add_string(field_tree, hf_tcp_proc_dst_cmd, tvb, 0, 0, tcpd->fwd->process_info->command);
6230 }
6231 if (tcpd->rev && tcpd->rev->process_info && tcpd->rev->process_info->command) {
6232 proto_tree_add_uint(field_tree, hf_tcp_proc_src_uid, tvb, 0, 0, tcpd->rev->process_info->process_uid);
6233 proto_tree_add_uint(field_tree, hf_tcp_proc_src_pid, tvb, 0, 0, tcpd->rev->process_info->process_pid);
6234 proto_tree_add_string(field_tree, hf_tcp_proc_src_uname, tvb, 0, 0, tcpd->rev->process_info->username);
6235 proto_tree_add_string(field_tree, hf_tcp_proc_src_cmd, tvb, 0, 0, tcpd->rev->process_info->command);
6236 }
6237 }
6238
6239 /*
6240 * XXX - what, if any, of this should we do if this is included in an
6241 * error packet? It might be nice to see the details of the packet
6242 * that caused the ICMP error, but it might not be nice to have the
6243 * dissector update state based on it.
6244 * Also, we probably don't want to run TCP taps on those packets.
6245 */
6246 if (captured_length_remaining != 0) {
6247 if (tcph->th_flags & TH_RST0x0004) {
6248 /*
6249 * RFC1122 says:
6250 *
6251 * 4.2.2.12 RST Segment: RFC-793 Section 3.4
6252 *
6253 * A TCP SHOULD allow a received RST segment to include data.
6254 *
6255 * DISCUSSION
6256 * It has been suggested that a RST segment could contain
6257 * ASCII text that encoded and explained the cause of the
6258 * RST. No standard has yet been established for such
6259 * data.
6260 *
6261 * so for segments with RST we just display the data as text.
6262 */
6263 proto_tree_add_item(tcp_tree, hf_tcp_reset_cause, tvb, offset, captured_length_remaining, ENC_NA0x00000000|ENC_ASCII0x00000000);
6264 } else {
6265 /*
6266 * XXX - dissect_tcp_payload() expects the payload length, however
6267 * SYN and FIN increments the nxtseq by one without having
6268 * the data.
6269 */
6270 if ((tcph->th_flags&(TH_FIN0x0001|TH_SYN0x0002)) && (tcph->th_seglen > 0)) {
6271 nxtseq -= 1;
6272 }
6273 dissect_tcp_payload(tvb, pinfo, offset, tcph->th_seq, nxtseq,
6274 tcph->th_sport, tcph->th_dport, tree, tcp_tree, tcpd, &tcpinfo);
6275 }
6276 }
6277 return tvb_captured_length(tvb);
6278}
6279
6280static void
6281tcp_init(void)
6282{
6283 tcp_stream_count = 0;
6284 reassembly_table_init(&tcp_reassembly_table,
6285 &addresses_ports_reassembly_table_functions);
6286
6287 /* MPTCP init */
6288 mptcp_stream_count = 0;
6289 mptcp_tokens = wmem_tree_new(wmem_file_scope());
6290}
6291
6292static void
6293tcp_cleanup(void)
6294{
6295 reassembly_table_destroy(&tcp_reassembly_table);
6296}

7231 static build_valid_func tcp_da_src_values[1] = {tcp_src_value};
7232 static build_valid_func tcp_da_dst_values[1] = {tcp_dst_value};
7233 static build_valid_func tcp_da_both_values[2] = {tcp_src_value, tcp_dst_value};
7234 static decode_as_value_t tcp_da_values[3] = {{tcp_src_prompt, 1, tcp_da_src_values}, {tcp_dst_prompt, 1, tcp_da_dst_values}, {tcp_both_prompt, 2, tcp_da_both_values}};
7235 static decode_as_t tcp_da = {"tcp", "Transport", "tcp.port", 3, 2, tcp_da_values, "TCP", "port(s) as",
7236 decode_as_default_populate_list, decode_as_default_reset, decode_as_default_change, NULL((void*)0)};

7238 module_t *tcp_module;
7239 module_t *mptcp_module;
7240 expert_module_t* expert_tcp;
7241 expert_module_t* expert_mptcp;
7242
7243 proto_tcp = proto_register_protocol("Transmission Control Protocol", "TCP", "tcp");
7244 register_dissector("tcp", dissect_tcp, proto_tcp);
7245 proto_register_field_array(proto_tcp, hf, array_length(hf)(sizeof hf / sizeof hf[0]));
7246 proto_register_subtree_array(ett, array_length(ett)(sizeof ett / sizeof ett[0]));
7247 expert_tcp = expert_register_protocol(proto_tcp);
7248 expert_register_field_array(expert_tcp, ei, array_length(ei)(sizeof ei / sizeof ei[0]));
7249
7250 /* subdissector code */
7251 subdissector_table = register_dissector_table("tcp.port",
7252 "TCP port", proto_tcp, FT_UINT16, BASE_DEC);
7253 heur_subdissector_list = register_heur_dissector_list("tcp", proto_tcp);
7254
7255 register_capture_dissector_table("tcp.port", "TCP");
7256
7257 /* Register configuration preferences */
7258 tcp_module = prefs_register_protocol(proto_tcp, NULL((void*)0));
7259 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "summary_in_tree",
7260 "Show TCP summary in protocol tree",
7261 "Whether the TCP summary line should be shown in the protocol tree",
7262 &tcp_summary_in_tree);
7263 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "check_checksum",
7264 "Validate the TCP checksum if possible",
7265 "Whether to validate the TCP checksum or not. "
7266 "(Invalid checksums will cause reassembly, if enabled, to fail.)",
7267 &tcp_check_checksum);
7268 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "desegment_tcp_streams",
7269 "Allow subdissector to reassemble TCP streams",
7270 "Whether subdissector can request TCP streams to be reassembled",
7271 &tcp_desegment);
7272 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "analyze_sequence_numbers",
7273 "Analyze TCP sequence numbers",
7274 "Make the TCP dissector analyze TCP sequence numbers to find and flag segment retransmissions, missing segments and RTT",
7275 &tcp_analyze_seq);
7276 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "relative_sequence_numbers",
7277 "Relative sequence numbers",
7278 "Make the TCP dissector use relative sequence numbers instead of absolute ones. "
7279 "To use this option you must also enable \"Analyze TCP sequence numbers\". ",
7280 &tcp_relative_seq);
7281 prefs_register_enum_preference(tcp_module, "default_window_scaling",
7282 "Scaling factor to use when not available from capture",
7283 "Make the TCP dissector use this scaling factor for streams where the signalled scaling factor "
7284 "is not visible in the capture",
7285 &tcp_default_window_scaling, window_scaling_vals, FALSE(0));
7286
7287 /* Presumably a retired, unconditional version of what has been added back with the preference above... */
7288 prefs_register_obsolete_preference(tcp_module, "window_scaling");
7289
7290 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "track_bytes_in_flight",
7291 "Track number of bytes in flight",
7292 "Make the TCP dissector track the number on un-ACKed bytes of data are in flight per packet. "
7293 "To use this option you must also enable \"Analyze TCP sequence numbers\". "
7294 "This takes a lot of memory but allows you to track how much data are in flight at a time and graphing it in io-graphs",
7295 &tcp_track_bytes_in_flight);
7296 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "calculate_timestamps",
7297 "Calculate conversation timestamps",
7298 "Calculate timestamps relative to the first frame and the previous frame in the tcp conversation",
7299 &tcp_calculate_ts);
7300 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "try_heuristic_first",
7301 "Try heuristic sub-dissectors first",
7302 "Try to decode a packet using an heuristic sub-dissector before using a sub-dissector registered to a specific port",
7303 &try_heuristic_first);
7304 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "ignore_tcp_timestamps",
7305 "Ignore TCP Timestamps in summary",
7306 "Do not place the TCP Timestamps in the summary line",
7307 &tcp_ignore_timestamps);
7308
7309 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "no_subdissector_on_error",
7310 "Do not call subdissectors for error packets",
7311 "Do not call any subdissectors for Retransmitted or OutOfOrder segments",
7312 &tcp_no_subdissector_on_error);
7313
7314 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "dissect_experimental_options_with_magic",
7315 "TCP Experimental Options with a Magic Number",
7316 "Assume TCP Experimental Options (253, 254) have a Magic Number and use it for dissection",
7317 &tcp_exp_options_with_magic);
7318
7319 prefs_register_bool_preference(tcp_module, "display_process_info_from_ipfix",
7320 "Display process information via IPFIX",
7321 "Collect and store process information retrieved from IPFIX dissector",
7322 &tcp_display_process_info);
7323
7324 register_init_routine(tcp_init);
7325 register_cleanup_routine(tcp_cleanup);
7326
7327 register_decode_as(&tcp_da);
7328
7329 register_conversation_table(proto_tcp, FALSE(0), tcpip_conversation_packet, tcpip_hostlist_packet);
7330 register_conversation_filter("tcp", "TCP", tcp_filter_valid, tcp_build_filter);

7333 /* considers MPTCP as a distinct protocol (even if it's a TCP option) */
7334 proto_mptcp = proto_register_protocol("Multipath Transmission Control Protocol", "MPTCP", "mptcp");
7335
7336 proto_register_field_array(proto_mptcp, mptcp_hf, array_length(mptcp_hf)(sizeof mptcp_hf / sizeof mptcp_hf[0]));
7337 proto_register_subtree_array(mptcp_ett, array_length(mptcp_ett)(sizeof mptcp_ett / sizeof mptcp_ett[0]));
7338
7339 /* Register configuration preferences */
7340 mptcp_module = prefs_register_protocol(proto_mptcp, NULL((void*)0));
7341 expert_mptcp = expert_register_protocol(proto_tcp);
7342 expert_register_field_array(expert_mptcp, mptcp_ei, array_length(mptcp_ei)(sizeof mptcp_ei / sizeof mptcp_ei[0]));
7343
7344 prefs_register_bool_preference(mptcp_module, "analyze_mptcp",
7345 "Map TCP subflows to their respective MPTCP connections",
7346 "To use this option you must also enable \"Analyze TCP sequence numbers\". ",
7347 &tcp_analyze_mptcp);
7348
7349 prefs_register_bool_preference(mptcp_module, "relative_sequence_numbers",
7350 "Display relative MPTCP sequence numbers.",
7351 "In case you don't capture the key, it will use the first DSN seen",
7352 &mptcp_relative_seq);
7353
7354 prefs_register_bool_preference(mptcp_module, "analyze_mappings",
7355 "In depth analysis of Data Sequence Signal (DSS) mappings.",
7356 "You need to capture the handshake for this to work."
7357 "\"Map TCP subflows to their respective MPTCP connections\"",
7358 &mptcp_analyze_mappings);
7359
7360 prefs_register_bool_preference(mptcp_module, "intersubflows_retransmission",
7361 "Check for data duplication across subflows",
7362 "You need to enable DSS mapping analysis for this option to work",
7363 &mptcp_intersubflows_retransmission);
7364
7365 register_conversation_table(proto_mptcp, FALSE(0), mptcpip_conversation_packet, tcpip_hostlist_packet);
7366 register_follow_stream(proto_tcp, "tcp_follow", tcp_follow_conv_filter, tcp_follow_index_filter, tcp_follow_address_filter,
7367 tcp_port_to_display, follow_tcp_tap_listener);
7368}
7369
7370void
7371proto_reg_handoff_tcp(void)
7372{
7373 dissector_handle_t tcp_handle;
7374
7375 tcp_handle = find_dissector("tcp");
7376 dissector_add_uint("ip.proto", IP_PROTO_TCP6, tcp_handle);
7377 data_handle = find_dissector("data");
7378 sport_handle = find_dissector("sport");
7379 tcp_tap = register_tap("tcp");
7380 tcp_follow_tap = register_tap("tcp_follow");
7381
7382 register_capture_dissector("ip.proto", IP_PROTO_TCP6, capture_tcp, proto_tcp);
7383 register_capture_dissector("ipv6.nxt", IP_PROTO_TCP6, capture_tcp, proto_tcp);
7384
7385 mptcp_tap = register_tap("mptcp");
7386}
